In Freerun mode, SSG does not wait at half-vsync and vsync strobes to re-sync/re-start the SSG.%%0A1'b0: Disable of SSG VSYNC Freerun Mode. TAC_CLK_VALID_FILTER_CNT.Comment: RESERVED FOR TAC_CLK Clock Valid Filter Count%%0ADelay the startup of the TAC_CLK gate enable, while the TAC_CLK initial startup frequency stabilizes.%%0A16'd65535 to 16'd3 Override the TAC_CLK Clock Source Valid Status assertion for an extra TAC_CLK_VALID_FILTER_CNT clocks while blocking the Clock Gate Enable.

HSO_CLK_VALID_FILTER_CNT.Comment: HSO_CLK Clock Valid Filter Count%%0ADelay the startup of the HSO_CLK gate enable, while the HSO_CLK initial startup frequency stabilizes.%%0A16'd65535 to 16'd3 Override the HSO_CLK Clock Source Valid Status assertion for an extra HSO_CLK_VALID_FILTER_CNT clocks while blocking the Clock Gate Enable.

FRO_CLK_VALID_FILTER_CNT.Comment: FRO_CLK Clock Valid Filter Count%%0ADelay the startup of the FRO_CLK gate enable, while the FRO_CLK initial startup frequency stabilizes.%%0A12'd1023 to 12'd2 Override the FRO_CLK Clock Source Valid Status assertion for an extra FRO_CLK_VALID_FILTER_CNT clocks while blocking the Clock Gate Enable.

OSC_CLK_VALID_FILTER_CNT.Comment: OSC_CLK Clock Valid Filter Count%%0ADelay the startup of the OSC_CLK gate enable, while the OSC_CLK initial startup frequency stabilizes. This Filter is applied prior to when the OSC_CLK_DLY_CNT1 occurs.%%0A12'd1023 to 12'd2 Override the OSC_CLK Clock Source Valid Status assertion for an extra OSC_CLK_VALID_FILTER_CNT clocks while blocking the Clock Gate Enable.

OSC_CLK_DLY_CNT2.Comment: OSC_CLK Delay Count 2%%0ADelay the startup of the OSC_CLK gate enable, while the 0.1ms BG2 Enable Settling Select occurs, prior to the BG2 being fully Selected.%%0AThe counter uses OSC_CLK. This Delay is applied after when OSC_CLK_VALID_FILTER_CNT and OSC_CLK_DLY_CNT1 occurs.%%0A16'd65536 to 16'd0: Delay the BG2 Enable Settling Select for an extra OSC_CLK_DLY_CNT2 OSC_CLK clock periods. Note that the OSC_CLK and TME_WINDOW timer will continue to tick/count during the OSC_CLK_DLY_CNT2 Delay.

OSC_CLK_DLY_CNT1.Comment: OSC_CLK Delay Count 1%%0ADelay the startup of the OSC_CLK gate enable, while the 5.0ms Power-Up ramp to BG2 Enable occurs.%%0AThe counter uses FRO_CLK and is pre-divided by 750. This Delay is applied after when OSC_CLK_VALID_FILTER_CNT occurs and prior to when OSC_CLK_DLY_CNT2 occurs.%%0A16'd65536 to 16'd0: Delay BG Enable and Override the OSC_CLK Clock Source Valid Status and  assertion and the start of the TME_WINDOW timer, for an extra OSC_CLK_DLY_CNT1*750 FRO_CLK clock periods.

CLK_PHASE_FLUSH.Comment: Clock Phase Flush. Holds all primary HSO_CLK-based clocks low at the end of their respective current clock cycle. Clears all clock phase counters when all clocks are detected low. For the clocks that use the same or power-of-2 divisors relative to HSO_CLK_DIV, the 1st high phases of each of those clocks will remain in relative alignment to each other. FW must set low, prior to setting high. Note that all clocks that are to be flushed must be clk_gate enabled.

CLK_PHASE_FLUSH_ADJ.Comment: Clock Phase Flush Adjustment. Reserved for manufacting. Inserts extra alignment latency clock delay into the HSO_DIV2_CLK, which although HSO_DIV2_CLK is independent of the of the HSO_MUX_CLK tree, can be optionall be manually aligned during manufactuting tests.

APB_PCLK_DIV.Comment: APB_PCLK Clock Divider 'DIVP'. Applies to APB_PCLK and APB_PCLK_UNGATED. Firmware must program APB_PCLK_DIV to be the same as DAQ_CLK_DIV or a lesser rational power-of-2 DIVP value.%%0A4'd3, 4'd7: Reserved for Manufacturing %%0A4'd1: DIVP=APB_PCLK_DIV+1 = 2%%0A4'd0: Reserved. Will set to the default value.

HSO_CLK_DIV.Comment: HSO_CLK Clock Divider 'DIVC'. Applies to CORE_CLK_UNGATED, DEBUG_CLK. DTIM_CLK, AHB_HCLK, and HYDRA_CLK.%%0A4'd8 to 4'd15: Reserved%%0A4'd0 to 4'd07: DIVC=HSO_CLK_DIV+1 = 1 to 8

QSPI_MAS_CLK1_DIVL.Comment: QSPI_MAS_CLK1 High Phase Clock Divider 'DIVQ1L'. Automatically aligns rising edge with APB_PCLK rising edge. (QSPI_MAS_CLK1_DIVH + QSPI_MAS_CLK1_DIVL + 2) must be divisable by (APB_PCLK_DIV + 1).%%0A4'd0 to 4'd63: DIVQ1L=QSPI_MAS_CLK1_DIVL+1 = 1 to 64 clock low phase

QSPI_MAS_CLK1_DIVH.Comment: QSPI_MAS_CLK1 High Phase Clock Divider 'DIVQ1H'. Automatically aligns rising edge with APB_PCLK rising edge. (QSPI_MAS_CLK1_DIVH + QSPI_MAS_CLK1_DIVL + 2) must be divisable by (APB_PCLK_DIV + 1).%%0A4'd0 to 4'd63: DIVQH1=QSPI_MAS_CLK1_DIVH+1 = 1 to 64 clock high phase

QSPI_MAS_CLK0_DIVL.Comment: QSPI_MAS_CLK0 High Phase Clock Divider 'DIVQ0L'. Automatically aligns rising edge with APB_PCLK rising edge. (QSPI_MAS_CLK0_DIVH + QSPI_MAS_CLK0_DIVL + 2) must be divisable by (APB_PCLK_DIV + 1).%%0A4'd0 to 4'd63: DIVQ0L=QSPI_MAS_CLK0_DIVL+1 = 1 to 64 clock low phase

QSPI_MAS_CLK0_DIVH.Comment: QSPI_MAS_CLK0 High Phase Clock Divider 'DIVQ0H'. Automatically aligns rising edge with APB_PCLK rising edge. (QSPI_MAS_CLK0_DIVH + QSPI_MAS_CLK0_DIVL + 2) must be divisable by (APB_PCLK_DIV + 1).%%0A4'd0 to 4'd63: DIVQ0H=QSPI_MAS_CLK0_DIVH+1 = 1 to 64 clock high phase

CHIM_HSO_CLK_DIV.Comment: RESERVED FOR CHIM_HSO_CLK Clock Divider 'DIVCHIM'. Applies to CHIM_HSO_CLK.%%0A4'd8 to 4'd15: Reserved%%0A4'd0 to 4'd07: DIVD=CHIM_HSO_CLK_DIV+1 = 1 to 8

OSC_DIV_CLK_DIV.Comment: OSC_DIV_CLK Clock Divider 'DIVO'. Applies to IVMON Clock Root.%%0A4'd4 to 4'd15: Reserved for Manufacturing%%0A4'd1, 4'd3 DIVO=OSC_CLK_DIV+1 = 2, 4%%0A4'd2: Reserved for Manufacturing%%0A4'd0: Reserved

TAC_ALT_CLK_DIV.Comment: RESERVED FOR TAC_ALT_CLK Clock Divider 'DIVTR'. Applies to TAC Alternate Clock Root.%%0A4'd1 to 4'd15: DIVT=TAC_ALT_CLK_DIV+1 = 6 to 16%%0A4'd4: Reserved for Manufacturing%%0A4'd0 - 4d3: Reserved

LVDS_REF_PLL_ALT_CLK_DIV.Comment: LVDS_REF_PLL_ALT_CLK1/0 Clock Divider 'DIVLR'. Applies to LVDS PLL Reference Alternate Clock 1 and 0 Root.%%0A4'd2, 4'd4, 4'd6, 4'd8 to 4'd15 Reserved%%0A4'd1, 4'd3, 4'd5, 4'7: DIVLR=LVDS_REF_PLL_ALT_CLK_DIV+1 = 2, 4, 6, 8%%0A4'd0: Reserved

DISP_ALT_CLK_DIV.Comment: DISP_ALT_CLK Clock Divider 'DIVD'. Applies to Display Pixel Pipeline Alternate Clock Root.%%0A4'd2, 4'd4, 4'd6, 4'd8 to 4'd15 Reserved%%0A4'd1, 4'd3, 4'd5, 4'7: DIVD=DISP_ALT_CLK_DIV+1 = 2, 4, 6, 8%%0A4'd0: Reserved

CHIM_HSO_ALT_CLK_DIV.Comment: RESERVED FOR CHIM_HSO_ALT_CLK Clock Divider 'DIVCHR'. Applies to Touch CPU Chimera Alternate Clock Root.%%0A4'd2, 4'd4, 4'd6, 4'd8 to 4'd15 Reserved%%0A4'd1, 4'd3, 4'd5, 4'7: DIVCHR=CHIM_HSO_ALT_CLK_DIV+1 = 2, 4, 6, 8%%0A4'd0: Reserved

HSO_ALT_CLK_DIV.Comment: HSO_ALT_CLK Clock Divider 'DIVHR'. Applies to HSO Alternate Clock Root.%%0A4'd2, 4'd4, 4'd6, 4'd8 to 4'd15 Reserved%%0A4'd1, 4'd3, 4'd5, 4'7: DIVHR=HSO_ALT_CLK_DIV+1 = 2, 4, 6, 8%%0A4'd0: Reserved

LVDS_PLL_REF_CLK1_LOCK_DET_MAX.Comment: Lock Detection Maximum Count Allowed. If LVDS_PLL_REF_CLK1_LOCK_DET_SSG_EN is disabled, then the maximum count allowed. If LVDS_PLL_REF_CLK1_LOCK_DET_SSG_EN is enabled, then the Maximum Difference Allowed. FW must only change this register field value when LVDS_PLL_REF_CLK1_LOCK_DET_EN is disabled.

LVDS_PLL_REF_CLK1_LOCK_DET_MIN.Comment: Lock Detection Minimum Count Allowed. If LVDS_PLL_REF_CLK1_LOCK_DET_SSG_EN is disabled, then the minimum count allowed. If LVDS_PLL_REF_CLK1_LOCK_DET_SSG_EN is enabled, then this field is not used. FW must only change this register field value when LVDS_PLL_REF_CLK1_LOCK_DET_EN is disabled.

LVDS_PLL_REF_CLK1_LOCK_DET_ERR_ALLOW.Comment: Lock Detection Error Allowance. Number of Lock Detect Errors to allow. FW must only change this register field value when LVDS_PLL_REF_CLK1_LOCK_DET_EN is disabled.%%0A8'd0: Allow all errors.

LVDS_PLL_REF_CLK1_LOCK_DET_T_LOCK.Comment: Lock Detection Time. Time in units of REF_CLK (OSC_CLK) cycles to detect lock and latch LVDS_PLL_REF_CLK1_LOCK_DET_CNT. FW must only change this register field value when LVDS_PLL_REF_CLK1_LOCK_DET_EN is disabled. The minimum value must be larger than at least 3 and also larger than at least 3 TAR_CLK (LVDS_PLL_REF_CLK1) periods.

LVDS_PLL_REF_CLK1_LOCK_DET_LOOP_EN.Comment: Lock Detection Continuous Loop Repeat Mode. FW must only change this register field value when LVDS_PLL_REF_CLK1_LOCK_DET_EN is disabled.

LVDS_PLL_REF_CLK1_LOCK_DET_SSG_EN.Comment: Lock SSG Mode. Lock Detection. FW must only change this register field value when LVDS_PLL_REF_CLK1_LOCK_DET_EN is disabled.%%0A1'b1: Compares that the next LVDS_PLL_REF_CLK1_LOCK_DET_CNT - the current LVDS_PLL_REF_CLK1_LOCK_DET_CNT is less than or equal to LVDS_PLL_REF_CLK1_LOCK_DET_MAX.%%0A1'b0: Compares that the next LVDS_PLL_REF_CLK1_LOCK_DET_CNT is less than or equal to LVDS_PLL_REF_CLK1_LOCK_DET_MAX and greater than or equal to LVDS_PLL_REF_CLK1_LOCK_DET_MIN.

LVDS_PLL_REF_CLK1_LOCK_DET_EN.Comment: Lock Detection Enable. FW must only change this register field value no more often than once every 10 APB_PCLK cycles (once every OSC_CLK) and not near the end of the T_LOCK period. All other CLKRST_LVDS_PLL_REF_CLK1_LOCK_CTL3/2/1/0 fields must only change value when LVDS_PLL_REF_CLK1_LOCK_DET_EN is disabled.

LVDS_PLL_REF_CLK1_LOCK_DET_CNT.Comment: Lock Count. Last latched lock count each time T_LOCK count reached.

LVDS_PLL_REF_CLK1_LOCK_DET_ERR_CNT.Comment: Lock Error Count for Debug Observation. Saturates to maximum value if maximum value is reached.

CLKOUT_CNT_EN.Comment: Clock Output Counter Enable. Enable or disable counters. FW should only change this register field value no more often than once every 10 PCLK cycles. All other CLKRST_CLKOUT_CNT_CTL fields must only change value when CLKOUT_CNT_EN is disabled.%%0A1'b1: Clear all counters and then Enable%%0A1'b0: Disable and stop all counters

CLKOUT_CNT_LOOP_EN.Comment: Clock Output Counter Loop Enable. If Counters are Enabled, then continuously loop the REF_CLK_CNT counter while re-latching the TAR_CLK_CNT each time REF_CLK_CNT is reached.  FW must only change this register field value when CLKOUT_CNT_EN is disabled.%%0A1'b1: Continuously loop forever%%0A1'b0: Run loop once

CLKOUT_REF_CLK_CNT.Comment: Clock Output Reference Clock (OSC_CLK) Count Compare Value to reach in units of REF_CLK (OSC_CLK) clocks. Internal counter counts upward from zero. FW must only change this register field value when CLKOUT_CNT_EN is disabled. The minimum value must be larger than at least 3 TAR_CLK periods.

CLKOUT_TAR_CLK_CNT.Comment: Clock Output Target Clock Count Value. Latches currently selected Target Clock Output 0 Total Count each time when REF_CLK_CNT is reached. Internal counter counts upward from zero.%%0AFrequency = TAR_CLK_CNT / REF_CLK_CNT  * 24Mhz.

CLKOUT_REF_CLK_CNT_DONE.Comment: Clock Output Reference Clock Count Done. REF_CLK_CNT is reached. Clear by disabling then re-enablng CLKOUT_CNT_EN.

LSO_DISABLE_KEY.Comment: Values other than the key enable LSO clock. See Reference manual for the key for debug only.

L2_SOFT_RST.Comment: L2 Soft Reset%%0A1'b1: Set Soft Reset. Self-clears.%%0A1'b0: No-action.

APB_PERIPH_SOFT_RST.Comment: APB Peripheral Soft Reset%%0A1'b1: Set Soft Reset. Self-clears.%%0A1'b0: No-action.

AHB_PERIPH_SOFT_RST.Comment: AHB Peripheral Soft Reset%%0A1'b1: Set Soft Reset. Self-clears.%%0A1'b0: No-action.

CORE_SOFT_RST.Comment: CPU Core Soft Reset%%0A1'b1: Set Soft Reset. Self-clears.%%0A1'b0: No-action.

AFE_OVRD_RST.Comment: RESERVED FOR AFE Override Reset (Soft Reset)%%0AFirmware is expected to set AFE_OVRD_RESET for as long as needed to meet the minimum AFE Reset pulse width, then clear AFE_OVRD_RESET.%%0A1'b1: Set (override) AFE Reset.%%0A1'b0: Clear (don't-override) AFE Reset. Depending on the specific ASIC, the specific ASIC may have another functional means of setting/clearing AFE Reset. For DIG2409, no such other functional means exists, so AFE_OVRD_RESET=0 clears AFE Reset.

RST_REASON.Comment: Reset Reason%%0ARESERVED FOR 0x20: Wake up from the hibernate powered down mode.%%0A0x18: Reset from CLKRST_RST_CTL.CORE_SOFT_RST register field being set.%%0A0x13: Reset from CLKRST_RST_CTL.L2_SOFT_RST register field being set.%%0A0x12: Reset from CPU (Depends on the specific ASIC. For SB7900, Reset from the Display CPU does not occur).%%0A0x11: WDT (Watchdog) Timeout%%0A0x10: DEBUG_NDRESET (Debug NDMRESET Register Field) Timeout%%0A0x08: Pin-based Hard Reset (RESET_N). Note that RESET_N detection depends on RESET_N asserting while the OSC_CLK is active.%%0A0x01: POR (Power-On Reset) assertion%%0A0x00: No reason recorded

RST_PC.Comment: Reset Program Counter Value. On Reset, captures the last CPU Fetch PC, just prior to the Reset.

GPT1_CFG.Description: Timer #1 control register%%0ANote:  Any write to this register will automatically reset timer #1

GPT1_DMA_CAPTURE.Comment: Set to 1 to enable DMA on timer capture%%0ADIG2409 does not implement DMA for timers; it implements but ignores this mode bit

GPT1_IEN_CAPTURE.Comment: If 1, timer capture sets the timer's interrupt flag

GPT1_IEN_OVERFLOW.Comment: If 1, timer overflow to 0xFFFFFFFF sets the interrupt flag

GPT1_IEN_MATCH.Comment: If 1, timer count > target sets the interrupt flag

GPT1_DEBUG_HALT.Comment: Set to 1 to freeze the timer when CPU is halted for debug

GPT1_INIT_ENABLE.Comment: If 1, timer starts out enabled after any timer reset

GPT1_WRAP.Comment: Timer wraparound mode%%0A0: Timer counts up to 0xFFFFFFFF and then stops%%0A1: Timer wraps around from target to 0x0%%0A2: Timer wraps around from 0xFFFFFFFF to 0x0

GPT1_DIVIDE.Comment: If non-zero, divide the timer source clock by N+1

GPT1_SOURCE.Comment: Select the source clock to drive the timer%%0A0: No clock  (timer is disabled)%%0A1: CPU clock%%0A2: HSO oscillator clock%%0A3: MSO oscillator clock%%0A4: XCLK external clock%%0A5: XTAL oscillator clock%%0A6: LSO oscillator clock

GPT1_OVERRUN.Comment: Read-only view of capture overrun flag

GPT1_INTR.Comment: Read-only view of the timer's interrupt flag%%0AThis flag is set by various interrupting events in the timer and it is cleared by IACK or when the timer resets%%0AWhen this flag is high, the timer asserts a CPU interrupt but only if its IMASK is clear

GPT1_ENABLE.Comment: Read-only view of the timer's enable state%%0AThe enable state resets to GPT1_INIT_ENABLE when the timer resets; after that, it can be set or cleared by writing to GPT_START or GPT_STOP, or by START/STOP trigger events

GPT1_IACK.Comment: Any read or write to this register acknowledges timer #1's interrupt, clearing its interrupt flag

GPT1_TRIGSEL.Description: Timer #1 trigger selection register%%0ANote:  Any write to this register automatically resets this timer

GPT1_TRIGSEL_CAPTURE.Comment: Set to 1-3 to cause trigger #N to capture this timer

GPT1_TRIGSEL_RESTART.Comment: Set to 1-3 to cause trigger #N to restart this timer at zero

GPT1_TRIGSEL_COUNT.Comment: Set to 1-3 to cause trigger #N to increment the timer, or set to 0 for the timer to increment continuously at the rate of its source clock

GPT1_TRIGSEL_STOP.Comment: Set to 1-3 to cause trigger #N to stop this timer (this clears the timer's ENABLE state, freezing its counter)

GPT1_TRIGSEL_START.Comment: Set to 1-3 to cause trigger #N to start this timer (this sets the timer's ENABLE state, un-freezing its counter)

GPT1_COUNT.Comment: A read-only view of the timer's current count%%0AThe count resets to 0 when the timer resets or restarts%%0AThen the timer increments either continuously or counting trigger events, depending on TRIGSEL_COUNT

GPT1_TARGET.Description: Timer #1 target register%%0ANote:  Any write to this register automatically resets the timer

GPT1_TARGET.Comment: The comparison target value for the register%%0ADepending on the timer's settings, the timer may generate an interrupt, wrap to zero, and/or trigger another timer when its COUNT increments past its TARGET

GPT1_CAPTURE.Comment: A read-only view of the timer's capture register%%0AThis loads from COUNT upon a TRIGSEL_CAPTURE event, and it clears to zero when the timer resets%%0AIf TRIGSEL_CAPTURE is 0, this register is unused

GPT3_CFG.Description: Timer #3 control register%%0ASee the description of GPT1_CFG

GPT4_CFG.Description: Timer #4 control register%%0ASee the description of GPT1_CFG

GPT_IMASK.Description: Global interrupt masking state for all timers

IMASK.Comment: A read-only view of the IMASK bits of all timers%%0ABit #N shows the IMASK bit for timer #N%%0ATimer #N sends the CPU an interrupt whenever its INTR flag is high and its IMASK bit is clear

GPT_START.Description: Global timer enable register for all timers

START.Comment: Write 1 to bit #N to set timer #N's ENABLE state

GPT_STOP.Description: Global timer disable register for all timers

STOP.Comment: Write 1 to bit #N to clear timer #N's ENABLE state

FORCE_CLK2.Comment: Set to 1 to override the clock source #2 signal using the testbench  (on DIG2409, clock source #2 is 'HSO')

GPT_TEST_OUT.Description: Testbench output register%%0AThis register exists only if GPT_TEST_ID.SIG != 0

GPT_TEST_STIM.Description: Testbench stimulus register%%0AThis register exists only if GPT_TEST_ID.SIG2 != 0

HALTED.Comment: Drives the 'halted' signal when FORCE is set

CLKS.Comment: Set to 1 to force all clock sources other than FCLK and PCLK to be under testbench control

FORCE.Comment: Set to 1 to force all non-clock inputs to the timers to be under testbench control

SEL.Comment: Select which input signal to drive in FORCE or CLKS mode%%0A0: Do not drive any signal high%%0A2-6: Drive clock source #N high%%0A48-TBD: Drive misc trigger input #N high%%0A64-TBD: Drive GPIO trigger input #N high%%0A128-TBD: Drive CPU interrupt trigger input #N high

GPT_TEST_DRIVE.Description: Testbench drive register%%0AThis register exists only if GPT_TEST_ID.SIG2 != 0

DRIVE_CLEAR.Comment: Write 1 to this bit to clear WATCH_COUNT to zero

DRIVE_PULSE.Comment: Write 1 to this bit to generate a one-cycle pulse on the input selected by GPT_TEST_STIM.SEL

DRIVE_LEVEL.Comment: Set to 1 to continuously drive high the input selected by GPT_TEST_STIM.SEL

GPT_TEST_WATCH.Description: Testbench watch register%%0AThis register exists only if GPT_TEST_ID.SIG2 != 0

WATCH_INTR.Comment: Readable view of the timer interrupt output signals

WATCH_WAKEUP.Comment: Readable view of the timer wakeup output signal

NUM_BITS.Comment: Number of bits in the timers

SYNC_DELAY.Comment: Number of stages in synchronizers used in the timers%%0A(TBD: This number may change to 3 depending on impl)

NUM_COMPARES.Comment: Number of timers with COMPARE registers%%0AThis feature is not used in DIG2409

NUM_PULSES.Comment: Number of pulse output signals from the timers module%%0AThis feature is not used in DIG2409

NUM_TRIGGERS.Comment: Number of independent triggers (this is the number of GPT_TRIGGER registers)

NUM_SOURCES.Comment: Number of available clock sources (maximum setting of GPT_CFG.SOURCE)

SCH_RESET.Comment: Active high soft reset for CH_SCH%%0A1: Reset%%0A0: Normal

INT_EN0.Comment: Interrupt enable. Interrupt is generated at the end of transfer.

DCO0.Comment: Transfer Count (number of double words in BYTE_MODE=0, else bytes)

TRANS_DONE.Comment: Each bit shows the corresponding DMA channel transfer done status.%%0A1: Transfer is done%%0A0: Transfer is not done.

I2C_SLV_TX.Description: Data to be Transmitted to the Host

IS_IDLE.Comment: If this bit is clear, this device has been selected

SCL_FALL.Comment: This bit is set when SINGLE_STEP is set and falling edge of SCL is observed.%%0AIt is cleared by setting SCL_CLAMP_DONE or by clearing SINGLE_STEP.

IS_ADDR.Comment: Indicates that RX_DATA contains slave address and R/W bit

DATA_FLAG.Comment: New data is available or CPU should provide new data

END_FLAG.Comment: One of the end conditions detected

START_FLAG.Comment: Indicates that a start condition is detected

SDA_ST.Comment: Indicates SDA state.%%0A2'b00: SDA constant low%%0A2'b01: STOP detected%%0A2'b10: START detected%%0A2'b11: Constant high

XFER_END_REASON.Comment: Bit 5: SMBus timeout%%0ABit 4: Stretch-inhibit bus error%%0ABit 3: Arbitration failure%%0ABit 2: Repeated start%%0ABit 1: Stop%%0ABit 0: NACK

BUS_IDLE_FLAG.Comment: Indicates if the I2C bus is idle.  Bit is clear when HSO is off.  Set when HSO is running.

MANUAL_UNGATE_CLK.Comment: Manual override bit for clock gating. Set this bit to enable the peripheral's clocks.

WAKE_TO_EN.Comment: Wake timeout enable.  Enables counter that counts from START to first SCL falling edge.

SINGLE_STEP.Comment: Enables interrupt generation on every SCL falling edge

TO_EN.Comment: Bit to enable timeout of stretch period

STR_INH.Comment: Setting this bit turns off ability of hardware to stretch the clock

AUTO_ACK.Comment: Bit to allow hardware to acknowledge transfers

EN.Comment: Bit to enable I2C state machine

SCL_CLAMP_DONE.Comment: Writing to this register will clear the SCL fall interrupt

NACK_DONE.Comment: Setting this bit clears the ACK interrupt%%0AWhen AUTO_ACK or AUTO_MATCH bits are 0, writing to this bit sends a NACK

ACK_DONE.Comment: Setting this bit clears the ACK interrupt%%0AWhen AUTO_ACK or AUTO_MATCH bits are 0, writing to this bit sends a ACK

DATA_DONE.Comment: Writing this bit clears DATA interrupt condition

END_DONE.Comment: Writing this bit clears END interrupt condition

START_DONE.Comment: Writing this bit clears START interrupt condition

I2C_SLV_GPIO.Description: CAUTION: The GPIO register controls the pins at the peripheral block only. It does NOT control the ASIC GPIO pins. There is a separate register for that purpose. Both need to be properly configured to allow the peripheral interface to function properly.

SCL_PIN.Comment: Value or SCL pin as seen by I2C Slave

SDA_PIN.Comment: Value of SDA pin as seen by I2C Slave

ADDR_STRETCH_EN.Comment: Enable clock stretching during slave address byte

AUTO_MODE_EN.Comment: RESERVED FOR: Enable buffer controller mode

DEV_ADDR.Comment: Holds the I2C slave device address

AUTO_MATCH.Comment: Setting this bit enables hardware address comparison%%0AIf this bit is clear, firmware is responsible for address comparison

I2C_SLV_TIMING.Description: Setup and Hold Time Values in Terms of System Clock Count

SETUP_VALUE.Comment: Duration in system clock count to hold SCL low after a SDA transition

HOLD_VALUE.Comment: Duration in system clock count to hold data after falling edge of SCL

TO_VALUE.Comment: Duration in system clock count before SCL low period timeout

TX_FIFO_WATERMARK_FLAG.Comment: Interrupt flag for TX_FIFO watermark. %%0AShows TX_FIFO_DATACOUNT is less than or equal to TX_FIFO_WATERMARK_THR. %%0AThis is for non-DMA mode. FW can use this flag as almost_empty status.

RX_FIFO_WATERMARK_FLAG.Comment: Interrupt flag for RX_FIFO watermark. %%0AShows RX_FIFO_DATACOUNT is grater than or equal to RX_FIFO_WATERMARK_THR. %%0AThis is for non-DMA mode. FW can use this flag as almost full status.

XFER_ERR_FLAG.Comment: RESERVED FOR: STOP before byte completed

ADDR_STRETCH_FLAG.Comment: SCL is being stretched during the slave address byte after matching; Cleared by clearing ADDR_STRETCH_EN

SDA_SYNC_SAMPLE.Comment: 2'd0: Sample sync FSM SDA with _d3 delay tap (high-speed setting). Note: legacy-based project may use _d2 tap.%%0A2'd1: Sample sync FSM SDA with _d2 delay tap (legacy low-speed setting). Note: legacy-based project may use _d3 tap.%%0A2'd2: Sample sync FSM SDA with _d4 delay tap (very high-speed setting. %%0A2'd3: Sample sync FSM SDA with scl_thigh delay tap.

SCL_DELAY_OVRD.Comment: 2'd0: Use SCL with default delay, HS_MODE_EN uses 2FF, else no delay. %%0A2'd1: Use SCL with 1FF delay.%%0A2'd2: Use SCL with 2FF delay.%%0A2'd3: RESERVED.

HW_RST_DET_DIS.Comment: RESERVED FOR: Disable of hardware reset detect over I2C

EP0_OUT_DET_DIS.Comment: RESERVED FOR: EP0 OUT detect disable - this logic grabs the DFT word over I2C

XFER_ERR_IEN.Comment: RESERVED FOR: Interrupt enable for XFER_ERR_FLAG

HS_DUMMY_DATA_HOLD_EN.Comment: Enable extra hold time on High-speed-mode ACK when HSO is off and both HS_DUMMY_DATA_EN and HS_ADDR_STRETCH_EN are also enabled.%%0A3'd0: Default of 0 PCLK hold time; %%0A3'd1: 1 PCLK hold time%%0A3'd2: 2 PCLK hold time%%0A3'd3: 3 PCLK hold time%%0A3'd4-3'd6: RESERVED%%0A3'd7: Use HOLD_VALUE.

HS_DUMMY_DATA_EN.Comment: Enable DUMMY_DATA fill-in data value to be transferred on RX_DATA for the 1st byte of a read transaction.

HS_DUMMY_DATA.Comment: 8-bit dummy fill-in data value to be transferred on RX_DATA underflow.

HS_RX_DATA_OF_FLAG.Comment: Sets if RX_DATA is already full and overflows when the load is attempted from the internal de-serializer. Automatically clears when HS_RX_DATA_FLUSH is set.

HS_TX_DATA_UF_FLAG.Comment: Sets if TX_DATA is empty and underflows when its invalid value is loaded into the internal serializer. If HS_DUMMY_DATA_EN is set, then this FLAG potentially sets only after the 1st byte. Automatically clears when HS_TX_DATA_FLUSH is set.

HS_RX_NOT_EMPTY_FLAG.Comment: After HS_MODE_EN is set, this FLAG sets if RX_DATA is not empty.  Automatically clears when RX_DATA read causes RX_DATA to be empty.

HS_TX_NOT_FULL_FLAG.Comment: After HS_MODE_EN is set, this FLAG sets if TX_DATA is not full. If HS_DUMMY_DATA_EN is set, then this FLAG sets only after the 1st byte. Automatically clears when TX_DATA write causes TX_DATA to be full.

SCL_HS_PAD_DIS.Comment: If present, High-speed-mode I/O drive disable for the SCL pin. By the default, the SCL pin has the highest I/O pad drive stength available, unless this field is set. If misc_ctl.A[]_DRV_STR register field is present, the SCL_HS_PAD_DIS is not used nor applicable.

SDA_HS_PAD_DIS.Comment: If present, High-speed-mode I/O drive disable for the SDA pin. By the default, the SDA pin has the highest I/O pad drive stength available, unless this field is set. If misc_ctl.A[]_DRV_STR register field is present, the SCL_HS_PAD_DIS is not used nor applicable.

HS_FLUSH_RX_DATA.Comment: Flush RX_DATA to an empty condition. Automatically clears HS_RX_DATA_OF_FLAG.

HS_FLUSH_TX_DATA.Comment: Flush TX_DATA to an empty condition. Automatically clears HS_TX_DATA_UF_FLAG.

HS_MODE_RX_TX_DATA_OVRD.Comment: Enable HS RX/TX DATA and FLAGs even when HS_MODE_EN is disabled.

HS_MODE_SLOW_START_DIS.Comment: Disable slow_start feature completely, even if HS_MODE_SLOW_START_OVRD is set.

HS_MODE_SLOW_START_OVRD.Comment: Override slow_start feature to always be in use. Usually disabled when hs_mode_en or addr_stretch_en is active.

HS_MODE_CLK_GATE_STOP_DIS.Comment: Disable High-speed-mode ability to keep clock gating enabled to main FSM if STOP bit is detected.

HS_MODE_DEGLITCH_DIS.Comment: Disable High-speed-mode 10ns de-glitchers on SCL and SDA inputs and use the 50ns de-glitchers.

HS_MODE_LEGACY_DIS.Comment: Disable non-High-speed-mode backward compatibility of masking out I2C_SLV_DEV_ADDR bits 15:8 from being read as non-zero. In other words, allow all I2C speeds to read I2C_SLV_STS bits 15:8. Also allow use of to_det_dly instead of to_det for start_hold handshake.

HS_MODE_LEGACY_ASE_MODE_EN.Comment: Enable legacy address stretch enable feature using ADDR_STRETCH_EN.

HS_MODE_EN.Comment: Enable High-speed-mode entry/exit detection, transactions and when in High-speed-mode, select the 10ns SCL/SDA input de-glitcher, HS_SETUP_VALUE, HS_HOLD_VALUE and HS_TO_VALUE.

HS_ADDR_DATA_FLAG_EN.Comment: Enable IS_ADDR and DATA_FLAG during master code.

HS_ADDR_STRETCH_EN.Comment: Enable clock stretching during High-speed-mode master code.

HS_AUTO_MODE_EN.Comment: Enable High-speed-mode automatic data transfers between RX_DATA buffer from RX de-serializer and TX_DATA buffer to TX serializer. Current RX_DATA must be unloaded prior to the next byte's DATA_FLAG. Current TX_DATA must be pre-loaded prior to the next byte's DATA_FLAG.

HS_MAS_CODE_MASK.Comment: Each mask bit enables a corresponding High-speed-mode master code: 0: 0x08; 1: 0x09; 2: 0x0A; and so on; 7: 0x0F. When HS_MODE_EN=1, 0xFF is the only valid value. 0x00-0xFE values are RESERVED.

I2C_SLV_HS_TIMING.Description: High-speed-mode setup and hold time values in terms of clock count.

HS_SETUP_VALUE.Comment: Duration in clock count to hold SCL low after a SDA transistion. HS_SETUP_VALUE is used only during High-speed-mode.

HS_HOLD_VALUE.Comment: Duration in clock count to hold data after falling edge of SCL. HS_HOLD_VALUE is used only during High-speed-mode.

HS_TO_VALUE.Comment: Duration in clock count before SCL low period timeout. Value of 0x0000 disables the timeout counter. HS_TO_VALUE is used only during High-speed-mode.

HS_ADDR_STRETCH_FLAG.Comment: SCL is being stretched during the slave address byte after matching; Cleared by clearing HS_ADDR_STRETCH_EN

CRC_LSB_FIRST.Comment: 0: Write upper 8-bit of CRC into TX_FIFO%%0A1: Write lower 8-bit of CRC into TX_FIFO

AUTO_CRC_INS_EN.Comment: Automatically insert CRC to TX_FIFO when DMA transfer is done.

AUTO_POP_EN.Comment: When 1 allows the RX_FIFO read data pointer to auto-increment when the RX_FIFO is read. Otherwise the FW must write the RX_FIFO_POP bit to increment the pointer.

I2C_SLV_FIFO_CMD.Description: I2C Slave FIFO Command register.  Used for Flushing the FIFOs and Popping the Rx FIFO

RX_FIFO_POP.Comment: If AUTO_POP_EN==0 the FW must write this bit to a 1 after reading RX_DATA to increment the RX_FIFO read pointer.  IF AUTO_POP_EN==1, then writing to this bit has no effect.

RX_FLUSH.Comment: Write to 1 to flush (Reset) the RX_FIFO

TX_FLUSH.Comment: Write to 1 to flush (Reset) the TX_FIFO

TX_FIFO_DATACOUNT.Comment: Number of filled slots in the FIFO

RX_FIFO_DATACOUNT.Comment: Number of filled slots in the FIFO

TX_FIFO_WATERMARK_THR.Comment: TX_FIFO watermark threshold.%%0AThis is used to generate TX_FIFO_WATERMARK_FLAG.%%0AThis is considered as almost empty level in non-DMA mode while it's considered as almost_full in DMA mode.%%0ADMA will stop writing TX_FIFO when TX_FIFO_DATACOUNT is greater than or equal to this value.

RX_FIFO_WATERMARK_THR.Comment: RX_FIFO watermark threshold%%0AThis is used to generate RX_FIFO_WATERMARK_FLAG.%%0AThis is considered as almost full level in non-DMA mode while it's considered as almost empty in DMA mode. %%0ADMA will start reading RX_FIFO when RX_FIFO_DATACOUNT is greater than or equal to this value.

TX_COUNTER.Comment: Number of bytes sent. Cleared when TX_COUNTER_CLR is set.

RX_COUNTER.Comment: Number of bytes received. Cleared when RX_COUNTER_CLR is set.

TX_DATA.Comment: TX FIFO data: This 8-bit data will be stored in TX FIFO.

RX_DATA.Comment: RX FIFO data: This 8-bit data indicates the data in RX FIFO, pointed by read pointer

CLK_DETECTED.Comment: This bit indicates that SCK is toggling when set.

TX_LEVEL.Comment: TX Level flag: This flag indicates that TX_BYTES is less than or equal to TX_THRESHOLD.%%0AThis is for non-DMA mode. FW can use this flag as almost empty status.

RX_LEVEL.Comment: RX LEVEL Flag: This is flag indicates that RX_BYTES is greater than or equal to RX_THRESHOLD.%%0AThis is for non-DMA mode. FW can use this flag as almost full status.

RX_FULL.Comment: RX FIFO full status: Set when RX FIFO is full. Cleared by hardware when RX FIFO is not full.

RX_EMPTY.Comment: RX FIFO empty status: Set when RX FIFO is empty. Cleared by hardware when RX FIFO is not empty.

TX_FULL.Comment: TX FIFO full status: Set when TX FIFO is full. Cleared by hardware when TX FIFO is not full.

TX_EMPTY.Comment: TX FIFO empty status: Set when TX FIFO is empty. Cleared by hardware when TX FIFO is not empty.

SPIE_SLV_0_CFG.Description: SPI Slave Configuration Registe.  Sets SPI operational parameters and enables/disables interrupt sources.

SRQ_STATE.Comment: Holds the value to drive MISO during the SRQ state when%%0A TX_ERROR = 0

SPIE_SLV_0_CTL.Description: SPI Slave Control register.  Used for clearing interrupt/status conditions and to issue transfer cancel command.

CRC_LSB_FIRST.Comment: 0: Write upper 8-bit of CRC into TX_FIFO%%0A1: Write lower 8-bit of CRC into TX_FIFO

AUTO_CRC_INS_EN.Comment: Automatically insert CRC to TX_FIFO when DMA transfer is done.

RX_FIFO_POP.Comment: If AUTO_POP_EN==0 the FW must write this bit to a 1 after reading RX_DATA to increment the RX_FIFO read pointer.  IF AUTO_POP_EN==1, then writing to this bit has no effect.

RX_FLUSH.Comment: Write to 1 to flush (Reset) the RX_FIFO

TX_FLUSH.Comment: Write to 1 to flush (Reset) the TX_FIFO

TX_STALL_SETUP_TIME.Comment: Use legacy mode with 1 PCLK MOSI data setup time prior to SPI MODE 0 and 2 TX_FIFO Stall re-start of 1st SCK clock edge. Otherwise use half-virtual-SCK-clock MOSI data setup time prior to SPI MODE 0 and 2 TX_FIFO Stall re-start of 1st SCK clock edge.

STALL_STS_MODE.Comment: Use legacy mode with all status and interrupts delayed whenever a stall occurs at the end of a MODE1/3 transaction. Otherwise only the stall related status and interrupt itself are delayed whenever a stall occurs at the end of a MODE1/3 transaction.

MOSI_HOLD_TIME.Comment: MOSI Hold Time for SPI Mode 1 and 3 (CPHA = 1). %%0A0 = Auto insert MOSI Hold Time of 1/2 virtual SCK cycle if CLK_RATIO > 0. %%0A1 = Auto insert MOSI Hold Time of 3 PCLK's if CLK_RATIO > 1. %%0A2 = Reserved. %%0A3 = Auto insert MOSI Hold time of 1 PCLK.

FC_READ_EN.Comment: Full Cycle Read Enable. Allows for using a full SCK cycle for read data. Usable only in MODE 0. Not meant for normal operation.

SPI_MAS_EN.Comment: Enable the SPI Master engine, including local module and chip top shared I/O controls.

CLK_RATIO2_EN.Comment: Enable use of CLK_RATIO for 1st clock edge and CLK_RATIO2 for 2nd clock edge.

CLK_RATIO2.Comment: If enabled by CLK_RATIO2_EN, value loaded into down-counter at middle of clock phase.

CRC_INS_REQ.Comment: CRC insertion request. Need to be cleared for next packet.%%0A1 = Insert 2-byte CRC data into TX_FIFO

CRC_LSB_FIRST.Comment: 0: Write upper 8-bit of CRC into TX_FIFO%%0A1: Write lower 8-bit of CRC into TX_FIFO

AUTO_CRC_INS_EN.Comment: Automatically insert CRC to TX_FIFO when CRC_INSERT_REQ is set.

TRIM_LAST.Comment: valid only when byte_mode==0 (32 bit transfer, little endian)%%0A0=do not trim, 1=trim last byte, 2=trim last 2 bytes, 3=trim last 3 bytes

CRC_LSB_FIRST.Comment: 0: Write upper 8-bit of CRC into TX_FIFO%%0A1: Write lower 8-bit of CRC into TX_FIFO

AUTO_CRC_INS_EN.Comment: Automatically insert CRC to TX_FIFO when DMA transfer is done.

AUTO_POP_EN.Comment: When 1 allows the RX_FIFO read data pointer to auto-increment when the RX_FIFO is read. Otherwise the FW must write the RX_FIFO_POP bit to increment the RX_FIFO read pointer.

USE_NOT_INV_MAS_RX_CLK.Comment: Available in master mode only%%0A1: Use non-inverted RX_CLK

INST_MODE.Comment: Controls how instruction is sent thru single, dual or quad IO pads.%%0A00: Reserved%%0A01: Instruction is sent to thru IO0 pad only even in quad spi mode.%%0A10: Instruction is sent to thru IO0 and IO1 pads only even in quad spi mode.%%0A11: Instruction is sent to thru IO0, IO1, IO2 and IO3 pads.

IO_MODE.Comment: 00: Reserved%%0A01: Single SPI mode%%0A10: Dual SPI mode%%0A11: Quad SPI mode

MAS_MODE.Comment: QSPI is defult in Master mode

QSPI_EN.Comment: 0: Disable QSPI block, 1: Enable QSPI block

DUMMY_END.Comment: Number of QSPI_CLK cycles before Dummy ends for bus turnaround.

DUMMY_START.Comment: Number of QSPI_CLK cycles before Dummy starts for bus turnaround. QSPI_IO0-3 needs to be driven by high-Z during dummy period. Dummy counter starts once the first byte data is sent (in Master) or received (in Slave).

RX_FIFO_POP.Comment: If AUTO_POP_EN==0 the FW must write this bit to a 1 after reading RX_DATA to increment the RX_FIFO read pointer.  IF AUTO_POP_EN==1, then writing to this bit has no effect.

TX_FIFO_RESET.Comment: 1: Active high reset for TX_FIFO, 0: Normal

RX_FIFO_RESET.Comment: 1: Active high reset for RX_FIFO, 0: Normal

FSM_RESET.Comment: 1: Active high reset for FSM, 0: Normal

NUM_EXT_CLK.Comment: Send number of extra QSPI_CLK to SLAVE to store the last captured byte to TX_FIFO. Extra QSPI_CLK and QSPI_CS need to be driven in Master mode.

SEND_PKT_IS_READ.Comment: 1: Packet that is being sent is for read, 0: Packet that is being sent is for write.

SEND_PKT.Comment: 1: Start Master FSM to send byte data stored in TX_FIFO. (Core needs to store byte data before this bit is set to '1')

RCVD_PKT_IS_READ.Comment: 1: Received packet is for read. 0: Received packet is for write.

TX_FIFO_DATA.Comment: Byte data stored in this register is transferred to TX_FIFO when TX_FIFO_WR is set.

QSPI_TX_FIFO_NUM_BYTES_TO_SEND_LOW.Description: QSPI TX_FIFO number of bytes to send LSB

TX_FIFO_NUM_BYTES_TO_SEND_LOW.Comment: LSB number of bytes to send from TX_FIFO

QSPI_TX_FIFO_NUM_BYTES_TO_SEND_HIGH.Description: QSPI TX_FIFO number of bytes to send MSB

TX_FIFO_NUM_BYTES_TO_SEND_HIGH.Comment: MSB number of bytes to send from TX_FIFO

TX_FIFO_WATERMARK_THR.Comment: TX_FIFO Watermark threshold level for TFWMI interrupt

TX_FIFO_UR_DATA.Comment: This value is sent if TX_FIFO is underrun.

RX_FIFO_DATA.Comment: Byte data read from RX_FIFO is stored in this register when RX_FIFO_RD is set.

ADDR_MODE.Comment: Controls how address is sent thru single, dual or quad IO pads.%%0A00: Reserved%%0A01: Instruction is sent to thru IO0 pad only even in quad spi mode.%%0A10: Instruction is sent to thru IO0 and IO1 pads only even in quad spi mode.%%0A11: Instruction is sent to thru IO0, IO1, IO2 and IO3 pads.

CRC_LSB_FIRST.Comment: 0: Write upper 8-bit of CRC into TX_FIFO%%0A1: Write lower 8-bit of CRC into TX_FIFO

AUTO_CRC_INS_EN.Comment: Automatically insert CRC to TX_FIFO when DMA transfer is done.

AUTO_POP_EN.Comment: When 1 allows the RX_FIFO read data pointer to auto-increment when the RX_FIFO is read. Otherwise the FW must write the RX_FIFO_POP bit to increment the RX_FIFO read pointer.

USE_NOT_INV_MAS_RX_CLK.Comment: Available in master mode only%%0A1: Use non-inverted RX_CLK

INST_MODE.Comment: Controls how instruction is sent thru single, dual or quad IO pads.%%0A00: Reserved%%0A01: Instruction is sent to thru IO0 pad only even in quad spi mode.%%0A10: Instruction is sent to thru IO0 and IO1 pads only even in quad spi mode.%%0A11: Instruction is sent to thru IO0, IO1, IO2 and IO3 pads.

IO_MODE.Comment: 00: Reserved%%0A01: Single SPI mode%%0A10: Dual SPI mode%%0A11: Quad SPI mode

MAS_MODE.Comment: FLASH QSPI is defult in Master mode

QSPI_EN.Comment: 0: Disable QSPI block, 1: Enable QSPI block

DUMMY_END.Comment: Number of QSPI_CLK cycles before Dummy ends for bus turnaround.

DUMMY_START.Comment: Number of QSPI_CLK cycles before Dummy starts for bus turnaround. QSPI_IO0-3 needs to be driven by high-Z during dummy period. Dummy counter starts once the first byte data is sent (in Master) or received (in Slave).

RX_FIFO_POP.Comment: If AUTO_POP_EN==0 the FW must write this bit to a 1 after reading RX_DATA to increment the RX_FIFO read pointer.  IF AUTO_POP_EN==1, then writing to this bit has no effect.

TX_FIFO_RESET.Comment: 1: Active high reset for TX_FIFO, 0: Normal

RX_FIFO_RESET.Comment: 1: Active high reset for RX_FIFO, 0: Normal

FSM_RESET.Comment: 1: Active high reset for FSM, 0: Normal

NUM_EXT_CLK.Comment: Send number of extra QSPI_CLK to SLAVE to store the last captured byte to TX_FIFO. Extra QSPI_CLK and QSPI_CS need to be driven in Master mode.

SEND_PKT_IS_READ.Comment: 1: Packet that is being sent is for read, 0: Packet that is being sent is for write.

SEND_PKT.Comment: 1: Start Master FSM to send byte data stored in TX_FIFO. (Core needs to store byte data before this bit is set to '1')

RCVD_PKT_IS_READ.Comment: 1: Received packet is for read. 0: Received packet is for write.

TX_FIFO_DATA.Comment: Byte data stored in this register is transferred to TX_FIFO when TX_FIFO_WR is set.

W.Comment: Value of this bit get map to W pin in SIG/DUAL mode. W pin shared with IO2. '1' design will drive value 1 on W pin . '0' design will drive value 0 on W pin. Note: W pin on flash is active low, delault W protection disabled.

HOLD.Comment: Value of this bit get map to HOLD pin in SIG/DUAL mode.HOLD pin shared with IO3. '1' design will drive value 1 on HOLD pin . '0' design will drive value 0 on HOLD pin. Note: HOLD pin on flash is active low., default HOLD operation disabled.

W_OE.Comment: Output enable for W (write protect) pin in SIG/DUAL mode. This is tri state buf enable which gets map to qspi_io_oe[2]. '1' W pin on flash get driven by Design. '0' HOLD pin not get driven by design

HOLD_OE.Comment: Output enable for HOLD pin in SIG/DUAL mode.This is tri state buf enable which gets map to qspi_io_oe[3]. '1' HOLD pin on flash get driven by Design. '0' HOLD pin not get driven by design

NO_ADDR.Comment: This bit to take care of special case when address is not there but data is part of package(other than Instruction). 0: TX package has only instruction OR instruction + Addr + Data 1: TX package as Instruction + data(but no address)

CRC_RESET_ALL.Comment: Active High reset. This bit is cleared automatically by HW.%%0A1: Reset all CRC blocks

SEL_CRC_ALG_0.Comment: Select CRC-16 algorithm%%0A0: CRC-16-CCITT algorithm%%0A1: CRC-16-IBM algorithm

SEL_DELAY_CH1_0.Comment: 0: Use data_en without delay%%0A1: Select delay version of data_en of channel 1

SEL_DELAY_CH0_0.Comment: 0: Use data_en without delay%%0A1: Select delay version of data_en of channel 0

INIT_VAL_0.Comment: This is used to initialize CRC shift register when INIT is set to 1.

CRC_EN_MAN_0.Comment: 1: Calculate CRC with DATA_IN_MAN. This is cleared automatically by HW.

DATA_IN_MAN_0.Comment: This is used to calculate CRC when CRC_EN_MAN is set to 1.

CRC_OUT_0.Comment: CRC output for either DATA_IN or DATA_IN_MAN.

SEL_CRC_ALG_1.Comment: Select CRC-16 algorithm%%0A0: CRC-16-CCITT algorithm%%0A1: CRC-16-IBM algorithm

SEL_DELAY_CH0_1.Comment: 0: Use data_en without delay%%0A1: Select delay version of data_en of channel 0

MODE.Comment: [15] - Mode select.  0 for decryption, 1 for encryption.  The value after reset is 0.%%0ACan only be updated when Cipher block is idle

REG_OFFSET.Comment: Offset address of the OTP register

CMD.Comment: BOOT_CMD  0   %%0A BIST_CMD  1%%0A PROG_CMD  2%%0A REGRD_CMD 3%%0A REGWR_CMD 4%%0A OTPRD_CMD 5

IS_DED.Comment: Flag for Double-bit Error Detect. Set when ECC detects an error during read. Cleared by writing 1 to this bit.

IS_SEC.Comment: Flag for Single-bit Error Corrected. Set when ECC detects and corrects an error during read. Cleared by writing 1 to this bit.

IS_KEYREAD_DONE.Comment: Flag for boot-time key read done. Set when OTP wrapper finishes reading the 128-bit key after CPU reset. Cleared by writing 1 to this bit.

IS_RWFSM_WDOG_EXP.Comment: Flag for OTP read/write watchdog timeout. Set when the OTP's internal watchdog times out because a REGRD, REGWR, or OTPRD ran too long. Cleared by writing 1 to this bit.

IS_OTPRD_DONE.Comment: Flag for OTPRD comman done. Set when an OTPRD_CMD that was posted to OTP_COMMAND has completed. Cleared by writing 1 to this bit.

IS_REGWR_DONE.Comment: Flag for REGWR comman done. Set when a REGWR_CMD that was posted to OTP_COMMAND has completed. Cleared by writing 1 to this bit.

IS_REGRD_DONE.Comment: Flag for REGRD comman done. Set when a REGRD_CMD that was posted to OTP_COMMAND has completed. Cleared by writing 1 to this bit.

IS_PROG_DONE.Comment: Flag for PROG comman done. Set when a PROG_CMD that was posted to OTP_COMMAND has completed. Cleared by writing 1 to this bit.

IS_BIST_DONE.Comment: Flag for BIST comman done. Set when a BIST_CMD that was posted to OTP_COMMAND has completed. Cleared by writing 1 to this bit.

IS_BOOT_DONE.Comment: Flag for BOOT comman done. Set when a BOOT_CMD that was posted to OTP_COMMAND has completed. Cleared by writing 1 to this bit.

pass_fail_status.Comment: [5:4]:%%0A2'b00: Pass%%0A2'b01: PROG FAIL, Soak limit Exceeded%%0A            BIST: FAIL%%0A            BOOT: FAIL%%0A2'b10: PROG: FAIL, Compare Mismatch%%0A            BIST, BOOT: Should not occur%%0A2'b11: Should not occur

Soak_Counter.Comment: [3:0]:%%0APROG: Lower 4 bits of soak counter%%0ABIST: Lower 4 bits of running address counter%%0ABOOT: Not used

SEC_ECC.Comment: Shows whether the most recent OTPRD saw a single-bit error corrected.

DED_ECC.Comment: Shows whether the most recent OTPRD saw a double-bit error detected.

PARITY.Comment: The raw ECC and BRP parity bits from the most recent OTPRD

RDATA.Comment: Read data from OTP after OTPRD or from register after REGRD.

VAL.Comment: Watchdog timeout value. Bit 31 = 1 enables the watchdog.

DBG_OP_MODE.Comment: RESERVED FOR: Debug op mode to chimera_subs

READ_NUM.Comment: Internal read delay ETP clock cycles for read data

NO_HALT.Comment: No Halt%%0A1'b0: ETP halts CPU as needed%%0A1'b1: ETP does not halt CPU

DBG_OP_EN.Comment: RESERVED FOR: Debug op enable to chimera_subs

PEN.Comment: Selects PMEM/DMEM access mux in NVM space%%0A1'b0: DMEM%%0A1'b1: PMEM

NO_INC_R.Comment: Address incremental%%0A1'b0:  auto increment%%0A1'b1:  no auto increment

BLK_LEN_R.Comment: Number of remaining reads to perform.  The value of 0 indicates a single read.  The value is decremented as the block read progresses until 0 is reached.  This is field is only readable if etp clk is present.

NO_INC_W.Comment: Address incremental%%0A1'b0:  auto increment%%0A1'b1:  no auto increment

BLK_LEN_W.Comment: Number of remaining writes to perform.  The value of 0 indicates a single write.  The value is decremented as the block write progresses until 0 is reached.  This field is only readable if etp clk is present.

OUT_SEL1.Comment: Steers internal data out1 to 1 of 4 output pins

OUT_SEL0.Comment: Steers internal data out0 to 1 of 4 output pins

IN_MODE.Comment: Configures the number of active input pins. 0 to 5. Values can be overriden by mode entry, after that the value becomes read only.

OUT_MODE.Comment: Configures the number of active output pins.  0 to 2. Values can be overriden by mode entry, after that the value becomes read only.

WR_CMD_ERR.Comment: Sets if Wrtie Command FIFO overflows. Can be cleared by writing a 1 to this bit field.

RD_CMD_ERR.Comment: Sets if Read Command fails have valid Read Data available in the Read Data FIFO in time for the ETP output stream. Can be cleared by writing a 1 to this bit field.

WR_TRANS_EN.Comment: 1'b0: Single writes to ETP_BLWR_LEN, ETP_BLRD_LEN, and ETP_STATUS always to go the register instead of to the debug port. %%0A1'b1: The next%%0A single write will go to the debug port.%%0ACPU non-0 Write overrides ETP Write.

BLWR_TRANS_DISABLE.Comment: 1'b0: Block Writes are transparently sent to the debug port until the Block Write is complete (ETP_BWR_LEN = 0). %%0A1'b1: Disable Transparent Writes, such that Writes to ETP_BLWR_LEN, ETP_BLRD_LEN and ETP_STATUS always go the register instead of to the debug port.%%0ACPU non-0 Write overrides ETP Write.

INCSZ.Comment: Address increment size:%%0A0 for increment by 1%%0A1 for increment by 2%%0A2 for increment by 4%%0ACPU non-0 Write overrides ETP Write.

DPA.Comment: Drives debug_program_access for debug_interface%%0ACPU non-0 Write overrides ETP Write.

TEST_MODE_SCAN_COMP_SW.Comment: Reserved for: If SCAN switch is enabled, then also switch on SCAN Compression attribute (if SCAN Compression is present).

TEST_MODE_SCAN_MULTICHAIN_SW.Comment: Reserved for: If SCAN switch is enabled, then also switch on SCAN Multiple-Chain attribute (if SCAN Multiple-Chain is present; or ignored if SCAN Single-Chain is not present and thus SCAN Multiple-Chain is always present).

TEST_MODE_SCAN_SW.Comment: Reserved for: If ETP or if present, SER_PROG test mode is enabled, switch from ETP/SER_PROG to SCAN.

TEST_MODE_FLASH_SW.Comment: Reserved For: If ETP or if present, SER_PROG test mode is enabled, switch from ETP/SER_PROG to OTP Test Mode (if OTP Test Mode is present).

TEST_MODE_EXT_BCLK_SW.Comment: Reserved for: If MBIST or Ext-MBIST switch is enabled, then also switch on Ext-BCLK attribute (if Ext-BCLK is present).

TEST_MODE_EXT_MBIST_SW.Comment: Reserved for: If ETP or if present, SER_PROG test mode is enabled, switch from ETP/SER_PROG to Ext-MBIST (if Ext-MBIST is present).

TEST_MODE_MBIST_SW.Comment: Reserved for: If ETP or if present, SER_PROG test mode is enabled, switch from ETP/SER_PROG to MBIST.

XTRIG_EN.Comment: Debug Mode Multi-Core Cross Trigger Enable:%%0A0: Disable%%0A1: Enable

DEBUG_CORE_SEL.Comment: Debug Mode Multi-Core Cross Trigger Select:%%0A0: Select Core0%%0A1: Select Core1%%0A2: Reserved%%0A3: Reserved

READ_NUM_EXT.Comment: Counter most-significant extention bits for Internal read delay ETP clock cycles for read data.

ETP_HI_PAGE_ADDR.Description: ETP High Page Address Register. On ETP Writes/Reads, set the etp_addr[1:0] bits to 2'b10, i.e., use etp_addr[7:0] offset 0x2E, in order to access this register, no matter the value of the HI_PAGE_ADDR.

HI_PAGE_ADDR_ALIAS.Comment: Address offset alias of lower half-word. Halfword writes/reads data to/from lower-half-word of the register.

HI_PAGE_ADDR.Comment: ETP Bridge will combine HI_PAGE_ADDR[31:16] as the upper 16-bits with the incoming etp_addr[15:0] as the lower 16-bits to form the address[31:0] to access the CPU-CORE BUS MATRIX.

ETP_HI_WR_DATA.Description: ETP High Write Data Register. On ETP Writes/Reads, set the etp_addr[1:0] bits to 2'b10, i.e., use etp_addr[7:0] offset 0x32, in order to access this register, no matter the value of the HI_PAGE_ADDR.

HI_WR_DATA_ALIAS.Comment: Address offset alias of lower half-word. Halfword writes/reads data to/from lower-half-word of the register.

HI_WR_DATA.Comment: ETP/CPU-CORE Bridge on ETP Writes will combine HI_WR_DATA[15:0] as the upper 16-bits with the incoming etp_data[15:0] as the lower 16-bits to form the write data[31:0] to the CORE BUS MATRIX.

ETP_HI_RD_DATA.Description: ETP High Read Data Register. On ETP Halfword writes/Reads, set the etp_addr[1:0] bits to 2'b10, i.e., use etp_addr[7:0] offset 0x36, in order to access this register, no matter the value of the HI_PAGE_ADDR.

HI_RD_DATA_ALIAS.Comment: Address offset alias of lower half-word. Halfword writes/reads data to/from lower-half-word of the register.

HI_RD_DATA.Comment: ETP/CPU-CORE Bridge on ETP Reads will distribute the upper 16-bits of ETP Read Data to HI_RD_DATA[15:0] with the lower 16-bits of outgoing etp_data[15:0] when reading data[31:0] from the CPU-CORE BUS MATRIX.

TEST_MODE.Comment: Reads the value of the TEST_MODE pin.

SER_PROG_NO_HALT.Comment: Serial Programming No Halt. Note: FW is only allowed to set SER_PROG_NO_HALT. Once set FW may never unset SER_PROG_NO_HALT.%%0A1: Disable Halt-on-Reset to allow the CPU to fetch instructions.%%0A0: Enable Halt-on-Reset to prevent the CPU from fetching its first instructions when SER_PROG Test Mode is activated prior to the CPU coming out of reset.

SER_PROG_PP_MODE.Comment: Serial Programming Mode SDA Push-Pull Output Mode.%%0A1: Use Push-Pull for SDA output%%0A0: Use Open-Drain or Psuedo-Open-Drain for SDA output.

DEBUG_SER_PROG_MODE.Comment: Set when EITHER Serial Programming Mode or Debug Mode are enabled.  See SER_PROG_MODE to distinguish between serial programming and debug modes.%%0A3'b010: GPIO A3/2-MODE ; %%0A3'b100: A6/5-MODE ;%%0AOthers: NA

SER_PROG_MODE.Comment: Set if in ANY serial programming mode via mode-entry

TEST_MODE_SCAN_COMP_SW.Comment: Reserved for: If SCAN switch is enabled, then also switch on SCAN Compression attribute (if SCAN Compression is present)

TEST_MODE_SCAN_MULTICHAIN_SW.Comment: Reserved for: If SCAN switch is enabled, then also switch on SCAN Multiple-Chain attribute (if SCAN Multiple-Chain is present; or ignored if SCAN Single-Chain is not present and thus SCAN Multiple-Chain is always present).

TEST_MODE_SCAN_SW.Comment: Reserved for: If ETP or if present, SER_PROG test mode is enabled, switch from ETP/SER_PROG to SCAN Test Mode

TEST_MODE_OTP_SW.Comment: Reserved for: If ETP or if present, SER_PROG test mode is enabled, switch from ETP/SER_PROG to OTP Test Mode (if OTP Test Mode is present).

TEST_MODE_EXT_BCLK_SW.Comment: Reserved for: If MBIST or Ext-MBIST switch is enabled, then also switch on Ext-BCLK attribute (if Ext-BCLK is present).

TEST_MODE_EXT_MBIST_SW.Comment: Reserved for: If ETP P or if present, SER_PROG test mode is enabled, switch from ETP/SER_PROG to Ext-MBIST (if Ext-MBIST is present).

TEST_MODE_MBIST_SW.Comment: Reserved for: If ETP or if present, SER_PROG test mode is enabled, switch from ETP/SER_PROG to MBIST Test Mode.

LFSR_UNLK.Comment: Bit to unlock LFSR to switch mode. This feature is reserved.

DEBUG_ACTIVE_THIRD.Comment: 1 if the THIRD debug port is activated

DEBUG_ACTIVE_GPIO.Comment: 1 if the GPIO debug port is activated

DEBUG_ACTIVE_MAIN.Comment: 1 if the MAIN debug port is activated

DEBUG_SENS_THIRD.Comment: enable run-time activation of the THIRD debug ports

DEBUG_SENS_GPIO.Comment: enable run-time activation of the GPIO debug ports

DEBUG_SENS_MAIN.Comment: enable run-time activation of the MAIN debug ports

DEBUG_SOFT_BREAK_STATE.Comment: Legacy Register and Register Field. Not used for RISCV CPU Debug Soft Break Function/Status (use RISCV-JTAG-Debug-Module related registers instead). When this bit is set to '1', it allows RISCV Subsystem WDT to be disabled when WDT_LIMIT is programmed to the freeze value

DPROBE_EN.Comment: Enable DPROBE signal output on GPIO[TBD7:TBD0]

DPROBE_BLK_SEL_HIGH.Comment: Select block for dprobe[7:4]%%0A0000: dprobe_block_aon%%0A0001: dprobe_block_tbd%%0A0010: dprobe_block_tbd%%0A0011: dprobe_block_tbd%%0A0100: dprobe_block_tbd%%0AOthers: Reserved

DPROBE_BLK_SEL_LOW.Comment: Select block for dprobe[3:0]%%0A0000: dprobe_block_aon%%0A0001: dprobe_block_tbd%%0A0010: dprobe_block_tbd%%0A0011: dprobe_block_tbd%%0A0100: dprobe_block_tbd%%0AOthers: Reserved

DMON_EN.Comment: When enabled, the dmon signal will become active on LED1_GPIO4

DTIM_MEM_CTL.Comment: Memory control bits for DTIM RAMs; %%0ADTIM_RAM_MEM_CTL[14:0]%%0ABit 0 = TEST1; Bit 1 = TEST_RNM; Bit 3 = RME; %%0ABit 7:4= RM;%%0ABit 9:8 = RA; Bit 11:10 = WA (default '10'); %%0ABit 14:12 = WPULSE%%0AECO_03 UPDATE: On reg write, Bit[11:10] = WA[0:1]; On reg read, Bit[11:10] = WA[1:0]

ITIM_ROM_MEM_CTL.Comment: Memory control bits for ITIM ROM;%%0AITIM_ROM_MEM_CTL[14:0] %%0ABit 0 = TEST1; Bit 3 = RME; %%0ABit 7:4= RM;%%0AOther bits not used

ITIM_RAM_MEM_CTL.Comment: Memory control bits for ITIM RAMs; %%0AITIM_RAM_MEM_CTL[14:0]%%0ABit 0 = TEST1; Bit 1 = TEST_RNM; Bit 3 = RME; %%0ABit 7:4= RM;%%0ABit 9:8 = RA; Bit 11:10 = WA (default '10'); %%0ABit 14:12 = WPULSE%%0AECO_03 UPDATE: On reg write, Bit[11:10] = WA[0:1]; On reg read, Bit[11:10] = WA[1:0]

BRANCH_BASE_MEM_CTL.Comment: Memory control bits for Branch predictor base RAM;%%0ABRANCH_BASE_MEM_CTL[14:0]%%0ASame bit arrangement as ITIM_RAM_MEM_CTL;%%0AECO_03 UPDATE also applies here

BRANCH_TAG_MEM_CTL.Comment: Memory control bits for Branch predictor tag RAM;%%0ABRANCH_TAG_MEM_CTL[14:0]%%0ASame bit arrangement as ITIM_RAM_MEM_CTL%%0AECO_03 UPDATE also applies here

DISP_RF1P_MEM_CTL.Comment: Memory control bits for DISPLAY_TOP rf1p;%%0ADISP_RF1P_MEM_CTL[14:0]%%0ABit 0 = TEST1; Bit 1 = TEST_RNM; Bit 3 = RME; %%0ABit 7:4= RM; %%0ABit 9:8 = RA; Bit 11:10 = WA (default '10'); %%0ABit 14:12 = WPULSE%%0AECO_03 UPDATE: On reg write, Bit[11:10] = WA[0:1]; On reg read, Bit[11:10] = WA[1:0]

DISP_SRAM1P_MEM_CTL.Comment: Memory control bits for DISPLAY_TOP sram1p;%%0ADISP_SRAM1P_MEM_CTL[14:0]%%0ABit 0 = TEST1; Bit 1 = TEST_RNM; Bit 3 = RME; %%0ABit 7:4= RM;%%0ABit 9:8 = RA; Bit 11:10 = WA (default '10'); %%0ABit 14:12 = WPULSE%%0AECO_03 UPDATE: On reg write, Bit[11:10] = WA[0:1]; On reg read, Bit[11:10] = WA[1:0]

EDP_RF2P_MEM_CTL.Comment: Memory control bits for EDP_TOP rf2p %%0A(NOT USED in SB7900 A0)%%0ABit 0 = TEST1A; Bit 1 = TEST1B; Bit 2 = TEST_RNMA; %%0ABit 4 = RMEA; Bit 5 = RMEB; %%0ABit 11:8 = RMA; Bit 15:12 = RMB%%0ABit 17:16 = RA; Bit 19:18 = WA (default '10'); %%0ABit 22:20 = WPULSE;

EDP_RF2PU_MEM_CTL.Comment: Memory control bits for EDP_TOP rf2pu;%%0A(NOT USED in SB7900 A0)%%0ABit 0 = TEST1; Bit 1 = TEST_RNM; Bit2 = TESTRWM; Bit 3 = RME; %%0ABit 7:4= RM; %%0ABit 9:8 = RA; Bit 11:10 = WA (default '01'); %%0ABit 14:12 = WPULSE

WDT_LIMIT.Comment: Holds the desired WDT timeout period in number of LSO cycle periods.

DEBUG_HALT.Comment: 1 = clear and pause watchdog when CPU halts for debug%%0A0 = do not pause;

SLEEP_HALT.Comment: 0x421B9A6 = clear and pause watchdog when the system is in SLEEP or HIBERNATE mode%%0A0xB9A60B9 = clear and pause watchdog unconditionally%%0AAny other value = do not pause

WDT_CLR.Comment: Write %%E2%%80%%981%%E2%%80%%99 to this bit will clear the watchdog count to 0x0

SYS_PERMISSION_CHECK_DISABLE.Comment: System permission check disable;%%0AWhen set to '1', it disables permission check on AHB and APB accesses;This should be cleared to '0' during normal operation

IVMON_INT_FLAG.Comment: IVMON interrupt flag; This is a global combined interrupt status for IVMON. Details are shown in IVMON_INT_STATUS register; interrupt enable and interrupt clear are handled by IVMON_INT_EN and IVMON_INT_STATUS_CLEAR registers

SW0_INT.Comment: Software interrupt 0;%%0AWriting any non-zero values will trigger the SW0_INT interrupt; Writing 0 will clear the interrupt interrupt.

SW1_INT.Comment: Software interrupt 1; %%0AWriting any non-zero values will trigger the SW1_INT interrupt; Writing 0 will clear the interrupt interrupt.

ITIM_PARITY_ERROR.Comment: Indicates if ITIM had parity error

DTIM_PARITY_ERROR.Comment: Indicates which DTIM bank had parity error

DTIM_FAST_WRITE_MODE.Comment: 1 = allow firmware to write to all 8 banks simultaneously; %%0AWhen set to '1' and FW write to a memory location, the same data will be written to all 8 DTIM banks simultaneously

DTIM_BANK_REMAP.Comment: 1 = 2 regions of 4 interleaving banks%%0A0 = 1 region of 8 interleaving banks

DTIM_ARB_MODE.Comment: DTIM arbitration mode:%%0A0 = CPU > DMA_A > DMA_B > Hydra %%0A1 = CPU > DMA_B > DMA_A > Hydra%%0AOther values are reserved for future use

PARITY_BYPASS_MODE_ENABLE.Comment: 1 = bypass parity generation and detection. When in pairty bypass mode, PARITY_WRITE_VAL and PARITY_READ_VAL registers are used

PARITY_BYPASS_MEM.Comment: Controls which memory is put in parity bypass mode. %%0A0 = DTIM. %%0A1 = ITIM%%0AOther values are reserved for future use

ITIM_PARITY_DETECT_DISABLE.Comment: ITIM parity error detection disable%%0A1 = Disable parity error detection

DTIM_PARITY_DETECT_DISABLE.Comment: DTIM parity error detection disable%%0A1 = Disable parity error detection

ERROR_PARITY_VAL.Comment: Value of RAM parity bits when the first parity error occurred

ERROR_MEM.Comment: Indicates which memory encountered the first parity error;%%0A0 = DTIM%%0A1 = ITIM%%0AOther values are not used

ERROR_ADDR.Comment: Indicates the address that has error when error occurs. If more than 1 bank has error in the same cycle, this signal indicates the address of the lowest numbered bank

ERROR_RDATA1.Comment: Value of RAM read data bit 31:0 when the first parity error occurred

ERROR_RDATA2.Comment: Value of RAM read data bit 63:32 when the first parity error occurred

PARITY_WRITE_VAL.Comment: Used in parity bypass mode as parity value being written to the RAM. For ITIM, only bit 0 is being used. For DTIM, this 4-bit write value is used for the 4 parity bits of the SRAM bank that is accessed.

PARITY_READ_VAL.Comment: Used in parity bypass mode capturing the parity value being read from SRAM. For ITIM, only bit 0 is used. For DTIM, this 32-bit read value corresponds to 4 parity bit values of the SRAM bank that was most recently accessed

STARVE_THRESHOLD.Comment: Threshold value for a starvation event. When a bus master gets NACK continuously for this number of times, it will be counted as starvation event%%0A0 = 16 times%%0A1 = 32 times%%0A2 = 64 times%%0A3 = 128 times%%0A4 = 256 times%%0A5 = 512 times%%0A6 = 1024 times%%0AOther values are reserved

STARVE_MAX_DURATION.Comment: 10-bit value indicating the longest starvation ever occurred. This value is only valid when DTIM_STARVE_DETECT_EN is 1 and when the starvation count ever  exceeds the DTIM_STARVE_THRESHOLD%%0ACounts up to 1023;%%0AAny write to this field will clear the value to 0

STARVE_EVENT_COUNT.Comment: Number of times that starvation event occurred. This counter is incremented that each time one of the starvation monitor hits the threshold. %%0AAny write to this field will clear the value to 0

DISP_I2C_SEL.Comment: 0: Select Display SPI, 1: Select Display I2C

SPARE_OUT_VDD08_TO_VDD18.Comment: Spare bits coming from VDD08 domain, level shifted to VDD18 on analog side

SPARE_OUT_VDD08.Comment: spare bits coming from VDD08 domain, buffered 0.8V

SPARE_IN_VDD08.Comment: Connect to spare_in_vdd08[7:0] input port for spare analog status in VDD08 domain, level shifted from 1.8V

IVMON_AUTO_MON_MODE.Comment: IVMON Automatic Calibration/Monitor/Gap Mode Enable. On each CAL/MON/GAP iteration, automatically sequences through Quiet/Calibration/Wait Phases, Monitor Measurement Phase which indexes through Channels 0-31 and a Gap Phase which waits until the IVMON_AUTO_MON_PERIOD completes prior to automatically re-starting the next CAL/MON/GAP iteration. %%0A1: Enable Automatic Monitor Mode (Disable Manual Monitor Mode)%%0A0: Disable Automatic Monitor Mode (Enable Manual Monitor Mode)

IVMON_AUTO_MON_PERIOD.Comment: IVMON Automatic Monitor Mode Period. Number of milliseconds (assuming 24MHz IVMON_CLK) between AUTO_MON_MODE iterations.%%0A4'd15 - 4'd1: Number of milliseconds%%0A4'd0: 16 milliseconds

IVMON_CH_STATUS_READ.Comment: IVMON Channel Status Read. Set the Monitor to use the selected channel number. The selected channel comparator result can be read via the IVMON_CH_STATUS register field. IVMON_CH_STATUS_READ is also used by the IVMON Test Mode to select a fixed channel number.%%0A5'd31 - 5'd0: Monitor Channel Number.

IVMON_MSTART.Comment: IVMON Manual Start Trigger. FW toggles IVMON_MSTART from low to high to set the IVMON Manual Start Triggger. Note: IVMON_MSTART must be cleared prior to set. Also IVMON_MSTART must be asserted while the IVMON is IDLE or DONE.%%0A1'b1: Set Start Trigger%%0A1'b0: Clear Trigger

ISENS_HI_THR.Comment: Current sense high threshold Reference voltage.%%0AIref_hi = 800mV + 5mV*code%%0AIREF_HI setting: 0x10 = 0.88V  (0.8V+10%%)

ISENS_OFFSET.Comment: PGA common mode Reference voltage (for Reference Buffer). Vref_vcm = 500mV + 5mV*code%%0AVREF_VCM setting: 0x10 = 0.58V

IVMON_TM_SEL.Comment: IVMON Test Mode Select between AMON and DMON.%%0AAMON Bits [5:0] are one-hot encoded. FW must only set 1-bit on/high at any time including other AMON related register fields.%%0ADMON Bits [7:6] are one-hot encoded. FW must only set 1-bit on/high at any time including other DMON related register fields.%%0ABit 7: comp_hi_out %%E2%%80%%93 high comparator output%%0ABit 6: comp_low_out %%E2%%80%%93 low comparator output%%0ABit 5: vsens_mux - Common sense bus for muxes & PGA%%0ABit 4: PGA_Amp1_out - PGA amplifier 1 output%%0ABit 3: dac_out_hi %%E2%%80%%93 RDAC output voltages for high comparator%%0ABit 2: dac_out_lo %%E2%%80%%93 RDAC output voltages for low comparator%%0ABit 1: vref_low %%E2%%80%%93 RDAC output for Reference Buffer (PGA Vcm)%%0ABit 0: PGA_Amp2_out - PGA amplifier 2 output%%0ASee CLKRST CORE_PLL_CTRL_0 CORE_PLL_TM_PLL register field for other AMON and DMON related register fields.

IVMON_TM_OVRD.Comment: 1'b1: RESERVED FOR MANUFACTURING USE ONLY. Set to allow any TM_SEL value to override and propagate to DMON/AMON whether valid or not.%%0A1'b0: TM_SEL values are HW decoded for validity prior to propagating to AMON/DMON so that at most, only one AMON source is selected at a time and separately, at most, one DMON source is selected at a time.

IVMON_TM.Comment: IVMON Test Mode. Monitors one selected channel rather than indexing through all channels. Note the either Manual MSTART Mode or Automatic AUTO_MON_MODE may be used.%%0A1'b1: Set the internal monitor array counter to the IVMON_CH_STATUS_READ value and constantly stays at the selected channel.%%0A1'b0: internal monitor array counter increments automatically and indexes through all channels.

COMP_HI_THR.Comment: High Comparator Reference voltage for 1.8V & 0.8V signals%%0AVref_hi = 800mV + 5mV*code%%0AVREF_HI setting: 0x0A = 0.85V (0.8V+6%%)

COMP_LO_THR.Comment: Low Comparator Reference voltage for 1.8V & 0.8V signals%%0AVref_lo = 600mV + 5mV*code%%0AVREF_LO setting: 0x1E = 0.75V (0.8V-6%%)

IVMON_INT_STATUS_CLEAR.Comment: Write to clear the interrupt condition and the IVMON interrupt status register. Note that this field is R/W not W1C (not Write 1 to Clear) and thus must be set back low after setting high. This register field must be held high for at least 2 IVMON_CLK periods.%%0A1'b1: Clear interrupt condition if held high for at least 2 OSC_CLK periods.%%0A1'b0: Do not clear interrupt condition.

COMP_LO_33_THR.Comment: Low Comparator Reference voltage for 3.3V signals.%%0Avref_lo = 600mV + 5mV*code%%0AVREF_LO setting: 0x1E = 0.75V (0.8V-6%%)

COMP_HI_33_THR.Comment: High Comparator Reference voltage for 3.3V signals.%%0Avref_hi = 600mV + 5mV*code.%%0AVREF_HI setting: 0x0A = 0.85V (0.8V+6%%)

MON_DONE.Comment: IVMON CAL or MON operation is done.

IVMON_BUSY.Comment: IVMON CAL Phase operation busy/in-progress. -A0 Silicon: not asserted for MON Phase operation.

IVMON_CH_STATUS.Comment: Note this register must wait for at least 2 IVMON_CLK periods after the CH_STATUS_READ register is set, prior to reading.%%0ABit 1: compout_hi (set if comparator output is too high)%%0ABit 0: compout_lo (set if comparator output is too low)

IVMON_INT_STATUS.Comment: IVMON Interrupt Status. Reflects the last IVMON interrupt cause. If possible multiple causes matter, FW may want to manually loop and read each individual channel number status. Note that FW must wait at least 2 IVMON_CLK periods before all field values settle. FW may also read this register twice consecutively and compare to confirm the value of the first read.%%0ABit 7: Interrupt Line Status%%0ABit 6: compout_hi%%0ABit 5: compout_lo%%0ABits 4:0: IVMON counter (channel number)

SEL_VRR_ATEST.Comment: mux sel bit to monitor 1.2V VRR (OTP) supply

SEL_VPP_ATEST.Comment: To send out one-tenth of VPP (typ 5.2V) to ana_test amon_atest

ANA_TEST_IE.Comment: To enable the schmitt trigger to drive ANA_TEST to digital, during amon monitoring thru ANA_TEST pad, ANA_TEST_IE must be set LOW

PM_TEST.Comment: If 1 selects bg2, if 0 selects bg1 (simpler bg) for Vrefs to PM block.

BG_IREF_TEST_SEL.Comment: Bandgap Current Reference Test Select. FW/ATE must program to be one hot. Brings out various internal test voltages.%%0A3'b100: itest_10uA_0v80: Copy of 10uA mirror current from the same circuit which creates 50uA for LVDS. VDD08 referenced.%%0A3'b010: iptat_18uA: Copy of iptat 18uA to core PLL is brought out. VDD18 referenced.%%0A3'b001: Vbg_iref: Iref_amp output. Buffered VBG 1.23V Nominal Untrimmed.%%0A3'b000: none selected: Not connected.%%0AOther: All other settings are invalid and shall not be used. No two bits should be high at any time.

BG_IREF_VTEST_EN.Comment: Bandgap Current Reference Voltage Test Enable. Brings outs Vref 1.27V. This output voltage can be trimmed by i_reg_bg_vref_trim.%%0A1'b1: vreg_test_1v27%%0A1'b0: none selected

BG_IREF_ITEST_EN.Comment: Bandgap Current Reference Current Test Enable. Brings out ibias test 2.5uA .%%0A1'b1: bg2_itest_2p5uA%%0A1'b0: none selected

BG_VREF_TRIM.Comment: BG_IREF vref(s) trim. See i_reg_bg_iref_vtest_en test bit which can bring out 1.27 reference voltage on AMON pad. All voltage references are affected by this trim. Target Voltage is 1.27 V. AFE_AUX_RTERM_EN_N.Comment: AUX termination resistor enable. Active Low

AFE_AUX_MAUXRX_IRCTL.Comment: AUX RX Amplifier bias controls: 1x bias current: 2x bias current: 0.5x bias current: 0.7x bias current

AFE_AUX_VCMCNTL.Comment: AUX RX Vcm control: VDD-0.2V: VDD-0.3V: VDD-0.4V: VDD-0.5V

AFE_AUX_VCMHIGH_LOWRES.Comment: Set AUX RX Vcm to Vdd. Active high.

AFE_AUX_VCMHIGH.Comment: Set AUX RX Vcm to Vdd. Active high.

HPD_PIN_CONFIG.Description: HPD pin configuration. Accessed on reg_clk (27MHz - 270MHz) domain.

HPD_TX_DATA_BYP.Comment: Select TX data from bypass path. OE is still register controlled.

HPD_IGNORE_RX_DATA.Comment: Ignore receive data (disables all IRQ/HPD monitoring counters).  Useful if HPD is a downstream device

HPD_DEBOUNCE_COUNT.Description: number of clocks to debounce incoming HPD to remove noise and high-frequency glitching.  All events shorter than this are lost! Accessed on reg_clk (27MHz - 270MHz) domain.

HPD_DEBOUNCE_COUNT.Comment: A good starting point is 50us with reg_clk (27MHz - 270MHz)

HPD_CLKS_PER_TICK.Description: Clocks per time unit (tick).  Accessed on reg_clk (27MHz - 270MHz) domain.

HPD_IRQ_DET_THRESH.Description: IRQ detection thresholds.  Accessed on reg_clk (27MHz - 270MHz) domain.

HPD_IRQ_DET_THRESH_MAX.Comment: Maximum pulse width (in ticks) for detecting IRQ.

HPD_IRQ_DET_THRESH_MIN.Comment: Minimum pulse width (in ticks) for detecting IRQ.

HPD_PLUG_DET_THRESH_MIN.Description: minimum pulse width (in ticks) for detecting HPD plug . Accessed on reg_clk (27MHz - 270MHz) domain.

HPD_UNPLUG_DET_THRESH_MIN.Description: minimum pulse width (in ticks) for detecting HPD unplug. Accessed on reg_clk (27MHz - 270MHz) domain.

HPD_IRQ_WIDTH.Description: IRQ width. Accessed on reg_clk (27MHz - 270MHz) domain.

HPD_IRQ_GEN_WIDTH.Comment: width of generated IRQ pulse (in ticks)

HPD_IRQ_GEN.Description: IRQ generation control. Accessed on reg_clk (27MHz - 270MHz) domain.

HPD_IRQ_HOLDOFF_IN_PROGRESS.Comment: 2ms hold-off period after IRQ has not yet elapsed

HPD_SRC_DET_DEBOUNCE_COUNT.Description: SRC_DET debouncer config.  Accessed on reg_clk (27MHz - 270MHz) domain.

HPD_SRC_DET_DEBOUNCE_COUNT.Comment: # of clocks to debounce incoming source-detect pin to remove noise, glitching, and AUX traffic.  Some suggested values are:- 1ms if waiting for initial source connection- 200ns if using SRC_DET to detect MAUX transactions during D3 power state It is highly unlikely to detect FAUX transactions - 10ns if using SRC_DET to detect MAUX transactions during D3 power state

HPD_SRC_DET_CTRL.Description: Control of SRC_DET input.  Accessed on reg_clk (27MHz - 270MHz) domain.

HPD_SRC_DET_INT_ON_FALLING_EDGE.Comment: Assert SRC_DET interrupt on debounced falling edges of SRC_DET pin?

HPD_SRC_DET_INT_ON_RISING_EDGE.Comment: Assert SRC_DET interrupt on debounced rising edges of SRC_DET pin?

HPD_SRC_DET_EN.Comment: Source-detect enable.  Firmware should disable once source is detected and HPD is asserted.  Firmware may also use this feature as a 'wake from D3' interrupt if transitions are detected on AUX+ pin

SST_REG_CLK_CTRL.Description: Control Rx port to deframer assignment.  Accessed on reg_clk (27MHz - 270MHz) domain.

SST_REG_CLK_REG_SST_RBIF_FORCE_CLK_EN.Comment: Force SST reg_clk register bus clock enable.  Only for backup in case register events are broken.

SST_REG_CLK_AUD1_ASP_RAM_RETN.Comment: Audio 1 output fifo ram retention: 0=mem off, 1=mem on.

SST_REG_CLK_AUD1_CTL_RAM_RETN.Comment: Audio 1 control fifo ram retention: 0=mem off, 1=mem on.

SST_REG_CLK_AUD0_ASP_RAM_RETN.Comment: Audio 0 output fifo ram retention: 0=mem off, 1=mem on.

SST_REG_CLK_AUD0_CTL_RAM_RETN.Comment: Audio 0 control fifo ram retention: 0=mem off, 1=mem on.

SST_REG_CLK_IGNORE_INIT_DONES.Comment: Ignore INIT_DONE signals in the event something terrible happens in silicon.

SST_REG_CLK_FRM1_PORT.Comment: Framer 1, Audio 1 port assignment. 3 indicates disabled.

SST_REG_CLK_FRM0_PORT.Comment: Framer 0, Audio 0 port assignment. 3 indicates disabled.

SST_REG_CLK_INTR_FRM0_INT_STATUS.Description: Mainlink FRM interrupts. Accessed on reg_clk (27MHz - 270MHz) domain; Writing '1' will clear the status to 0

SST_REG_CLK_INTR_FRM0_MEAS_ACTIVE_SYM_CH.Comment: Measured Active Symbols per line changed

SST_REG_CLK_INTR_FRM0_DSC_CHUNK_SIZE_ERR.Comment: Unexpected chunk size received on link

SST_REG_CLK_INTR_FRM0_COMP_R_CRC_MATCH_E.Comment: CRC Match error for component R

SST_REG_CLK_INTR_FRM0_COMP_G_CRC_MATCH_E.Comment: CRC Match error for component G

SST_REG_CLK_INTR_FRM0_COMP_B_CRC_MATCH_E.Comment: CRC Match error for component B

SST_REG_CLK_INTR_FRM0_REG_CLK_VIDEO_STAT.Comment: Video status update, measured on reg_clk
