ML_COMMON_MST_MODE.Comment: RWX, This bit should be set in MST mode

ML_COMMON_LS_RBIF_FORCE_CLK_EN.Comment: Forces ls_clk register bus clock enable.  Only for backup in case register events are broken.

ML_COMMON_SPARE0.Description: Spare RW registers.  Accessed on ls_clk domain.

ML_COMMON_SPARE0.Comment: Spare registers for ECO.: Alignment SM config. When 1, clears a_is_stored when a found in all lanes.: When set to 1, filtering of K-char from SDP data is disabled.

ML_COMMON_SPARE1.Description: Spare RW registers.  Accessed on ls_clk domain.

ML_PHY_VID_RDY_EN.Comment: Enables for phy signals that can bring DP video ready output low16: Symbol align lock lost17: Lane align lock lost

ML_PHY_ENABLE_SR_CORRECTION.Comment: Enable SR correction in MST mode

ML_PHY_CLK_GATE.Comment: When this field is cleared, all flops in the logic block hold state.

ML_PHY_SERDES_AND_PRBS.Description: Accessed on ls_clk domain. These registers are provided for seamless connection of the Serdes to the RTL modules

ML_PHY_DATAVALID_MASK_ENABLED.Comment: If this bit is set, the data coming in from the serdes will be masked by the datavalid signal.

ML_PHY_DELAY_ONE_LANE_ALIGNMENT.Comment: If set lane alignment for one lane will only be set when symbol locked.

ML_PHY_PRBS_BIT_SLIP_MODE.Comment: the 2 least significant bits of this field define the number of prbs errors to be counted in a bit-slip event.0 = 1 error1 = total number of errors / prbs_bit_slip_mode[4:2]2 = 0 errors3 = all errors.

ML_PHY_AFE_LN_SEL_FOR_LOGIC_LN3.Comment: This selects the AFE lane feeding to the logical Lane 3

ML_PHY_AFE_LN_SEL_FOR_LOGIC_LN2.Comment: This selects the AFE lane feeding to the logical Lane 2

ML_PHY_AFE_LN_SEL_FOR_LOGIC_LN1.Comment: This selects the AFE lane feeding to the logical Lane 1

ML_PHY_AFE_LN_SEL_FOR_LOGIC_LN0.Comment: This selects the AFE lane feeding to the logical Lane 0

ML_PHY_FLIP_BIT_POLARITY.Comment: Setting these will reverse the bit polarity on a per lane basis.

ML_PHY_FLIP_BIT_ORDER.Comment: Setting these will reverse the bit order within a symbol on a per lane basis.

ML_PHY_FLIP_SYMBOL_ORDER.Comment: Setting these will reverse the symbol order on a per lane basis.

ML_PHY_ALPM_EN.Comment: Setting this bit will enable the Phy circuitry to look for ALPM signals.

ML_PHY_COUNT_UNLKS_IN_TP.Comment: unsetting this bit will actually count the number of 8b10b errors in TP, else it will count the number of unlocks.

ML_PHY_COUNT_8B10B_ERRS_IN_SERM.Comment: Error counters in SERM mode:= SERM errors only= 8b10b errors only= SERM and 8b10b errors

ML_PHY_ERR_SEL_8B10B.Comment: 0 = Count both Illegal Symbol errors and Running Disparity Errors= Count only Running Disparity Errors.= Count only Illegal Symbol Errors3 = Count either Illegal Symbol errors or Running Disparity Errors, mask sequential symbol errors

ML_PHY_SYM_ALIGN_EN.Comment: Setting this bit will enable the symbol alignment module. Symbol alignment is necessary for TP2/TP3/SERM and normal video traffic.

ML_PHY_LANE_ALIGN_EN.Comment: Setting this bit will enable the inter lane alignment module. Inter lane alignment is necessary for all link layer functionality.

ML_PHY_DESKEW_EN.Comment: Setting this bit will enable the inter lane deskew module. Deskew is necessary for all link layer functionality.

ML_PHY_SCRM_EN.Comment: RWX, Setting this enables the scrambler.

ML_PHY_TP3_EN.Comment: RWX, Setting this enables the TP3 checker. This does not affect the through datapath.

ML_PHY_TP2_EN.Comment: RWX, Setting this enables the TP2 checker. This does not affect the through datapath.

ML_PHY_TP1_EN.Comment: RWX, Setting this enables the TP1 checker. This does not affect the through datapath. There are different bits for different lanes to allow independent Nyquist checking on the lanes.

ML_PHY_SERM_EN.Comment: RWX, Setting this enables the SERM checker. SCRM_EN has to be set for correct operation. This does not affect the through datapath.

ML_PHY_PRBS_EN.Comment: RWX, Setting this enables the PRBS checker. This does not affect the through datapath.

ML_PHY_UPAT_EN.Comment: Setting this enables the UPAT checker. This does not affect the through datapath.

ML_PHY_LANE_EN.Comment: RWX, Lanes can be individually enabled by setting these bits.

ML_PHY_STOP_LFSR_IN_FEC_EN.Comment: LFSR not to be advance mode enabled

ML_PHY_PH_CHAR_FROM_FEC.Comment: For FEC, not to advance when parity place holder is received.

ML_PHY_TP4_LOCK.Comment: If TP4_EN is set, this field denotes the lock state of the TP4 checker on a per lane basis.

ML_PHY_UPAT_LOCK.Comment: If UPAT_EN is set, this field denotes the lock state of the UPAT checker on a per lane basis.

ML_PHY_LANE_ALIGN_LOCK.Comment: If LANE_ALIGN_EN is set, this field denotes the alignment state of the inter lane alignment block.

ML_PHY_TP3_LOCK.Comment: If TP3_EN is set, this field denotes the lock state of the TP3 checker on a per lane basis.

ML_PHY_TP2_LOCK.Comment: If TP2_EN is set, this field denotes the lock state of the TP2 checker on a per lane basis.

ML_PHY_TP1_LOCK.Comment: If TP1_EN is set, this field denotes the lock state of the TP1 checker on a per lane basis.

ML_PHY_SYM_ALIGN_LOCK.Comment: This field denotes the alignment state of the symbol alignment module on a per lane basis. Symbol alignment is necessary to perform 8b10b decode.

ML_PHY_PRBS_LOCK.Comment: If PRBS_EN is set, this field denotes the lock state of the PRBS checker on a per lane basis.

ML_PHY_SYM_ALIGN_UNLOCK_INT_CTRL.Comment: tp3 unlock interrupt behavior.  See PRBS_UNLOCK_INT_CTRL for behavior.

ML_PHY_SYM_ALIGN_LOCK_INT_CTRL.Comment: tp3 lock interrupt behavior.  See PRBS_LOCK_INT_CTRL for behavior.

ML_PHY_TP3_UNLOCK_INT_CTRL.Comment: tp3 unlock interrupt behavior.  See PRBS_UNLOCK_INT_CTRL for behavior.

ML_PHY_TP3_LOCK_INT_CTRL.Comment: tp3 lock interrupt behavior.  See PRBS_LOCK_INT_CTRL for behavior.

ML_PHY_TP2_UNLOCK_INT_CTRL.Comment: tp2 unlock interrupt behavior.  See PRBS_UNLOCK_INT_CTRL for behavior.

ML_PHY_TP2_LOCK_INT_CTRL.Comment: tp2 lock interrupt behavior.  See PRBS_LOCK_INT_CTRL for behavior.

ML_PHY_TP1_UNLOCK_INT_CTRL.Comment: tp1 unlock interrupt behavior.  See PRBS_UNLOCK_INT_CTRL for behavior.

ML_PHY_TP1_LOCK_INT_CTRL.Comment: tp1 lock interrupt behavior.  See PRBS_LOCK_INT_CTRL for behavior.

ML_PHY_UPAT_UNLOCK_INT_CTRL.Comment: upat unlock interrupt behavior.  See PRBS_UNLOCK_INT_CTRL for behavior.

ML_PHY_UPAT_LOCK_INT_CTRL.Comment: upat lock interrupt behavior.  See PRBS_LOCK_INT_CTRL for behavior.

ML_PHY_PRBS_UNLOCK_INT_CTRL.Comment: prbs unlock interrupt behavior0 = fire interrupt when *any* lane loses lock1 = fire interrupt when *all* lanes loses lock

ML_PHY_PRBS_LOCK_INT_CTRL.Comment: prbs lock interrupt behavior0 = fire interrupt when *any* lane acquires lock1 = fire interrupt when *all* lanes aqcuire lock

ML_PHY_ERRS_LN3_INT_MASK.Comment: interrupt enable on too many errors on lane 3.

ML_PHY_ERRS_LN2_INT_MASK.Comment: interrupt enable on too many errors on lane 2.

ML_PHY_ERRS_LN1_INT_MASK.Comment: interrupt enable on too many errors on lane 1.

ML_PHY_ERRS_LN0_INT_MASK.Comment: interrupt enable on too many errors on lane 0.

ML_PHY_CLR_ERRS_ON_TP1_LOCK_EN.Comment: Clear symbols errors when tp1 is locked

ML_PHY_ERRS_INT_THRESHOLD.Comment: The threshold for asserting the too many errors interrupt.

ML_PHY_SYM_ERR_REPL_DATA.Comment: When a symbol error is detected, replace with this 8b code

ML_PHY_ERRS_CURR_WINDOW.Comment: Current error counter sliding window in units of 2^21 ls_clks.Use the below settings for 1s interval at various link rates: RBR  = 38 HBR  = 64 HBR2 = 128 HBR3 = 193

ML_PHY_SYM_ERR_REPL_CTRL.Comment: When a symbol error is detected, replacement is control symbol when 1

ML_PHY_SYM_ERR_REPL_EN.Comment: When a symbol error is detected, replace default decode with SYM_ERR_REPL 8b code

ML_PHY_SHOW_CURR_ERRS.Comment: Change ERR_COUNTER_0-3 CSRs to show:0 = DPCD cumulative error counts 1 = Current errors as defined in ERRS_CURR_WINDOW

ML_PHY_FEC_ERRS_SEL.Comment: Count errors from pre-FEC 8b10b decode rather than post-FEC 8b10b decode.

ML_PHY_ERRS_ENABLE.Comment: When enabled, the counter is active.  When disabled, the counter is frozen.

ML_PHY_ERRS_RESET_ON_READ.Comment: Writing a 1 to this bit clears the error counter whenever it is read

ML_PHY_ERRS_LN0_VALID.Comment: Indicates validity of the above error count

ML_PHY_ERRS_LN0.Comment: If PRBS_EN is set, this field counts the number of PRBS errors on lane 0, else if SERM_EN is set, this field counts the number of SERM symbol errors on lane 0, else this field counts the number of 8b10b errors on lane 0

ML_PHY_MAX_SKEW_CORR.Comment: Maximum skew corrected. If 8b10b TP2 is selected, must be set to 4 because commas characters are close. Value of 12 will handle comma spacing in TP3.

ML_PHY_CLR_ON_SET_RD_PTR.Comment: Clear a_is_stored when set_rd_ptr asserted. This can cause alias problems when multiple commas occur back to back and lane skew causes late lanes to retrigger comma detection prematurely

ML_PHY_WAIT_WHEN_COMMAS_ARE_SPARSED.Comment: When in state Aligning do not enter sym_aligned state if commas are sparsed

ML_PHY_LANE_ALIGN_MIN_ERRS_FOR_UNLK.Comment: Minimum mis-aligned BS symbols to see before declaring a loss of lock

ML_PHY_LANE_ALIGN_MIN_PATS_FOR_LOCK.Comment: Minimum aligned BS symbols to see clearly before declaring a lock

ML_PHY_SYM_ALIGN_MAX_ERRS_TOLERATED.Comment: Maximum 8b10b errors to be tolerated within 127 link symbols. A larger number of errors results in a loss of symbol alignment lock.

ML_PHY_SYM_ALIGN_MIN_COMMAS_REQD_TO_LOCK.Comment: Minimum BS symbols to see clearly before declaring a lock

ML_PHY_SYM_ALIGN_MAX_TIME_TO_SEE_COMMAS.Comment: This is the time in (2^12 LS clocks) that is allowed between two BS symbols. A larger separation between two BS symbols results in a loss of symbol alignment lock.

ML_PHY_PRBS_MIN_ERRS_FOR_UNLK.Comment: Minimum PRBS symbol errors to see before declaring a loss of lock

ML_PHY_PRBS_MIN_SYMS_FOR_LOCK.Comment: Minimum correct PRBS symbols to see clearly before declaring a lock

ML_PHY_TP3_MIN_ERRS_FOR_UNLK.Comment: Minimum TP3 errors to see before declaring a loss of lock

ML_PHY_TP3_MIN_PATS_FOR_LOCK.Comment: Minimum TP3 patterns to see clearly before declaring a lock

ML_PHY_TP2_MIN_ERRS_FOR_UNLK.Comment: Minimum TP2 errors to see before declaring a loss of lock

ML_PHY_TP2_MIN_PATS_FOR_LOCK.Comment: Minimum TP2 patterns to see clearly before declaring a lock

ML_PHY_TP1_MIN_ERRS_FOR_UNLK.Comment: Minimum TP1 errors to see before declaring a loss of lock

ML_PHY_TP1_MIN_PATS_FOR_LOCK.Comment: Minimum TP1 patterns to see clearly before declaring a lock

ML_PHY_UPAT_WORD2.Comment: Most significant part of the 80 bit user pattern.

ML_PHY_UPAT_MIN_ERRS_FOR_UNLK.Comment: Minimum UPAT errors to see before declaring a loss of lock

ML_PHY_UPAT_MIN_PATS_FOR_LOCK.Comment: Minimum UPAT patterns to see clearly before declaring a lock

ML_PHY_UPAT_WORD1.Comment: Middle part of the 80 bit user pattern.

ML_PHY_UPAT_WORD0.Comment: Least significant part of the 80 bit user pattern.

ML_PHY_CLK_CYCLE_THREE_BITS.Comment: this is the clk cycle which sample 3 bits the other cycle should have 2 bits

ML_PHY_CLK_CYCLE_CHOOSE_EN_8X.Comment: enable which reg programmable clk choice for 3 or 2 bits in 8x oversampling mode

ML_PHY_INDEX_OFFSET.Comment: Index offset used while sampling oversampled data

ML_PHY_CLK_DIV.Comment: Clock divider ratio to support downsampling of AFE output data.0 = No clock divide1 = Divide selected clock by 22 = Divide selected clock by 43 = Divide selected clock by 8

ML_PHY_WAIT_TO_START_TRAINING.Comment: wait from 0 to 500us for no aux handshake training to start

ML_PHY_RST_ON_REDGE_AFE_TP1_RDY_EN.Comment: Reset phy on rising edge of AFE_TP1_READY

ML_PHY_RST_ON_FULL_TP1_EN_FROM_PHY.Comment: For full link training to reset the phy based on tp1 PHY logic

ML_PHY_USE_AFE_TP23_RDY.Comment: Use AFE_TP23_READY signal to set tp2_en for full link training

ML_PHY_USE_AFE_TP1_RDY.Comment: Use AFE_TP1_READY signal to set tp1_en for full link training

ML_PHY_PROG_COUNTER_WAIT_BEFORE_TP1_EN_S.Comment: Use wait counter for full link training

ML_PHY_RST_ON_REDGE_AFE_TP0_RDY_EN.Comment: Reset phy on rising edge of AFE_TP0_READY

ML_PHY_RST_ON_REDGE_DATAVALID_EN.Comment: Reset phy on rising edge of datavalid from AFE

ML_PHY_TOGGLE_TP2_FOR_NOTRAINING.Comment: Toggle tp2 for no link training before goind to align_done

ML_PHY_NO_TP23_LOCK_REQ_FOR_ALPM.Comment: only toggle tp2 for ALPM phy wake link training

ML_PHY_USE_BOTH_LANES_FOR_DATAVALID.Comment: Usage of datavalid for link training00 = not to use datavalid for link training01 = use i_rx_datavalid_lane0 only for datavalid_en10 = use i_rx_datavalid_lane1 only for datavalid_en11 = use both lanes for datavalid_en

ML_PHY_NO_TRAINING_EN.Comment: no training enable thus goes directly for align

ML_PHY_FAST_TRAINING_SM_HW_RST_EN.Comment: Enable the Hardware reset of fast training state machine

ML_PHY_FAST_TP3_SET.Comment: Although option is provided but should not be set

ML_PHY_FAST_TP2_SET.Comment: As per specification only TP2 is supported thus this bit should be set

ML_PHY_FAST_TRAINING_EN.Comment: Enable after hpd assertion and disable when fast training is completed

ML_PHY_LANE_ALIGN_AUTO_RST.Comment: Auto reset alignment to help prevent it from getting stuck in a bad cycle on TP3

ML_PHY_FAST_TRAINING_SM_RST.Comment: Put Fast training statemachine in reset.

ML_PHY_WAIT_TO_START_TRAINING_IN_STDBY.Comment: wait from 0 to 500us for no aux handshake training to start during AlPM Standby

ML_PHY_CLR_SYM_ERR_CNT_ON_TIC_TOC_CLR.Comment: For fast link training clear error count earlier

ML_PHY_AFE_GLUE_RST_ON_PHY_SOFT_RST.Comment: Reset the write pointer of AFE glue module on PHY soft reset.

ML_PHY_AFE_GLUE_RST_ON_TP23_FROM_SM.Comment: Reset the write pointer of AFE glue module on TP2/3 enable from state machine.

ML_PHY_FORCE_LANE_ALIGN.Comment: Lane align set for link training.

ML_PHY_FORCE_SYM_ALIGN.Comment: Symbol align set for link training.

ML_PHY_SOFT_RST_FOR_NON_RESETABLE_FLOPS.Comment: Reset flops affecting SOFT_RST and CLK_GATE flops.

ML_PHY_RST_ON_REDGE_AFE_TP2_RDY_EN.Comment: Reset phy on rising edge of AFE_TP2_READY

ML_PHY_RST_PHY_FROM_FAST_SM_EN.Comment: Reset PHY when fast state machine counter expires.

ML_PHY_TRAINING_SM_RST_ON_DPCD_WR.Comment: Write to DPCD register by source will reset fast training state machine

ML_PHY_BS_CNT_FOR_LATE_SR.Comment: BS count when late SR will reset the count

ML_PHY_BS_CNT_FOR_EARLY_SR.Comment: BS count when early SR will reset the count

ML_PHY_DETECT_SR_CORRUPT_EN.Comment: Detection of SR corruption logic is enabled

ML_PHY_INVALID_SR_MASK_ENABLE_WO_ERR.Comment: Mask an invalid SR when 8b10b Error happens without errors

ML_PHY_INVALID_SR_MASK_ENABLE.Comment: Mask an invalid SR when 8b10b Error happens

ML_PHY_BS_COUNT_FOR_SR.Comment: SR comes every 512 BS symbols for SST

ML_PHY_TP4_MIN_ERRS_FOR_UNLK.Comment: Minimum TP4 errors to see before declaring a loss of lock

ML_PHY_TP4_MIN_PATS_FOR_LOCK.Comment: Minimum TP4 patterns to see clearly before declaring a lock

ML_PHY_SOFT_RST_CNT_FOR_CDC.Comment: Wait this many clock cycles before releasing soft reset

ML_PHY_WAIT_CNT_INIT_DISABLED.Comment: Initializing the counter after soft reset is disabled

ML_PHY_RST_FAST_SM_WHEN_UNLOCK.Comment: Reset fast training state machine when symbol and align lock is lost

ML_PHY_FAST_TRAIN_ONLY_WHEN_UNLOCK.Comment: Only when symbol lock and align lock is lost then enter fast/no state machine

ML_PHY_RST_FAST_SM_ON_ALPM_SLEEP_STDBY.Comment: Reset fast training state machine when alpm sleep or standby is recevied

ML_PHY_RST_PHY_IN_STDBY.Comment: Reset PHY logic in standby needed for sync fifo in glue logic

ML_PHY_TP4_EN.Comment: RWX, Setting this enables the TP4 checker.

ML_PHY_FEC_CONFIG.Description: Accessed on ls_clk domain. Used to configure the RX FEC behavior

ML_PHY_FEC_POST_RD_ERR_UNCORR.Comment: Consider running disparity errors that occur after FEC to be because of uncorrectable blocks

ML_PHY_FEC_POST_SYM_ERR_UNCORR.Comment: Consider symbol errors that occur after FEC to be because of uncorrectable blocks

ML_PHY_FEC_PARITY_ZEROS_ERR.Comment: 1: when 0 fields in parity bytes are 1, consider error. 0: ignore non 0 fields that should be 0 (DP 1.4a).

ML_PHY_FEC_HDCP_IGNORE_PM.Comment: 1: HDCP ignores PM and does not increment cipher

ML_PHY_FEC_DONT_FIX_UNCORR_ERR.Comment: Do not attempt to fix uncorrectable errors

ML_PHY_FEC_PM_RESYNC_THRESHOLD.Comment: Resync when parity marker is seen in wrong position this many times

ML_PHY_FEC_PM_RESYNC_MODE.Comment: Resync when parity marker is seen

ML_PHY_FEC_FORCE_DISABLE.Comment: Force the FEC block to be disabled

ML_PHY_FEC_FORCE_ENABLE.Comment: Force the FEC block to be enabled. Set the PM_RESYNC_MODE bit so that correction can find the parity symbols.

ML_PHY_FEC_CNT_RST.Comment: Reset FEC counters. Set to 0 to enable. Set to 1 to reset and disable counters.

ML_PHY_FEC_CONSIDER_RD_ERR.Comment: Running disparity error considered a symbol error. Setting to 1lead to more erasure locations but could just be propagatedprevious symbol error.

ML_PHY_FEC_ZERO_ERR_DATA.Comment: On a 8b10b decode error, zero out data. In the case of a propaged RDfrom previous symbol, it could lead to false error flagging.

ML_PHY_FEC_HANDLE_ERASURES.Comment: Use 8b10b decode errors for erasure locations. Up to 4 erasuresbe corrected with Reed-Solomon ECC. Not mentioned in DP 1.4.

ML_PHY_FEC_READY.Comment: Enable RX FEC. Delay input stream and wait for FEC_DECODE_ENABLE sequence.

ML_VC_USE_FEC_RDY_2_MASK_PH_PM.Comment: Use FEC Ready rather than FEC enabled to mask PH and PM

ML_VC_SWITCH_MST2SST.Comment: Set if MST symbols are to be converted to SST Mode.

ML_VC_CLK_GATE.Comment: When this field is cleared, all flops in the logic block hold state.

ML_VC_ACT_STATUS.Comment: Deferred Write Trigger Status (Read Only Field): 0 = Armed/Forced 1 = Trigger generated, now idle

ML_VC_ACT_EN_CMD.Comment: Deferred Write Trigger: 0x0 = Disarm Trigger 0x1 = Armed xF = Force trigger.

ML_FRM0_CTRL.Description: Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

ML_FRM0_HDMI_RX_EN.Comment: If set video data is via HDMI RX instead of DP RX

ML_FRM0_EFM.Comment: RWX, This is the EFM Value used by the deframer

ML_FRM0_FRM_DBG_BUS_SEL.Comment: Debug bus select as follows:000 - lsx_flag_dbg001 - vif_rd_dbg010 - vif_cnt_dbg011 - vif_flg_dbg100 - dsc_wr_pix_dbg101 - dsc_wr_fill_dbg110 - dsc_ls_pix_dbg.

ML_FRM0_LANE_CNT.Comment: RWX, This is the number of Lanes active during a session. In MST this should be always set to 4.

ML_FRM0_RD_CLK_GATE.Comment: This needs to be set when the first MSA comes in, and cleared when there is no video on the link

ML_FRM0_RD_SOFT_RST.Comment: This needs to be cleared when the first MSA comes in, and set when there is no video on the link

ML_FRM0_CLK_GATE.Comment: Unsetting this bit will disable the ls_clk domain

ML_FRM0_SOFT_RST.Comment: When clk_gate is set, setting this bit will reset the ls_clk domain logic of the entire Deframer.

ML_FRM0_USE_VIF_FOR_CLOCK_ADJUSTMENT.Comment: When 0, uses LS clk signals for clk adjustment. 1, uses VIF output signals for clk adjustment, for example with the pattern generator.

ML_FRM0_USE_LINES_FOR_CLOCK_ADJUSTMENT.Comment: Unsetting this bit will send out triggers on frame boundaries.

ML_FRM0_FRAMES_MOVING_WINDOW_SIZE.Comment: For Measurement of frame frequency from link symbols

ML_FRM0_ACTIVE_SYM_PER_LINE.Comment: Number of active symbols per line on the DP Link.

ML_FRM0_VBID_RESERVED_BIT7.Comment: This is the RESERVED_BIT7  value extracted from the VBID on the DP Link

ML_FRM0_VBID_COMPRESSED_STREAM.Comment: This is the COMPRESSED_STREAM_FLAG value extracted from the VBID on the DP Link

ML_FRM0_VBID_HDCP_SYNC_DETECT.Comment: This is the HDCP_SYNC_DETECT value extracted from the VBID on the DP Link

ML_FRM0_VBID_AUD_MUTE.Comment: This is the AUD_MUTE_FLAG  value extracted from the VBID on the DP Link

ML_FRM0_VBID_NOVID.Comment: This is the NOVID_FLAG     value extracted from the VBID on the DP Link

ML_FRM0_VBID_INTERLACE_EN.Comment: This is the INTERLACE_FLAG value extracted from the VBID on the DP Link

ML_FRM0_VBID_FIELD_ID.Comment: This is the FIELD_ID_FLAG  value extracted from the VBID on the DP Link

ML_FRM0_VBID_VBLANK.Comment: This is the VBLANK_FLAG    value extracted from the VBID on the DP Link

ML_FRM0_MVID0.Description: Bypass accumulator MVID values. Accessed on ls_clk domain.

ML_FRM0_MVID1.Description: Bypass accumulator MVID values. Accessed on ls_clk domain.

ML_FRM0_MVID2.Description: Bypass accumulator MVID values. Accessed on ls_clk domain.

ML_FRM0_MSA_NVID.Comment: This is the NVID value extracted from the MSA on the DP Link

ML_FRM0_MSA_VTOTAL.Comment: This is the VTOTAL value extracted from the MSA on the DP Link

ML_FRM0_MSA_HTOTAL.Comment: This is the HTOTAL value extracted from the MSA on the DP Link

ML_FRM0_MSA_VSTART.Comment: This is the VSTART value extracted from the MSA on the DP Link

ML_FRM0_MSA_HSTART.Comment: This is the HSTART value extracted from the MSA on the DP Link

ML_FRM0_MSA_VHEIGHT.Comment: This is the VHEIGHT value extracted from the MSA on the DP Link

ML_FRM0_MSA_HWIDTH.Comment: This is the HWIDTH value extracted from the MSA on the DP Link

ML_FRM0_MSA_VS_POL.Comment: This is the VS_POLARITY value extracted from the MSA on the DP Link

ML_FRM0_MSA_VS_WID.Comment: This is the VS_WIDTH value extracted from the MSA on the DP Link

ML_FRM0_MSA_HS_POL.Comment: This is the HS_POLARITY value extracted from the MSA on the DP Link

ML_FRM0_MSA_HS_WID.Comment: This is the HS_WIDTH value extracted from the MSA on the DP Link

ML_FRM0_MSA_MISC1.Comment: This is the MISC1                 value extracted from the MSA on the DP Link

ML_FRM0_MSA_MISC0.Comment: This is the MISC0                 value extracted from the MSA on the DP Link

ML_FRM0_MSA_STEREO_VID.Comment: This is the STEREO_VID            value extracted from MSA field MISC1, bit[2:1]

ML_FRM0_MSA_INTERLACE_VTOTAL_EVEN.Comment: This is the INTERLACE_VTOTAL_EVEN value extracted from MSA field MISC1, bit[  0]

ML_FRM0_MSA_BPC.Comment: This is the BPC                   value extracted from MSA field MISC0, bit[7:5]

ML_FRM0_MSA_YCC_COLORIMETRY.Comment: This is the YCC_COLORIMETRY       value extracted from MSA field MISC0, bit[  4]

ML_FRM0_MSA_DYN_RANGE.Comment: This is the DYN_RANGE             value extracted from MSA field MISC0, bit[  3]

ML_FRM0_MSA_COMP_FMT.Comment: This is the COMP_FMT              value extracted from MSA field MISC0, bit[2:1]

ML_FRM0_MSA_SYNC_CLK_MODE.Comment: This is the SYNC_CLK_MODE         value extracted from MSA field MISC0, bit[  0]

ML_FRM0_VTOTAL.Comment: This is the VTOTAL Value used by the deframer, regardless of what it extracted from the DP Link.

ML_FRM0_HTOTAL.Comment: This is the HTOTAL Value used by the deframer, regardless of what it extracted from the DP Link.

ML_FRM0_VSTART.Comment: This is the VSTART Value used by the deframer, regardless of what it extracted from the DP Link.

ML_FRM0_HSTART.Comment: This is the HSTART Value used by the deframer, regardless of what it extracted from the DP Link.

ML_FRM0_VHEIGHT.Comment: This is the VHEIGHT Value used by the deframer, regardless of what it extracted from the DP Link.

ML_FRM0_HWIDTH.Comment: This is the HWIDTH Value used by the deframer, regardless of what it extracted from the DP Link.

ML_FRM0_VS_POL.Comment: This is the VS_POL Value used by the deframer, regardless of what it extracted from the DP Link.

ML_FRM0_VS_WID.Comment: This is the VS_WID Value used by the deframer, regardless of what it extracted from the DP Link.

ML_FRM0_HS_POL.Comment: This is the HS_POL Value used by the deframer, regardless of what it extracted from the DP Link.

ML_FRM0_HS_WID.Comment: This is the HS_WID Value used by the deframer, regardless of what it extracted from the DP Link.

ML_FRM0_FLUSH_LINES.Comment: Number of dummy lines to generate for flushing pipeline downstream.

ML_FRM0_VTE.Comment: This is the VTE           Value used by the deframer, regardless of what it extracted from the DP Link.

ML_FRM0_YCC422_MODE.Comment: This is the YCC422_MODE   Value used by the deframer, regardless of what it extracted from the DP Link.

ML_FRM0_BPC.Comment: This is the BPC           Value used by the deframer, regardless of what it extracted from the DP Link.

ML_FRM0_HORZ_VIEW_XPAND_LAST_PIXEL.Comment: If the user wants to extract a horizontal subsectionof the image, this field specifies the last pixel

ML_FRM0_HORZ_VIEW_XPAND_FIRST_PIXEL.Comment: If the user wants to extract a horizontal subsectionof the image, this field specifies the first pixel

ML_FRM0_VERT_VIEW_XPAND_LAST_LINE.Comment: If the user wants to extract a vertical subsection of the image, this field specifies the last line

ML_FRM0_VERT_VIEW_XPAND_FIRST_LINE.Comment: If the user wants to extract a vertical subsection of the image, this field specifies the first line

ML_FRM0_MIN_R_CR_VAL.Comment: Min value for R/Cr component. The internal logic clips the signal to this value

ML_FRM0_MAX_R_CR_VAL.Comment: Max value for R/Cr component. The internal logic clips the signal to this value

ML_FRM0_MIN_G_Y_VAL.Comment: Min value for G/Y component. The internal logic clips the signal to this value

ML_FRM0_MAX_G_Y_VAL.Comment: Max value for G/Y component. The internal logic clips the signal to this value

ML_FRM0_MIN_B_CB_VAL.Comment: Min value for B/Cb component. The internal logic clips the signal to this value

ML_FRM0_MAX_B_CB_VAL.Comment: Max value for B/Cb component. The internal logic clips the signal to this value

ML_FRM0_VIEWXPAND_ALLOW_VERT.Comment: Allow vert viewexpand (cya, should be ok to leave=1)

ML_FRM0_VIEWXPAND_HWIDTH.Comment: This is the hwidth for viewxpand

ML_FRM0_HFILL.Comment: This field is to add HFILL for Bezel Correction. The field represents number of pixels of HFILL

ML_FRM0_VIF_SINK_RDY_PAUSE_BLANK.Comment: Allow vif_sink_rdy to pause blank pixel generation.  Set to 1 in HDMI2.1 FRL mode.

ML_FRM0_VID_REGEN_COMP_SEL_FOR_POST2.Comment: component remap control on the video interface, component 2 comes out on pixel interface bits 35:24, by default this is G (Y), which comes internally in section 1

ML_FRM0_VID_REGEN_COMP_SEL_FOR_POST1.Comment: component remap control on the video interface, component 1 comes out on pixel interface bits 23:12, by default this is B (Cb), which comes internally in section 0

ML_FRM0_VID_REGEN_COMP_SEL_FOR_POST0.Comment: component remap control on the video interface, component 0 comes out on pixel interface bits 11:0, by default this is R (Cr), which comes internally in section 2

ML_FRM0_VIF_FRAME_START_RD_SOFT_RST_EN.Comment: Assert read soft reset on falling edge of vblank

ML_FRM0_VIF_PIX_PER_CLK.Comment: Number of Pixels per clock on the VIF

ML_FRM0_HFILL_ON_RIGHT.Comment: This field is to add HFILL on right for Bezel Correction

ML_FRM0_HFILL_ON_LEFT.Comment: This field is to add HFILL on left for Bezel Correction

ML_FRM0_BLACK_SCREEN_IF_CP_ON.Comment: Set this bit if HDCP Authentication fails on the Tx.

ML_FRM0_PTG_B.Comment: This is the blue component for flat color pattern

ML_FRM0_PTG_G.Comment: This is the green component for flat color pattern

ML_FRM0_PTG_R.Comment: This is the red component for flat color pattern

ML_FRM0_PTG_HIGH_CONTRAST_COLOR_EN.Comment: Setting this will send colors in a non-gradient checkerboard pattern

ML_FRM0_PTG_LOW_CONTRAST.Comment: Setting this will send a gradient checkerboard pattern

ML_FRM0_PTG_PAT_SEL.Comment: 2'd0   :  white frame boundary whith balck background2'd1   :  color ramp2'd2   :  checker-board. Use the other fields to get all the functionality2'd3   :  VESA CTS checker-board. Use the other fields to get all the functionality

ML_FRM0_PTG_EN.Comment: Setting this bit will enable the deframer to send out an internally generated Video pattern

ML_FRM0_PTG_VSTRIP_SIZE.Comment: This is the hsize of a checkerboard block

ML_FRM0_PTG_HSTRIP_SIZE.Comment: This is the hsize of a checkerboard block

ML_FRM0_CRC1.Comment: This is the CRC calculation on the component in position 23:12

ML_FRM0_CRC0.Comment: This is the CRC calculation on the component in position 11:0

ML_FRM0_CRC_UPDATE_CNT.Comment: 4 bit wrap around count for CRC register updateTo be written to DPCD addr 246h

ML_FRM0_CRC2.Comment: This is the CRC calculation on the component in position 35:24

ML_FRM0_PTG_FRM_CNT_FOR_RFR_RATE_TRIG.Comment: Update TOTALS/STARTS every N frames during vblank

ML_FRM0_PTG_RFR_RATE_CHNG_EVERY_FRM.Comment: Update TOTALS/STARTS every frame during vblank

ML_FRM0_PTG_RFR_RATE_CHNG_TRIGGER_DIS.Comment: Disable trigger, update TOTALS/STARTS whenever new value is written

ML_FRM0_RELEASE_SOFT_RST_ON_PSR_STATE2_E.Comment: Release rd_soft_rst when psr state 2 is exited

ML_FRM0_RELEASE_SOFT_RST_ON_MSA_RCVD.Comment: Release rd_sof_rst when msa is received

ML_FRM0_RST_ON_ENTERING_PSR_STATE2.Comment: Reset read logic when PSR state 2 is entered

ML_FRM0_DISALLOW_POSEDGE_RST_FOR_SU.Comment: During Selective update we need to set this registerto disallow phase reset on posedge of vblank

ML_FRM0_RST_ON_END_OF_SU_IN_PSR.Comment: Put read logic of framer in soft reset when end ofselective update is received.

ML_FRM0_FORCE_SYM_LOCK_FOR_PSR.Comment: For standby when symbol lock is not flagged,set this to mask entering back into power down state.

ML_FRM0_PSR_SU_SM_IN_RST.Comment: Set this to reset PSR selective update state machine.

ML_FRM0_THROTTLE_FLUSH_LN.Comment: Enable throttling of pixel counter for flush lines, which is also considered a vblank line

ML_FRM0_THROTTLE_VACTIVE.Comment: Enable throttling of pixel counter for vactive lines

ML_FRM0_THROTTLE_VBLANK.Comment: Enable throttling of pixel counter for all vblank lines, not just flush lines

ML_FRM0_THROTTLE_EN.Comment: Top level enable throttling of pixel counter

ML_FRM0_LINE_CNT_IN_ACT_DLY.Comment: Line count in active delayed by number of lines

ML_FRM0_FRM_RESYNC_VBLANK_EDGE.Comment: Select vblank edge for setting vtotal to 0xffff. 0-neg, 1-pos

ML_FRM0_FRM_RESYNC_OFFSET.Comment: When FRM_RESYNC_EN=1, offset to be added to line_cnt for vsync line calculation

ML_FRM0_FRM_RESYNC_VFP_FOLLOW_MODE.Comment: When FRM_RESYNC_EN=1, make output lines in VFP follow input lines from link

ML_FRM0_ADD_ONE_LINE.Comment: Add one line for interlace video

ML_FRM0_FRM_RESYNC_EN.Comment: Regenerate vsync on line with adaptive sync SDP four use with HDMI ouput VRR

ML_FRM0_USE_VSYNC_FOR_CRC_FRAME.Comment: Use redge vsync to detect frame done

ML_FRM0_CLR_CRC_CNT_WHEN_SINK_START_LOW.Comment: TEST_SINK_START is low then clear the CRC update count.

ML_FRM0_TEST_SINK_START.Comment: DPCD 270 bit 1, written by source for resetting CRC

ML_FRM0_SET_VSC_CRC_VALID.Comment: To set that CRC from vsc packet is always valid

ML_FRM0_THROTTLE_N.Comment: Pixel count is enabled M cycles out of N cycles

ML_FRM0_THROTTLE_M.Comment: Pixel count is enabled M cycles out of N cycles

ML_FRM0_MAX_RW_PHASE_DIFF.Comment: Set this to HTOTAL. This is the max difference between buffer read and write phase at write vblank negedge and posedge if enabled.

ML_FRM0_ALLOW_POSEDGE_PHASE_RST.Comment: Allow phase reset logic to re-align on vblank posedge.

ML_FRM0_NO_BUBBLES.Comment: Set this bit in when HDMI TX is connected to allow for no bubbles on the Video interface.

ML_FRM0_LINE_END_FLUSH_EN.Comment: If enabled, the FIFO is flushed to the video interface at the arrival of a BS Link Symbol

ML_FRM0_PIX_BUFF_MIN_MAX_MARGIN.Comment: If the pixel buffer has less than this number of slots filled (or empty), an underflow (or overflow) is triggerred.

ML_FRM0_PIX_BUFF_DIS_WRAP.Comment: Disable buffer wrap condition asserting both uflow/oflow

ML_FRM0_PIX_BUFF_FTG_EVENT.Comment: 0: Use negedge vsync to trigger, 1: use posedge hactive

ML_FRM0_PIX_BUFF_FTG_MODE.Comment: 1: Modify RDY_THRES to lower level once transmission started.

ML_FRM0_PIX_BUFF_FLUSH_THRES.Comment: If, at the end of the line, only this many pixels are left to be sent on the video if, the Pixel Buffer is flushed regardless of the fill status.

ML_FRM0_PIX_BUFF_FTG_LINE_CNT.Comment: When FTG MODE=1 and EVENT=0, indicates the line to reduce the thresholdCan be used with DSC to skew extra lines to account for decoder line delay0=first line, 1=second, 2=third, 3=fourth

ML_FRM0_ALLOW_NEGEDGE_PHASE_RST.Comment: Allow phase reset logic to re-align on vblank negedge.

ML_FRM0_PIX_BUFF_RDY_THRES.Comment: The Pixel Buffer will retain at least this many pixels at all times (except the end of line) to allow for rate variations on the DP link.

ML_FRM0_DBG_RD_PTR.Comment: Value of pointer (sampled in ls_clk domain.

ML_FRM0_DBG_WR_PTR.Comment: Value of pointer (sampled in ls_clk domain.

ML_FRM0_PHASE_PIX_CNT_MIN_MARGIN.Comment: Minimum arbitrary margin for pixel count in phase difference calculation

ML_FRM0_PHASE_PIX_CNT_MAX_MARGIN.Comment: Maximum arbitrary margin for pixel count in phase difference calculation

ML_FRM0_PIX_HCNT_AT_PHASE_RST.Comment: Horizontal pixel count to start at after MAX_RW_PHASE_DIFF is hit.  Set to 0 for DP output and PIX_BUFF_RDY_THRES for HDMI output.

ML_FRM0_FORCE_CNT_SET.Comment: Force cnt_set on negative edge of vblank

ML_FRM0_PIX_BUFF_PTR_LIMIT_HI.Comment: Maximum buffer pointer address (upper 6-bits).  Set to (hactive/2)>>5 for resolutions>2k.

ML_FRM0_PIX_BUFF_PTR_LIMIT_LO.Comment: Minimum buffer pointer address (upper 6-bits).  Recommend not to change from default of 0.

ML_FRM0_RESYNC_VFP_DLY.Comment: Set to htotal/4 to ensure adaptive sync packet can account for buffer delay in active and generate output vsync on proper line.  Only used when FRM_RESYNC_EN=1.

ML_FRM0_IGNORE_SINK_RDY_ON_EOL.Comment: Sink rdy will be ignored on the end of line. In certain use cases, if sink rdy goes low on last pixel, buffer will stop working.

ML_FRM0_PIX_VCNT_AT_PHASE_RST.Comment: Vertical line count to start at after MAX_RW_PHASE_DIFF is hit.  Set to VSTART for DP output, VSTART for HDMI output, and 0 for HDMI freesync output.

ML_FRM0_MSA_CHANGE_CTRL0.Description: MSA-changed per-field enable mask for 'MSA changed' interrupt.  Accessed on ls_clk domain.  Reserved fields are not included.

ML_FRM0_MSA_CHANGE_REPEAT_CNT.Comment: When an MSA change is detected, send a 'FRMx_MSA_UPDATE interrupt' for this many more received MSA's, even if there is no change.

ML_FRM0_MSA_STEREO_VID_CHANGE_MASK_EN.Comment: change-detect EN for MSA field: STEREO_VID of MISC1 (bits[342:341])

ML_FRM0_MSA_INTERLACE_VTOTAL_EVEN_CHANGE.Comment: change-detect EN for MSA field: INTERLACE_VTOTAL_EVEN of MISC1 (bit[340])

ML_FRM0_MSA_BPC_CHANGE_MASK_EN.Comment: change-detect EN for MSA field: BPC of MISC0 (bits[337:335])

ML_FRM0_MSA_YCC_COLORIMETRY_CHANGE_MASK_.Comment: change-detect EN for MSA field: VCC_COLORIMETRY of MISC0 (bit[334])

ML_FRM0_MSA_DYN_RANGE_CHANGE_MASK_EN.Comment: change-detect EN for MSA field: DYN_RANGE of MISC0 (bit[333])

ML_FRM0_MSA_COMP_FMT_CHANGE_MASK_EN.Comment: change-detect EN for MSA field: COMP_FMT of MISC0 (bits[332:331])

ML_FRM0_MSA_SYNC_CLK_MODE_CHANGE_MASK_EN.Comment: change-detect EN for MSA field: SYNC_CLK_MODE of MISC0 (bit[330])

ML_FRM0_MSA_MISC1_CHANGE_MASK_EN.Comment: change-detect EN for MSA field: MISC1 (bits[347:340])

ML_FRM0_MSA_MISC0_CHANGE_MASK_EN.Comment: change-detect EN for MSA field: MISC0 (bits[337:330])

ML_FRM0_MSA_NVID_CHANGE_MASK_EN.Comment: change-detect EN for MSA field: NVID (bits[307:300],bits[317:310],bits[327:320])

ML_FRM0_MSA_VHEIGHT_CHANGE_MASK_EN.Comment: change-detect EN for MSA field: VHEIGHT (bits[237:230],bits[247:240])

ML_FRM0_MSA_HWIDTH_CHANGE_MASK_EN.Comment: change-detect EN for MSA field: HWIDTH (bits[217:210],bits[227:220])

ML_FRM0_MSA_VS_WID_CHANGE_MASK_EN.Comment: change-detect EN for MSA field: VS_WID (bits[166:160],bits[177:170])

ML_FRM0_MSA_VS_POL_CHANGE_MASK_EN.Comment: change-detect EN for MSA field: VS_POL (bit[167])

ML_FRM0_MSA_VSTART_CHANGE_MASK_EN.Comment: change-detect EN for MSA field: VSTART (bits[147:140],bits[157:150])

ML_FRM0_MSA_HSTART_CHANGE_MASK_EN.Comment: change-detect EN for MSA field: HSTART (bits[127:120],bits[137:130])

ML_FRM0_MSA_HS_WID_CHANGE_MASK_EN.Comment: change-detect EN for MSA field: HS_WID (bits[76:70],bits[87:80])

ML_FRM0_MSA_HS_POL_CHANGE_MASK_EN.Comment: change-detect EN for MSA field: HS_POL (bit[77])

ML_FRM0_MSA_VTOTAL_CHANGE_MASK_EN.Comment: change-detect EN for MSA field: VTOTAL (bits[57:50],bits[67:60])

ML_FRM0_MSA_HTOTAL_CHANGE_MASK_EN.Comment: change-detect EN for MSA field: HTOTAL (bits[37:30],bits[47:40])

ML_FRM0_MSA_MVID_CHANGE_MASK_EN.Comment: change-detect EN for MSA fields: MVID (bits?]

ML_FRM0_MSA_CHANGE_CTRL1.Description: MSA Change control.  Accessed on ls_clk domain.

ML_FRM0_MSA_MVID_CHANGE_THRESH.Comment: Any change in 24-bit MVID received in MSA will be compared to this value.  Changes greater than this amount (+/-) will trigger a 'FRMx_MSA_MVID_CHANGE interrupt', and also contribute to 'FRMx_MSA_CHANGE interrupt' if MSA_MVID_CHANGE_MASK_EN is set

ML_FRM0_MSA_CHANGE_STATUS.Description: MSA-changed per-field status.  Accessed on ls_clk domain.  Reading this register causes a clear event.  Only fields enabled in MSA_CHANGE_MASK will set bits in this register

ML_FRM0_COMP_RX_CTRL0.Description: Control for receiving compressed symbols over main link.

ML_FRM0_COMP_RX_CHUNK_SIZE.Comment: Calculated chunk size in number of pixels

ML_FRM0_COMP_RX_LANE_FILL.Comment: Number of lanes with fill at end of each chunk

ML_FRM0_COMP_RX_CRC_CHUNK.Comment: Calculate CRC with padding (if needed) at end of each chunk

ML_FRM0_COMP_RX_16BIT_CRC.Comment: Calculate CRC based on 16bit (2 symbols) received data

ML_FRM0_COMP_RX_NUM_SLICE.Comment: Number of slices of compressed symbols per line

ML_FRM0_COMP_RX_BYTES_FILL.Comment: Number of bytes of padding needed to bound at 48 bits

ML_FRM0_COMP_RX_ADD_PIX.Comment: Need to add pixel to actual hwidth for padding

ML_FRM0_COMP_RX_FRAME_EN.Comment: Receiving compressed symbols on main link

ML_FRM0_COMP_RX_STATUS.Description: Status for chunk_size error in compressed symbols over main link.

ML_FRM0_COMP_RX_CHUNK_SIZE_ERR_CNT.Comment: Pix_cnt at time of chunk_size error

ML_FRM0_LINK_PWR_DN_CTRL.Description: Control for main link power down during PSR.

ML_FRM0_ALLOW_RST_ON_FEDGE_OF_SYM_LOCK.Comment: HW state machine to auto reset FRM on loss of symbol lock

ML_FRM0_RELEASE_RESET_ON_PSR_PWR_UP.Comment: Release reset before symbol lock or vid_rdy

ML_FRM0_USE_SYM_LOCK_OR_VID_RDY_FOR_RST.Comment: 1:  use symbol lock for releasing reset:  use vid_rdy for releasing reset

ML_FRM0_BS_COUNT_FOR_STABLE_BS_AGE.Comment: Configure BS age after reaching a Stable state

ML_FRM0_INVALID_BS_MASK_ENABLE_WO_ERR.Comment: Mask invalid BS symbols regardless of symbole error

ML_FRM0_USE_CONFIG_BS_AGE.Comment: Use configured BS age to filter BS symbols

ML_FRM0_RST_BS_FILT_SM.Comment: FW reset of BS filtering state machine

ML_FRM0_EARLY_BS_THRESH.Comment: Threshold to detect early BS symbol

ML_FRM0_LATE_BS_THRESH.Comment: Threshold to detect late BS symbol

ML_FRM0_BS_AGE_DURING_VIDEO.Comment: BS age when video is being received

ML_FRM0_HTOTAL_IN_CLK_CYCLES.Comment: Horizontal total in cycles instead of pixels

ML_FRM0_USE_CONFIG_LINE_WIDTH.Comment: Use configured line width instead of measured

ML_FRM0_BE_COUNT_FOR_STABLE_BE_AGE.Comment: BE count to achieve stable state

ML_FRM0_INVALID_BE_MASK_ENABLE_WO_ERR.Comment: Mask invalid BE regardless of symbol error

ML_FRM0_USE_CONFIG_BE_AGE.Comment: Use configured BE age for filtering BE

ML_FRM0_BE_MASK_CTRL2.Description: Control for main link power down during PSR.

ML_FRM0_EARLY_BE_THRESH.Comment: Threshold to detect early BE symbol

ML_FRM0_LATE_BE_THRESH.Comment: Threshold to detect late BE symbol

ML_FRM0_BE_MASK_CTRL3.Description: Control for main link power down during PSR.

ML_FRM0_BE_STATUS.Description: Control for main link power down during PSR.

ML_FRM0_USE_FEC_RDY_2_MASK_PH_PM.Comment: If 1, use FEC ready to mask PH and PM characters. If 0, use FEC enable to mask PH and PM characters.

ML_FRM0_RBIF_CTRL.Description: Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

ML_FRM0_LS_SST_RBIF_FORCE_CLK_EN.Comment: Force SST ls_clk register bus clock enable.  Only for backup in case register events are broken.

AUD_LSCLK0_ECC_CONTROL.Description: DP RX ECC Control. Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

AUD_LSCLK0_RELEASE_RESET_ON_PSR_PWR_UP.Comment: Release reset before symbol lock or vid_rdy

AUD_LSCLK0_USE_SYM_LOCK_OR_VID_RDY_FOR_R.Comment: 1:  use symbol lock for releasing reset:  use vid_rdy for releasing reset

AUD_LSCLK0_ALLOW_CTL_FIFO_RST_IN_HW.Comment: For PSR, we need to reset ctl_fifo in HW.

AUD_LSCLK0_CORR_ECC_ERROR_DETECT_EN.Comment: Enable ECC logic to generate correctableinterrupt when error count is greater than error_thresh

AUD_LSCLK0_ECC_FAIL_DETECT_EN.Comment: Enable ECC logic to generate failure ifof failure is greater than fail_thresh

AUD_LSCLK0_ECC_ERR_CNT.Description: DP RX ECC Fail count. Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

AUD_LSCLK0_MN_CONTROL_A.Description: Audio MN control. Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

AUD_LSCLK0_MAUD_LSB_UPDATE_EN.Comment: 0: disable maud lsb update: enable maud lsb update

DEC0_PPS0.Description: Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

DEC0_DSC_VERSION_MAJOR.Comment: This value contains the major version of DSC. It shall be equal to 1 for encoders that implement this specification.

DEC0_DSC_VERSION_MINOR.Comment: This value contains the minor version of DSC. It shall be equal to 0 for encoders that implement this specification.

DEC0_PPS_IDENTIFIER.Comment: This value is an application-specific identifier that can be used to differentiate between different PPS tables. If the application specification does not specify an application-specific means of PPS transmission (see section 0), this value shall be equal to 0.

DEC0_BITS_PER_COMPONENT.Comment: This value indicates the number of bits per component for the original pixels of the encoded picture. It shall be equal to 8, 10, or 12.

DEC0_LINEBUF_DEPTH.Comment: This value contains the line buffer bit depth used to generate the stream. If the bit depth of a component (after color-space conversion, see section 10.1) is greater than this value, the line storage rounds the reconstructed values to this number of bits. It shall be in the range of 8 to 13, inclusive.

DEC0_PPS1.Description: Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

DEC0_BLOCK_PRED_ENABLE.Comment: This flag indicates that the decoder needs to select between block prediction and MMAP using the method described in section 10.4.4.1. If it is set to 0, no BP is used to code the picture.

DEC0_CONVERT_RGB.Comment: This flag indicates whether the compressed stream encodes RGB that was converted to YCoCg. If it is set to 0, the color space is assumed to be YCbCr. If it is set to 1, the decoder performs a color space conversion from YCoCg to RGB.

DEC0_SIMPLE_422.Comment: Indicates whether reconstructed pixels should be 4:2:2 format created by dropping samples using the method described in Annex B. simple_422 shall be 0 if either native_420 or native_422 is equal to 1.0 = Decoder does not drop samples to reconstruct 4:2:2 pixels= Decoder drops samples to reconstruct 4:2:2 pixels

DEC0_VBR_ENABLE.Comment: This flag enables on/off VBR mode if it is supported by the decoder and the transport (see section 7.7.2).

DEC0_BITS_PER_PIXEL.Comment: This value specifies the target bits/pixel (bpp) rate that was used by the encoder in steps of 1/16 of a bit per pixel. Only values greater than or equal to 6 bpp are allowed. If vbr_enable is set to 0, this value must be less than or equal to the sustained rate that would apply if MPP were always selected, which is a function of bits_per_component, convert_rgb, and rc_range_parameters[0].

DEC0_PIC_HEIGHT.Comment: This value specifies the size of the picture in terms of pixels, where pic_height specifies the number of rows of pixels in the raster. Although not required, it is suggested that pic_width be close to integer multiples of slice_width.

DEC0_PPS2.Description: Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

DEC0_PIC_WIDTH.Comment: This value specifies the size of the picture in terms of pixels, where pic_width specifies the number of columns of pixels in the raster. Although not required, it is suggested that pic_height be close to integer multiples of slice_height.

DEC0_SLICE_HEIGHT.Comment: This value specifies the slice height for each slice. All slices that comprise a single picture are required to have an identical size. If the pic_height is not evenly divisible by the slice_height, the bottom row of pixels is replicated to pad the bottom-most slice(s) to be the same height as the other slices. The transport must allocate transmission time for sending the compressed bits corresponding to any replicated pixels.

DEC0_PPS3.Description: Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

DEC0_SLICE_WIDTH.Comment: This value specifies the slice height for each slice. All slices that comprise a single picture are required to have an identical size. If the pic_width is not evenly divisible by the slice_width, the rightmost column of pixels is replicated to pad the rightmost slices to be the same width as the other slices. The transport must allocate transmission time for sending the compressed bits corresponding to any replicated pixels.

DEC0_CHUNK_SIZE.Comment: This value indicates the size in bytes of the chunks that are used for slice multiplexing (see section 8.2.2). If vbr_enable is set to 1, this is the maximum size of the chunks. This value shall be set to ceil(bits_per_pixel * slice_width / 8).

DEC0_PPS4.Description: Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

DEC0_INITIAL_XMIT_DELAY.Comment: This value specifies the number of pixel times that the encoder waits before transmitting data from its rate buffer.

DEC0_INITIAL_DEC_DELAY.Comment: This value specifies the number of pixel times that the decoder accumulates data in its rate buffer before starting to decode and output pixels.

DEC0_PPS5.Description: Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

DEC0_INITIAL_SCALE_VALUE.Comment: This value specifies the initial value for rcXformScale used at the beginning of a slice (see section 10.8.2).

DEC0_SCALE_INCREMENT_INTERVAL.Comment: This value specifies the number of group times between incrementing the rcXformScale factor at the end of a slice (see section 10.8.2).

DEC0_PPS6.Description: Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

DEC0_SCALE_DECREMENT_INTERVAL.Comment: This value specifies the number of group times between decrementing the rcXformScale factor at the beginning of a slice (see section 10.8.2).

DEC0_FIRST_LINE_BPG_OFFSET.Comment: This value specifies the number of additional bits that are allocated for each group on the first line of a slice.

DEC0_PPS7.Description: Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

DEC0_NFL_BPG_OFFSET.Comment: This value specifies the number of bits (including fractional bits) that are deallocated for each group for groups after the first line of a slice.

DEC0_SLICE_BPG_OFFSET.Comment: This value specifies the number of bits (including fractional bits) that are deallocated for each group in order to enforce the slice constraint (i.e., that the final fullness cannot exceed the initial transmission delay * bits per group) while allowing a programmable initial_offset.

DEC0_PPS8.Description: Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

DEC0_INITIAL_OFFSET.Comment: This value specifies the initial value for rcXformOffset, which is initial_offset - rc_model_size at the start of a slice (see section 10.8.2).

DEC0_FINAL_OFFSET.Comment: This value specifies the maximum end-of-slice value for rcXformOffset, which is final_offset - rc_model_size (see section 10.8.2).

DEC0_PPS9.Description: Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

DEC0_FLATNESS_MIN_QP.Comment: This value specifies the minimum QP where flatness is signaled and the flatness QP adjustment is made.

DEC0_FLATNESS_MAX_QP.Comment: This value specifies the maximum QP where flatness is signaled and the flatness QP adjustment is made.

DEC0_RC_MODEL_SIZE.Comment: This value specifies the number of bits in the 'RC model', which is described in section 10.8.2.

DEC0_PPS10.Description: Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

DEC0_RC_EDGE_FACTOR.Comment: This value is compared to the ratio of current activity to previous activity in order to determine the presence of an 'edge', which in turn determines whether or not the QP is incremented in the short-term rate control (see section 10.8.4).

DEC0_RC_QUANT_INCR_LIMIT0.Comment: This value is a QP threshold that is used in the short-term rate control (see section 10.8.4).

DEC0_RC_QUANT_INCR_LIMIT1.Comment: This value is a QP threshold that is used in the short-term rate control (see section 10.8.4).

DEC0_RC_TGT_OFFSET_HI.Comment: This value specifies the upper end of the range of variability around the target bits per group that is allowed by the short-term rate control (see section 10.8.4).

DEC0_RC_TGT_OFFSET_LO.Comment: This value specifies the lower end of the range of variability around the target bits per group that is allowed by the short-term rate control (see section 10.8.4).

DEC0_NATIVE_422.Comment: 0 = native 4:2:2 mode is not used= native 4:2:2 mode is usedvalue shall be 0 if dsc_version_minor equals 1, if simple_422 is equal to 1, or if native_420 is equal to 1.

DEC0_SECOND_LINE_BPG_OFS.Comment: Specifies additional bits/group budget for the second line of a slice in Native 4:2:0 mode (see Section 6.8.2).shall be 0 if either of the following conditions exist:* dsc_version_minor = 1* native_420 = 0

DEC0_NSL_BPG_OFFSET.Comment: Specifies the number of bits (including fractional bits) that are de-allocated for each group that is not in the second line of a slice. If the second line has an additional bit budget, the additional bits that are allocated must come out of the budget for coding the remainder of the slice. Therefore, the value must be programmed to second_line_bpg_offset / (slice_height - 1), and then rounded up to 16 fractional bits.shall be 0 if either of the following conditions exist:* dsc_version_minor = 1* native_420 = 0

DEC0_START_DLY.Description: Decoder start delay to output frame start. Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

DEC0_OUTPUT_DLY.Comment: Delay from decoder start to output frame start. Delay from input line start to output line start.

DEC0_STRICT_LINE_START_DLY.Comment: In strict timing mode, delay in line start. Typically program to HACTIVE/2 to account for DP jitter relative to HDMI timing

DEC0_FRM_CTRL.Description: In strict timing mode, reset frame when phase difference between actual and expected frame start is greater than margin. Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

DEC0_PHASE_DIFF_MARGIN.Comment: Margin for reset. Set from 0 (always resync) to htotal (don't resync within 1 line of expected)

DEC0_USE_HWIDTH_FOR_PIC_WIDTH.Comment: Ignore sdp configuration for pic width only. Use HWIDTH for PIC_WIDTH

DEC0_HSTART_MOD.Comment: In strict timing mode, 3 - HSTART/pix_per_clk mod 3

DEC0_SINGLE_CORE_MODE.Comment: Use only one 4 slice 10k decoder in 4 pix per clk mode.

DEC0_BLANK_PIX_THROTTLE_4PPC.Comment: In 4 pix per clk mode, throttle blank times. This will space out the blank pixels to fill line time.

DEC0_LINE_CNT_IN_ACT_MODE.Comment: 0 - Generate line count in active based on line count only- Assert line count in active just before first data and deassert before last data

DEC0_GEN_FLUSH_LINE_STARTS.Comment: Decoder generates flush lines instead of framer.

DEC0_OUT_FOLLOWS_INP_LINES.Comment: Output number of lines cannot exceed number of input lines

DEC0_IGNORE_SINK_RDY.Comment: Ignore downstream sink rdy. Can be used to get out of deadlocks but might cause underflows

DEC0_PHASE_DIFF_RESYNC_EN.Comment: When the phase difference on the incoming frame start is bigger than expected, resync output frame

DEC0_DBL_RATE_CTRL.Description: CRC on symbol data input. Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

DEC0_FLUSH_LINES.Comment: Generate a number of dummy lines at end of frame

DEC0_PIX_PREFETCH_MODE.Comment: When 1, read first pixels as soon as possible rather than beginning on line. When DBL_RATE_EN=1, set to 1.

DEC0_DBL_RATE_RDY_THRESH.Comment: When this number of pixels*3 is buffered, allow read out. For sustained readout at 6 pix pix per clk, set to SLICE_WIDTH/(3*2)+2. For sustained readout at 4 pix pix per clk, set to SLICE_WIDTH/(3*4*3)+2.

DEC0_DEBUG_CORE_MULT_SEL.Comment: Debug select for which core mult.

DEC0_DEBUG_SEL.Comment: Debug select for 8 bit debug bus.

DEC0_CRC_S422_AS_444.Comment: In simple 422, compute CRC on 444 data before downsample to 422

DEC0_CRC_OUT_POL_INV.Comment: In simple 422 and native 420 mode, invert odd/even pixel (simple422) or lines (native420) for accumulating chroma

DEC0_CRC_OUT_EN.Comment: Enable CRC generation on input symbol stream

DEC0_CRC_IN_EN.Comment: Enable CRC generation on input symbol stream

ML_FRM1_HORZ_VIEW_XPAND_LAST_PIXEL.Comment: If the user wants to extract a horizontal subsectionof the image, this field specifies the last pixel

ML_FRM1_HORZ_VIEW_XPAND_FIRST_PIXEL.Comment: If the user wants to extract a horizontal subsectionof the image, this field specifies the first pixel

ML_FRM1_VERT_VIEW_XPAND_LAST_LINE.Comment: If the user wants to extract a vertical subsection of the image, this field specifies the last line

ML_FRM1_VERT_VIEW_XPAND_FIRST_LINE.Comment: If the user wants to extract a vertical subsection of the image, this field specifies the first line

ML_FRM1_MIN_R_CR_VAL.Comment: Min value for R/Cr component. The internal logic clips the signal to this value

ML_FRM1_MAX_R_CR_VAL.Comment: Max value for R/Cr component. The internal logic clips the signal to this value

ML_FRM1_MIN_G_Y_VAL.Comment: Min value for G/Y component. The internal logic clips the signal to this value

ML_FRM1_MAX_G_Y_VAL.Comment: Max value for G/Y component. The internal logic clips the signal to this value

ML_FRM1_MIN_B_CB_VAL.Comment: Min value for B/Cb component. The internal logic clips the signal to this value

ML_FRM1_MAX_B_CB_VAL.Comment: Max value for B/Cb component. The internal logic clips the signal to this value

ML_FRM1_VIEWXPAND_ALLOW_VERT.Comment: Allow vert viewexpand (cya, should be ok to leave=1)

ML_FRM1_VIEWXPAND_HWIDTH.Comment: This is the hwidth for viewxpand

ML_FRM1_HFILL.Comment: This field is to add HFILL for Bezel Correction. The field represents number of pixels of HFILL

ML_FRM1_VIF_SINK_RDY_PAUSE_BLANK.Comment: Allow vif_sink_rdy to pause blank pixel generation.  Set to 1 in HDMI2.1 FRL mode.

ML_FRM1_VID_REGEN_COMP_SEL_FOR_POST2.Comment: component remap control on the video interface, component 2 comes out on pixel interface bits 35:24, by default this is G (Y), which comes internally in section 1

ML_FRM1_VID_REGEN_COMP_SEL_FOR_POST1.Comment: component remap control on the video interface, component 1 comes out on pixel interface bits 23:12, by default this is B (Cb), which comes internally in section 0

ML_FRM1_VID_REGEN_COMP_SEL_FOR_POST0.Comment: component remap control on the video interface, component 0 comes out on pixel interface bits 11:0, by default this is R (Cr), which comes internally in section 2

ML_FRM1_VIF_FRAME_START_RD_SOFT_RST_EN.Comment: Assert read soft reset on falling edge of vblank

ML_FRM1_VIF_PIX_PER_CLK.Comment: Number of Pixels per clock on the VIF

ML_FRM1_HFILL_ON_RIGHT.Comment: This field is to add HFILL on right for Bezel Correction

ML_FRM1_HFILL_ON_LEFT.Comment: This field is to add HFILL on left for Bezel Correction

ML_FRM1_BLACK_SCREEN_IF_CP_ON.Comment: Set this bit if HDCP Authentication fails on the Tx.

ML_FRM1_PTG_B.Comment: This is the blue component for flat color pattern

ML_FRM1_PTG_G.Comment: This is the green component for flat color pattern

ML_FRM1_PTG_R.Comment: This is the red component for flat color pattern

ML_FRM1_PTG_HIGH_CONTRAST_COLOR_EN.Comment: Setting this will send colors in a non-gradient checkerboard pattern

ML_FRM1_PTG_LOW_CONTRAST.Comment: Setting this will send a gradient checkerboard pattern

ML_FRM1_PTG_PAT_SEL.Comment: 2'd0   :  white frame boundary whith balck background2'd1   :  color ramp2'd2   :  checker-board. Use the other fields to get all the functionality2'd3   :  VESA CTS checker-board. Use the other fields to get all the functionality

ML_FRM1_PTG_EN.Comment: Setting this bit will enable the deframer to send out an internally generated Video pattern

ML_FRM1_PTG_VSTRIP_SIZE.Comment: This is the hsize of a checkerboard block

ML_FRM1_PTG_HSTRIP_SIZE.Comment: This is the hsize of a checkerboard block

ML_FRM1_CRC1.Comment: This is the CRC calculation on the component in position 23:12

ML_FRM1_CRC0.Comment: This is the CRC calculation on the component in position 11:0

ML_FRM1_CRC_UPDATE_CNT.Comment: 4 bit wrap around count for CRC register updateTo be written to DPCD addr 246h

ML_FRM1_CRC2.Comment: This is the CRC calculation on the component in position 35:24

ML_FRM1_PTG_FRM_CNT_FOR_RFR_RATE_TRIG.Comment: Update TOTALS/STARTS every N frames during vblank

ML_FRM1_PTG_RFR_RATE_CHNG_EVERY_FRM.Comment: Update TOTALS/STARTS every frame during vblank

ML_FRM1_PTG_RFR_RATE_CHNG_TRIGGER_DIS.Comment: Disable trigger, update TOTALS/STARTS whenever new value is written

ML_FRM1_RELEASE_SOFT_RST_ON_PSR_STATE2_E.Comment: Release rd_soft_rst when psr state 2 is exited

ML_FRM1_RELEASE_SOFT_RST_ON_MSA_RCVD.Comment: Release rd_sof_rst when msa is received

ML_FRM1_RST_ON_ENTERING_PSR_STATE2.Comment: Reset read logic when PSR state 2 is entered

ML_FRM1_DISALLOW_POSEDGE_RST_FOR_SU.Comment: During Selective update we need to set this registerto disallow phase reset on posedge of vblank

ML_FRM1_RST_ON_END_OF_SU_IN_PSR.Comment: Put read logic of framer in soft reset when end ofselective update is received.

ML_FRM1_FORCE_SYM_LOCK_FOR_PSR.Comment: For standby when symbol lock is not flagged,set this to mask entering back into power down state.

ML_FRM1_PSR_SU_SM_IN_RST.Comment: Set this to reset PSR selective update state machine.

ML_FRM1_THROTTLE_FLUSH_LN.Comment: Enable throttling of pixel counter for flush lines, which is also considered a vblank line

ML_FRM1_THROTTLE_VACTIVE.Comment: Enable throttling of pixel counter for vactive lines

ML_FRM1_THROTTLE_VBLANK.Comment: Enable throttling of pixel counter for all vblank lines, not just flush lines

DEC1_PPS0.Description: Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

DEC1_DSC_VERSION_MAJOR.Comment: This value contains the major version of DSC. It shall be equal to 1 for encoders that implement this specification.

DEC1_DSC_VERSION_MINOR.Comment: This value contains the minor version of DSC. It shall be equal to 0 for encoders that implement this specification.

DEC1_PPS_IDENTIFIER.Comment: This value is an application-specific identifier that can be used to differentiate between different PPS tables. If the application specification does not specify an application-specific means of PPS transmission (see section 0), this value shall be equal to 0.

DEC1_BITS_PER_COMPONENT.Comment: This value indicates the number of bits per component for the original pixels of the encoded picture. It shall be equal to 8, 10, or 12.

DEC1_LINEBUF_DEPTH.Comment: This value contains the line buffer bit depth used to generate the stream. If the bit depth of a component (after color-space conversion, see section 10.1) is greater than this value, the line storage rounds the reconstructed values to this number of bits. It shall be in the range of 8 to 13, inclusive.

DEC1_PPS1.Description: Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

DEC1_BLOCK_PRED_ENABLE.Comment: This flag indicates that the decoder needs to select between block prediction and MMAP using the method described in section 10.4.4.1. If it is set to 0, no BP is used to code the picture.

DEC1_CONVERT_RGB.Comment: This flag indicates whether the compressed stream encodes RGB that was converted to YCoCg. If it is set to 0, the color space is assumed to be YCbCr. If it is set to 1, the decoder performs a color space conversion from YCoCg to RGB.

DEC1_SIMPLE_422.Comment: Indicates whether reconstructed pixels should be 4:2:2 format created by dropping samples using the method described in Annex B. simple_422 shall be 0 if either native_420 or native_422 is equal to 1.0 = Decoder does not drop samples to reconstruct 4:2:2 pixels= Decoder drops samples to reconstruct 4:2:2 pixels

DEC1_VBR_ENABLE.Comment: This flag enables on/off VBR mode if it is supported by the decoder and the transport (see section 7.7.2).

DEC1_BITS_PER_PIXEL.Comment: This value specifies the target bits/pixel (bpp) rate that was used by the encoder in steps of 1/16 of a bit per pixel. Only values greater than or equal to 6 bpp are allowed. If vbr_enable is set to 0, this value must be less than or equal to the sustained rate that would apply if MPP were always selected, which is a function of bits_per_component, convert_rgb, and rc_range_parameters[0].

DEC1_PIC_HEIGHT.Comment: This value specifies the size of the picture in terms of pixels, where pic_height specifies the number of rows of pixels in the raster. Although not required, it is suggested that pic_width be close to integer multiples of slice_width.

DEC1_PPS2.Description: Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

DEC1_PIC_WIDTH.Comment: This value specifies the size of the picture in terms of pixels, where pic_width specifies the number of columns of pixels in the raster. Although not required, it is suggested that pic_height be close to integer multiples of slice_height.

DEC1_SLICE_HEIGHT.Comment: This value specifies the slice height for each slice. All slices that comprise a single picture are required to have an identical size. If the pic_height is not evenly divisible by the slice_height, the bottom row of pixels is replicated to pad the bottom-most slice(s) to be the same height as the other slices. The transport must allocate transmission time for sending the compressed bits corresponding to any replicated pixels.

DEC1_PPS3.Description: Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

DEC1_SLICE_WIDTH.Comment: This value specifies the slice height for each slice. All slices that comprise a single picture are required to have an identical size. If the pic_width is not evenly divisible by the slice_width, the rightmost column of pixels is replicated to pad the rightmost slices to be the same width as the other slices. The transport must allocate transmission time for sending the compressed bits corresponding to any replicated pixels.

DEC1_CHUNK_SIZE.Comment: This value indicates the size in bytes of the chunks that are used for slice multiplexing (see section 8.2.2). If vbr_enable is set to 1, this is the maximum size of the chunks. This value shall be set to ceil(bits_per_pixel * slice_width / 8).

DEC1_PPS4.Description: Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

DEC1_INITIAL_XMIT_DELAY.Comment: This value specifies the number of pixel times that the encoder waits before transmitting data from its rate buffer.

DEC1_INITIAL_DEC_DELAY.Comment: This value specifies the number of pixel times that the decoder accumulates data in its rate buffer before starting to decode and output pixels.

DEC1_PPS5.Description: Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

DEC1_INITIAL_SCALE_VALUE.Comment: This value specifies the initial value for rcXformScale used at the beginning of a slice (see section 10.8.2).

DEC1_SCALE_INCREMENT_INTERVAL.Comment: This value specifies the number of group times between incrementing the rcXformScale factor at the end of a slice (see section 10.8.2).

DEC1_PPS6.Description: Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

DEC1_SCALE_DECREMENT_INTERVAL.Comment: This value specifies the number of group times between decrementing the rcXformScale factor at the beginning of a slice (see section 10.8.2).

DEC1_FIRST_LINE_BPG_OFFSET.Comment: This value specifies the number of additional bits that are allocated for each group on the first line of a slice.

DEC1_PPS7.Description: Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

DEC1_NFL_BPG_OFFSET.Comment: This value specifies the number of bits (including fractional bits) that are deallocated for each group for groups after the first line of a slice.

DEC1_SLICE_BPG_OFFSET.Comment: This value specifies the number of bits (including fractional bits) that are deallocated for each group in order to enforce the slice constraint (i.e., that the final fullness cannot exceed the initial transmission delay * bits per group) while allowing a programmable initial_offset.

DEC1_PPS8.Description: Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

DEC1_INITIAL_OFFSET.Comment: This value specifies the initial value for rcXformOffset, which is initial_offset - rc_model_size at the start of a slice (see section 10.8.2).

DEC1_FINAL_OFFSET.Comment: This value specifies the maximum end-of-slice value for rcXformOffset, which is final_offset - rc_model_size (see section 10.8.2).

DEC1_PPS9.Description: Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

DEC1_FLATNESS_MIN_QP.Comment: This value specifies the minimum QP where flatness is signaled and the flatness QP adjustment is made.

DEC1_FLATNESS_MAX_QP.Comment: This value specifies the maximum QP where flatness is signaled and the flatness QP adjustment is made.

DEC1_RC_MODEL_SIZE.Comment: This value specifies the number of bits in the 'RC model', which is described in section 10.8.2.

DEC1_PPS10.Description: Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

DEC1_RC_EDGE_FACTOR.Comment: This value is compared to the ratio of current activity to previous activity in order to determine the presence of an 'edge', which in turn determines whether or not the QP is incremented in the short-term rate control (see section 10.8.4).

DEC1_RC_QUANT_INCR_LIMIT0.Comment: This value is a QP threshold that is used in the short-term rate control (see section 10.8.4).

DEC1_RC_QUANT_INCR_LIMIT1.Comment: This value is a QP threshold that is used in the short-term rate control (see section 10.8.4).

DEC1_RC_TGT_OFFSET_HI.Comment: This value specifies the upper end of the range of variability around the target bits per group that is allowed by the short-term rate control (see section 10.8.4).

DEC1_RC_TGT_OFFSET_LO.Comment: This value specifies the lower end of the range of variability around the target bits per group that is allowed by the short-term rate control (see section 10.8.4).

DEC1_PPS11.Description: Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

DEC1_RC_BUF_THRESH_0.Comment: These values specify the thresholds in the 'RC model' for the 15 ranges (see section 10.8.3). There are 6 LSB's appended to each value.

DEC1_RC_BUF_THRESH_1.Comment: These values specify the thresholds in the 'RC model' for the 15 ranges (see section 10.8.3). There are 6 LSB's appended to each value.

DEC1_NATIVE_420.Comment: 0 = native 4:2:0 mode is not used= native 4:2:0 mode is usedvalue shall be 0 if dsc_version_minor equals 1, if simple_422 is equal to 1, or if native_422 is equal to 1.

DEC1_NATIVE_422.Comment: 0 = native 4:2:2 mode is not used= native 4:2:2 mode is usedvalue shall be 0 if dsc_version_minor equals 1, if simple_422 is equal to 1, or if native_420 is equal to 1.

DEC1_SECOND_LINE_BPG_OFS.Comment: Specifies additional bits/group budget for the second line of a slice in Native 4:2:0 mode (see Section 6.8.2).shall be 0 if either of the following conditions exist:* dsc_version_minor = 1* native_420 = 0

DEC1_NSL_BPG_OFFSET.Comment: Specifies the number of bits (including fractional bits) that are de-allocated for each group that is not in the second line of a slice. If the second line has an additional bit budget, the additional bits that are allocated must come out of the budget for coding the remainder of the slice. Therefore, the value must be programmed to second_line_bpg_offset / (slice_height - 1), and then rounded up to 16 fractional bits.shall be 0 if either of the following conditions exist:* dsc_version_minor = 1* native_420 = 0

DEC1_PPS23.Description: Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

DEC1_SECOND_LINE_OFS_ADJ.Comment: Used as an offset adjustment for the second line in Native 4:2:0 mode (see Section 6.8.2).shall be 0 if either of the following conditions exist:* dsc_version_minor = 1* native_420 = 0
