DEC1_START_DLY.Description: Decoder start delay to output frame start. Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

DEC1_OUTPUT_DLY.Comment: Delay from decoder start to output frame start. Delay from input line start to output line start.

DEC1_STRICT_LINE_START_DLY.Comment: In strict timing mode, delay in line start. Typically program to HACTIVE/2 to account for DP jitter relative to HDMI timing

DEC1_FRM_CTRL.Description: In strict timing mode, reset frame when phase difference between actual and expected frame start is greater than margin. Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

DEC1_PHASE_DIFF_MARGIN.Comment: Margin for reset. Set from 0 (always resync) to htotal (don't resync within 1 line of expected)

DEC1_USE_HWIDTH_FOR_PIC_WIDTH.Comment: Ignore sdp configuration for pic width only. Use HWIDTH for PIC_WIDTH

DEC1_HSTART_MOD.Comment: In strict timing mode, 3 - HSTART/pix_per_clk mod 3

DEC1_SINGLE_CORE_MODE.Comment: Use only one 4 slice 10k decoder in 4 pix per clk mode.

DEC1_BLANK_PIX_THROTTLE_4PPC.Comment: In 4 pix per clk mode, throttle blank times. This will space out the blank pixels to fill line time.

DEC1_LINE_CNT_IN_ACT_MODE.Comment: 0 - Generate line count in active based on line count only- Assert line count in active just before first data and deassert before last data

DEC1_GEN_FLUSH_LINE_STARTS.Comment: Decoder generates flush lines instead of framer.

DEC1_OUT_FOLLOWS_INP_LINES.Comment: Output number of lines cannot exceed number of input lines

DEC1_IGNORE_SINK_RDY.Comment: Ignore downstream sink rdy. Can be used to get out of deadlocks but might cause underflows

DEC1_PHASE_DIFF_RESYNC_EN.Comment: When the phase difference on the incoming frame start is bigger than expected, resync output frame

DEC1_DBL_RATE_CTRL.Description: CRC on symbol data input. Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

DEC1_FLUSH_LINES.Comment: Generate a number of dummy lines at end of frame

DEC1_PIX_PREFETCH_MODE.Comment: When 1, read first pixels as soon as possible rather than beginning on line. When DBL_RATE_EN=1, set to 1.

DEC1_DBL_RATE_RDY_THRESH.Comment: When this number of pixels*3 is buffered, allow read out. For sustained readout at 6 pix pix per clk, set to SLICE_WIDTH/(3*2)+2. For sustained readout at 4 pix pix per clk, set to SLICE_WIDTH/(3*4*3)+2.

DEC1_DEBUG_CORE_MULT_SEL.Comment: Debug select for which core mult.

DEC1_DEBUG_SEL.Comment: Debug select for 8 bit debug bus.

DEC1_CRC_CTRL.Description: CRC on symbol data input. Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

DEC1_CRC_POLY.Comment: This is the Pix CRC polynomial.

DEC1_CRC_S422_AS_444.Comment: In simple 422, compute CRC on 444 data before downsample to 422

DEC1_CRC_OUT_POL_INV.Comment: In simple 422 and native 420 mode, invert odd/even pixel (simple422) or lines (native420) for accumulating chroma

DEC1_CRC_OUT_EN.Comment: Enable CRC generation on input symbol stream

DEC1_CRC_IN_EN.Comment: Enable CRC generation on input symbol stream

DEC1_CRC_CNT.Description: CRC on symbol data input. Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

DEC1_CRC_STAT0.Description: CRC on video data output. Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

DEC1_CRC_STAT1.Description: CRC on video data output. Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

DEC1_CRC_STAT2.Description: CRC on video data output. Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

DEC1_DEBUG_CTRL.Description: ASP control output. Accessed on ls_clk (81MHz/RBR, 135MHz/HBR, 270MHz/HBR2, reg_clk, or DC) domain.

DEC1_DBG_MASK.Comment: 1 - enable bit on debug bus, applied after rotate

DEC1_DBG_ROTR.Comment: Bits to rotate debug bus right, applied before mask

AUX_CTRL.Description: Clock / Reset control.  Accessed on aux_mailbox_intf_clk (27MHz - 270MHz, or DC) domain.

AUX_DBG_TAP_SEL.Comment: Debug-bus tap select0 = GTC counter bits[19:0]1 = GTC counter bits[31:12]2 = MAUX encode3 = MAUX decode4 = XMT framer5 = RCV framer6 = DPCD HW Rd7 = DPCD HW Wr8 = RCV Mbox9 = XMT Mboxothers reserved

AUX_AUX_RBIF_FORCE_CLK_EN.Comment: Force AUX register bus clock enable.  Only for backup in case register events are broken.

AUX_LS_HARD_RSTN.Comment: Hard reset (ls_clk for GTC synchronizer).  When asserted, AUX is held in reset.  Active low

AUX_LS_CLK_GATE.Comment: Clock gate (ls_clk for GTC synchronizer).  Clock is active when CLK_GATE=1

AUX_HARD_RSTN.Comment: Hard reset.  When asserted, AUX is held in reset.  Active low

AUX_CLK_GATE.Comment: Clock gate.  Clock is active when CLK_GATE=1

AUX_INT_STATUS.Description: AUX interrupts. Accessed on aux_mailbox_intf_clk (27MHz - 270MHz, or DC) domain; Writing '1' will clear the status to 0

AUX_GTC_RECEPTION_ERR_INT_STATUS.Comment: AUX GTC Reception value error interrupt

AUX_XMT_MAILBOX_FIFO_OFLOW_INT_STATUS.Comment: AUX Transmit Mailbox FIFO overflow event interrupt

AUX_XMT_MAILBOX_FIFO_UFLOW_INT_STATUS.Comment: AUX Transmit Mailbox FIFO underflow event interrupt

AUX_RCV_MAILBOX_FIFO_OFLOW_INT_STATUS.Comment: AUX Receive Mailbox FIFO overflow event interrupt

AUX_RCV_MAILBOX_FIFO_UFLOW_INT_STATUS.Comment: AUX Receive Mailbox FIFO underflow event interrupt

AUX_MAUX_RX_PHY_WAKE_INT_STATUS.Comment: ALPM sequence detected on  MAUX RX

AUX_XUSB_RX_ERR_INT_STATUS.Comment: Manchester-AUX Receiver ERR detected event interrupt

AUX_FAUX_RX_ERR_INT_STATUS.Comment: Manchester-AUX Receiver ERR detected event interrupt

AUX_MAUX_RX_ERR_INT_STATUS.Comment: Manchester-AUX Receiver ERR detected event interrupt

AUX_INT_EN.Description: AUX interrupt enables. Accessed on aux_mailbox_intf_clk (27MHz - 270MHz, or DC) domain

AUX_SPARE0.Description: Spare RW registers.  Accessed on aux_mailbox_intf_clk (27MHz - 270MHz, or DC) domain.

AUX_ANALOG_PORT_STATUS.Description: Read-only status of combinatorial signals between Analog/Custom and RTL.  Accessed on aux_mailbox_intf_clk (27MHz - 270MHz, or DC) domain.  FAUX data and clock are not represented in this register.  These values reflect the settings from POLARITY_CTRL unless otherwise stated.

AUX_ANALOG_SQDET_VAL.Comment: Raw input value of afe_aux_sqdet.  Not affected by SQDET_POL

AUX_ANALOG_MAUX_RX_DATA_VAL.Comment: Raw input value of afe_maux_rx_data.  Not affected by MAUX_RX_DATA_POL

AUX_ANALOG_FORCE_CDR_INIT_N.Comment: Force FAUX CDR into reset_n (active-low, just like afe_aux_cdr_init_n).

AUX_ANALOG_SQREFCTL_LEVELS.Description: Squelch-detector reference-voltage control.  Accessed on aux_mailbox_intf_clk (27MHz - 270MHz, or DC) domain.

AUX_ANALOG_FORCE_SQDET_STOP.Comment: Force afe_aux_sqdet_stop <= 1'b1.  This disables squelch detector.

AUX_ANALOG_POLARITY_CTRL.Description: Polarity control on interface signals between analog and core.  Accessed on aux_mailbox_intf_clk (27MHz - 270MHz, or DC) domain. 1'b0 = normal polarity (active-low for signals ending in _n, active-high for all others. 1'b1 = reversed polarity (active-high for signals ending in _n, active-low for all others.

AUX_ANALOG_BUS_TURNAROUND_CTRL.Description: Controls Rx<->Tx bus turnaround times.  Accessed on aux_mailbox_intf_clk (27MHz - 270MHz, or DC) domain.

AUX_ANALOG_FORCE_VCMEN_N.Comment: Force afe_aux_vcmen_n to 1'b1 (OFF) always.  Polarity bit can be used to set to static 1'b0

AUX_ANALOG_FORCE_TERM_EN.Comment: Force afe_aux_term_en to 1'b1 (ON) always.  Polarity bit can be used to set to static 1'b0

AUX_ANALOG_HW_BUS_TURNAROUND_CTRL.Description: Controls Rx<->Tx bus turnaround times.  Accessed on aux_mailbox_intf_clk (27MHz - 270MHz, or DC) domain.

AUX_MAUX_PHY_CONTROL_0.Description: MAUX PHY control register 0. Accessed on aux_mailbox_intf_clk (27MHz - 270MHz, or DC) domain.

AUX_MAUX_HALF_UI_PERIOD_LP.Comment: Average 1/2 UI period (in lposc clocks) for

AUX_MAUX_SEND_PHY_WAKE.Comment: This register is set to send phy_wake. DO_TRANSMIT bitshould be set along with this register

AUX_MAUX_SEND_PHY_WAKE_ACK.Comment: This register is set to send phy_wake_ack. DO_TRANSMIT bitshould be set along with this register

AUX_MAUX_TX_SYNC_COUNT.Comment: Number of Manchester-II encoded 0's to send in AUX preamble

AUX_MAUX_DEBOUNCE_LEN.Comment: Number of clocks to debounce inbound Manchester-II AUX data.  This is after meta-flop, and the actual number of clocks is MAUX_DEBOUNCE_LEN+2 (FIXME: check for accuracy)

AUX_MAUX_HALF_UI_PERIOD.Comment: Average 1/2 UI period (in clocks) for both seeding the receiver and for driving transmit data.

AUX_MAUX_PHY_STATUS_0.Description: MAUX PHY status register 0.  Accessed on aux_mailbox_intf_clk (27MHz - 270MHz, or DC) domain.

AUX_MAUX_MEAS_HALF_UI_PERIOD.Comment: Measured 1/2 UI period (in clocks) of the last received Manchester-II encoded transaction

AUX_FAUX_PHY_STATUS_0.Description: FAUX PHY status register 0. Accessed on aux_mailbox_intf_clk (27MHz - 270MHz, or DC) domain.

AUX_FAUX_BIT_INVERT_RSLT.Comment: Result of 8b/10b polarity detection.0 = FAUX polarity is correct.1 = FAUX polarity is inverted.

AUX_FAUX_BIT_REVERSE_RSLT.Comment: Result of 8b/10b bit-reversal detection.0 = FAUX is LSB-first.1 = FAUX is MSB-first.

AUX_FAUX_PHY_CONTROL_0.Description: FAUX PHY control register 0. Accessed on aux_mailbox_intf_clk (27MHz - 270MHz, or DC) domain.

AUX_FAUX_SCRAMBLER_EN.Comment: Enable LFSR de/scrambling on FAUX packets.

AUX_FAUX_CRC16_EN.Comment: Enable hardware calculation of CRC16 on FAUX packets.

AUX_FAUX_COMMA_SYMBOL.Comment: 8b/1b0 comma symbol.  8b/10b symbol alignment engine will attempt to find this 10-bit pattern and will align output data to comma boundary.  Alignment engine will check both positive and negative permutations of this register.  Register is defined in 8b/10b syntax as jhgf_iedcba.  Default value is K28.5+

AUX_FAUX_BIT_INVERT.Comment: When FAUX_BIT_INVERT_DETECT=0, enables 8b/10b polarity inversion.  Before MCU/FSM disables automatic polarity detection, it is necessary to copy the value of FAUX_BIT_INVERT_RSLT to this register.

AUX_FAUX_BIT_REVERSE.Comment: When FAUX_BIT_REVERSE_DETECT=0, enables 8b/10b bit reversal.  Before MCU/FSM disables automatic endian detection, it is necessary to copy the value of FAUX_BIT_REVERSE_RSLT to this register.

AUX_FAUX_BIT_INVERT_DETECT.Comment: Enables automatic detection/correction of 8b/10b polarity inversion.

AUX_FAUX_BIT_REVERSE_DETECT.Comment: Enables automatic detection/correction of 8b/10b symbol bit order.

AUX_FRAMER_SOURCE_MODE.Description: AUX Framer Source-mode configuration register.  Accessed on aux_mailbox_intf_clk (27MHz - 270MHz, or DC) domain.

AUX_FRAMER_REPEATER_MODE_EN.Comment: To enable legacy pass through repeater mode

AUX_FRAMER_SOURCE_MODE.Comment: Source-mode.0 = AUX port is configured as a sink-device1 = AUX port is configured as a source-device

AUX_FRAMER_XMT_CONTROL.Description: AUX Transmit Control Register. Accessed on aux_mailbox_intf_clk (27MHz - 270MHz, or DC) domain.

AUX_FRAMER_FW_RD_AUTORPLY_EN.Comment: Firmware Read Auto Reply logic is enabled if set to 1

AUX_FRAMER_TIMER_ELAPSED.Comment: AUX Timer to respond to an AUX request has expired

AUX_FRAMER_MASK_XMT_FRM_RD.Comment: Set for repeater mode to mask generation of xmt_framer_rd signal

AUX_FRAMER_IGNORE_MB_START_FOR_REPEATER.Comment: Ignore mailbox start signal when in repeater mode

AUX_FRAMER_IGNORE_MB_START_WHEN_ESM_EN.Comment: Ignore mailbox start signal when ESM xmt is in progress

AUX_FRAMER_IGNORE_MAILBOX_START.Comment: Ignore mailbox start signal when HW ACK is being sent

AUX_FRAMER_USE_DPCD_HW_PROC.Comment: Enabled only when dpcd read via aux hardware logic

AUX_FRAMER_TIMER_ELAPSED_TRANSMIT_EN.Comment: Enable transmission of reply from timeout

AUX_FRAMER_AUTO_TX_AT_EOF.Comment: Automatically begin transmission when EOF is written into XMT mailbox

AUX_FRAMER_DO_TRANSMIT.Comment: Write to trigger AUX transmission.  Data in mailbox will be transmitted based on TX_MAUXMODE register value.  Reading this register will always return '0'

AUX_FRAMER_RCV_CONTROL.Description: AUX receive framer control.  Accessed on aux_mailbox_intf_clk (27MHz - 270MHz, or DC) domain.

AUX_FRAMER_ENABLE_RECEIVE_FLAGS.Comment: If set, INPROGRESS flags are enabled.  Toggle this on-off-on to reset flags

AUX_FRAMER_XUSB_RECEIVE_INPROGRESS.Comment: FAUX decoder believes it is receiving 8b10b-encoded XUSB data.

AUX_FRAMER_FAUX_RECEIVE_INPROGRESS.Comment: FAUX decoder believes it is receiving 8b10b-encoded AUX data.

AUX_FRAMER_MAUX_RECEIVE_INPROGRESS.Comment: MAUX decoder believes it is receiving Manchester-encoded data.

AUX_FRAMER_CHECK_BAD_REPLY_COMMAND.Comment: Check for bits[3:0] of first received byte != 0, and that at most 1 bit is set in bits[7:4].Only useful for source-side (TX) AUX to detect improperly formatted reply.

AUX_FRAMER_ALLOW_LARGE_MAUX_TRANSACTIONS.Comment: Allow received MAUX transaction payloads larger than 16 bytes?0 = assert interrupt if MAUX payload is larger than 0xF1 = allow large MAUX payloads (even though they 'violate' spec)

AUX_FRAMER_TRASH_FIRST_N_BYTES.Comment: Trash first N received bytes.  RCV_CMD_ADDR will already store the first four bytes of request.  Setting this bit will save MCU cycles.  Recommended to set this = 4 for sink, 1 for source

AUX_FRAMER_REQUEST_COMMAND.Description: AUX Command, Address, and Length fields.  Accessed on aux_mailbox_intf_clk (27MHz - 270MHz, or DC) domain.

AUX_FRAMER_REPLY_STATUS.Description: AUX reply status and total # bytes written to FIFO.  Accessed on aux_mailbox_intf_clk (27MHz - 270MHz, or DC) domain.

AUX_FRAMER_AUTO_REPLY_FLAG.Comment: Current RCV payload (was)/(is being) automatically replied to

AUX_FRAMER_REP_LEN.Comment: Number of reply bytes, not including status byte

AUX_FRAMER_TIMEOUT_CONTROL.Description: AUX timeout control.  Accessed on aux_mailbox_intf_clk (27MHz - 270MHz, or DC) domain.

AUX_FRAMER_AUTO_ACK_LATE_READ_REQ.Comment: When read reply is presented to XMT FIFO after TIMEOUT occurs, automatically reply with pending XMT FIFO data if next read request is identical.

AUX_FRAMER_TIMEOUT_ACTION.Comment: Action to take at timeout event.0 = Do nothing.1 = Replay request from XMT FIFO.2 = Reply with DEFER.3 = Reply with ACK.4 = Reply with NACK.5 = Reply intelligently (ACK writes, DEFER reads if FIFO empty, partial ACK reads if FIFO is !empty but reply hasn't been initiated yet).6 = Reply based on firmware read of Receive MB FIFO.

AUX_FRAMER_NATIVE_AUTO_REPLY_ONLY.Comment: When replying w/ NACK or DEFER, only use Native-AUX (no I2C-over-AUX)

AUX_FRAMER_NATURAL_TIMEOUT_EN.Comment: To enable the natural timeout feature

AUX_FRAMER_FAUX_TIMER.Comment: Timeout timer ticks, in aux_mailbox_intf_clk (27MHz - 270MHz, or DC), for Fast-AUX transactions.

AUX_FRAMER_MAUX_TIMER.Comment: Timeout timer ticks, in usec, for Manchester-AUX transactions.

AUX_FRAMER_TIMER_STOP_TRG.Comment: Event that halts timeout counter.0 = detection of valid inbound transaction preamble1 = SYNC/START of inbound transaction2 = Preamble start of outbound transaction3 = SYNC/START of outbound transaction

AUX_FRAMER_TIMER_START_TRG.Comment: Event that initiates timeout counter.0 = Timer start disabled1 = STOP of inbound transaction2 = STOP of outbound transaction

AUX_FRAMER_TRANSACTION_ID.Description: Transaction IDs.  Accessed on aux_mailbox_intf_clk (27MHz - 270MHz, or DC) domain.

AUX_FRAMER_SBMSG_POLYNOMIALS.Description: Sideband Messaging CRC polynomials.  Accessed on aux_mailbox_intf_clk (27MHz - 270MHz, or DC) domain.

AUX_FRAMER_CRC_XMT_EN.Comment: Enable CRC generation for outbound SBMsg

AUX_FRAMER_CRC_RCV_EN.Comment: Enable CRC checking of inbound SBMsg

AUX_FRAMER_XMT_AUTOREPLY_CFG.Description: Configuration when timer elapsed is triggered.  Accessed on aux_mailbox_intf_clk (27MHz - 270MHz, or DC) domain.

AUX_FRAMER_CLR_XMT_FIFO_REPEAT_RD_NOTRDY.Comment: Allow clear of xmt FIFO for repeated read transactions

AUX_FRAMER_ALWYS_CLR_RCV_FIFO_FOR_RD.Comment: When set it clears RCV MB FIFO for read request on timeout

AUX_FRAMER_ALWYS_CLR_RCV_FIFO_FOR_WR.Comment: When set it clears RCV MB FIFO for write request on timeout

AUX_FRAMER_CLR_RCV_FIFO_ON_AUTOREPLY.Comment: This bit has to be set to honor bit 10 and bit 11 above

AUX_FRAMER_CLR_XMT_FIFO_ON_AUTOREPLY.Comment: This bit has to be set to honor bit 0 and bit 1 above

AUX_FRAMER_RST_FW_RD_ON_TIMEOUT.Comment: Reset fw_read bit when timer expired

AUX_FRAMER_RCV_SOF_2_RST_TIMER.Comment: Use rcv_sof interrupt to reset timer_elapsed_d

AUX_FRAMER_USE_MB_SAYS_START_2_RST_TIMER.Comment: Use mailbox_says_start signal to reset timer_elapsed_d

AUX_FRAMER_REP_DEFER_FOR_WR_NOFWRD.Comment: Autoreply with DEFER for write request when fw has not read the MB FIFO

AUX_FRAMER_ALWAYS_REP_ACK_FOR_WR.Comment: Autoreply with ACK for write request

AUX_FRAMER_RELEASE_CLR_ON_RCV_SOF.Comment: Release the clear of above FIFO when new aux request is received

AUX_FRAMER_ALWYS_CLR_XMT_FIFO_FOR_WR.Comment: When set it clears XMT MB FIFO for write request on timeout

AUX_FRAMER_ALWYS_CLR_XMT_FIFO_FOR_RD.Comment: When set it clears XMT MB FIFO for read request on timeout

AUX_XMT_MAILBOX_REG_CTRL.Description: AUX transmit Mailbox FIFO Read/Write MUX control.  Accessed on aux_mailbox_intf_clk (27MHz - 270MHz, or DC) domain.

AUX_XMT_MAILBOX_SPIF_THRESH.Comment: Threshold to enable SPIF interface.If RCV mailbox, will enable SPIF DEN when mailbox has 'SPIF_THRESH' or more bytes (or EOF received), and will hold SPIF DEN high until mailbox is empty.if XMT mailbox, will enable SPIF RDY when mailbox has 'SPIF_THRESH' or less bytes, and will hold SPIF RDY high until mailbox is full (or EOF received).

AUX_XMT_MAILBOX_NO_RD_WHEN_MT.Comment: CYA bit for the changed in mailbox logic

AUX_XMT_MAILBOX_REG_RD_CTRL.Comment: Set control source / data target for AUX transmit FIFO reads.0 = SPIF interface1 = AUX_transmit_MAILBOX_FIFO_DATA register

AUX_XMT_MAILBOX_REG_WR_CTRL.Comment: Set control & data source for AUX transmit FIFO writes.0 = SPIF interface1 = AUX_transmit_MAILBOX_FIFO_DATA register

AUX_XMT_MAILBOX_DATA.Description: AUX Mailbox FIFO Read/Write access. Accessed on aux_mailbox_intf_clk (27MHz - 270MHz, or DC) domain.

AUX_XMT_MAILBOX_EOF.Comment: Current write byte is last byte in transaction.

AUX_XMT_MAILBOX_SOF.Comment: Current write byte is 1st byte in transaction.

AUX_XMT_MAILBOX_DAT.Comment: Write or Read byte from mailbox FIFO.

AUX_XMT_MAILBOX_CLR_CTRL.Description: Clear and read-pointer write-triggered control for transmit mailbox FIFO. Accessed on aux_mailbox_intf_clk (27MHz - 270MHz, or DC) domain.

AUX_XMT_MAILBOX_SET_ON_WT.Comment: Read-pointer SET controlled by write-trigger?0 = RD_SET to FIFO always takes value of RD_SET field1 = RD_SET to FIFO is gated w/ WT event.

AUX_XMT_MAILBOX_RST_ON_WT.Comment: Read-pointer RESET controlled by write-trigger?0 = RD_RST to FIFO always takes value of RD_RST field1 = RD_RST to FIFO is gated w/ WT event.

AUX_XMT_MAILBOX_CLR_ON_WT.Comment: Clear controlled by write-trigger?0 = CLR to FIFO always takes value of CLR field1 = CLR to FIFO is gated w/ WT event.

AUX_XMT_MAILBOX_RD_SET.Comment: Set transmit mailbox FIFO base read pointer.

AUX_XMT_MAILBOX_RD_RST.Comment: Reset transmit mailbox FIFO read pointer back to base value.

AUX_XMT_MAILBOX_CLR.Comment: Clear transmit mailbox FIFO read and write pointers.

AUX_RCV_MAILBOX_REG_CTRL.Description: AUX receive Mailbox FIFO Read/Write MUX control.  Accessed on aux_mailbox_intf_clk (27MHz - 270MHz, or DC) domain.

AUX_RCV_MAILBOX_SPIF_THRESH.Comment: Threshold to enable SPIF interface.If RCV mailbox, will enable SPIF DEN when mailbox has 'SPIF_THRESH' or more bytes (or EOF received), and will hold SPIF DEN high until mailbox is empty.if XMT mailbox, will enable SPIF RDY when mailbox has 'SPIF_THRESH' or less bytes, and will hold SPIF RDY high until mailbox is full (or EOF received).

AUX_RCV_MAILBOX_NO_RD_WHEN_MT.Comment: CYA bit for the changed in mailbox logic

AUX_RCV_MAILBOX_REG_RD_CTRL.Comment: Set control source / data target for AUX receive FIFO reads.0 = SPIF interface1 = AUX_receive_MAILBOX_FIFO_DATA register

AUX_RCV_MAILBOX_REG_WR_CTRL.Comment: Set control & data source for AUX receive FIFO writes.0 = SPIF interface1 = AUX_receive_MAILBOX_FIFO_DATA register

AUX_RCV_MAILBOX_DATA.Description: AUX Mailbox FIFO Read/Write access. Accessed on aux_mailbox_intf_clk (27MHz - 270MHz, or DC) domain.

AUX_RCV_MAILBOX_EOF.Comment: Current write byte is last byte in transaction.

AUX_RCV_MAILBOX_SOF.Comment: Current write byte is 1st byte in transaction.

AUX_RCV_MAILBOX_DAT.Comment: Write or Read byte from mailbox FIFO.

AUX_RCV_MAILBOX_CLR_CTRL.Description: Clear and read-pointer write-triggered control for receive mailbox FIFO. Accessed on aux_mailbox_intf_clk (27MHz - 270MHz, or DC) domain.

AUX_RCV_MAILBOX_SET_ON_WT.Comment: Read-pointer SET controlled by write-trigger?0 = RD_SET to FIFO always takes value of RD_SET field1 = RD_SET to FIFO is gated w/ WT event.

AUX_RCV_MAILBOX_RST_ON_WT.Comment: Read-pointer RESET controlled by write-trigger?0 = RD_RST to FIFO always takes value of RD_RST field1 = RD_RST to FIFO is gated w/ WT event.

AUX_RCV_MAILBOX_CLR_ON_WT.Comment: Clear controlled by write-trigger?0 = CLR to FIFO always takes value of CLR field1 = CLR to FIFO is gated w/ WT event.

AUX_RCV_MAILBOX_RD_SET.Comment: Set receive mailbox FIFO base read pointer.

AUX_RCV_MAILBOX_RD_RST.Comment: Reset receive mailbox FIFO read pointer back to base value.

AUX_RCV_MAILBOX_CLR.Comment: Clear receive mailbox FIFO read and write pointers.

AUX_GTC_STEP_SIZE.Description: Step size.  Accessed on aux_mailbox_intf_clk (27MHz - 270MHz, or DC) domain.

AUX_GTC_STEP_SIZE.Comment: GTC step size.  upper 4 bits are integer portion, lower 28 bits are fractional portion.  This should be  1000 / (clk freq in MHz ) .

AUX_GTC_VALUE.Description: Current GTC value.  Accessed on aux_mailbox_intf_clk (27MHz - 270MHz, or DC) domain.

AUX_GTC_FIRST_COMMAND_EDGE.Description: FIRST_COMMAND_EDGE GTC value.  Accessed on aux_mailbox_intf_clk (27MHz - 270MHz, or DC) domain.

AUX_GTC_FIRST_COMMAND_EDGE.Comment: GTC value latched at first differential edge in MAUX COMMAND field.

AUX_GTC_RECEPTION.Comment: GTC value latched at the completion of receiving the GTC value over AUX

AUX_GTC_PHASE_OFFSET.Description: Apply GTC phase offset.  When register is written, value is added from current GTC value.  value treated as signed 2's compliment.  Accessed on aux_mailbox_intf_clk (27MHz - 270MHz, or DC) domain.

AUX_GTC_PHASE_OFFSET.Comment: signed value to add to GTC during phase lock acquisition.

AUX_GTC_CONFIG.Description: GTC configuration.  Accessed on aux_mailbox_intf_clk (27MHz - 270MHz, or DC) domain.

AUX_GTC_LSCLK_PHASE_OFFSET.Comment: Static offset to apply to GTC value when synchronized into LS_CLK, to account for delay through CDC

AUX_GTC_SKEW_OFFSET_ALLOWED.Comment: Allow skew offset from source to be added to the GTC counter

AUX_GTC_NO_DEB_FIRST_EDGE_EN.Comment: Use metaflopped maux_data instead of debounced one to meet firstedge detection within 10ns

AUX_GTC_RESET_EN.Comment: Reset of the local GTC counter to TX_GTC valued enabled

AUX_GTC_APPLY_XMT_FAUX_OFFSET.Comment: Apply FAUX delay/phase offset to local GTC values (1st edge, during XMT)

AUX_GTC_APPLY_XMT_MAUX_OFFSET.Comment: Apply MAUX delay/phase offset to local GTC values (1st edge, during XMT)

AUX_GTC_APPLY_RCV_FAUX_OFFSET.Comment: Apply FAUX delay/phase offset to local GTC values (1st edge, reception, during RCV)

AUX_GTC_APPLY_RCV_MAUX_OFFSET.Comment: Apply MAUX delay/phase offset to local GTC values (1st edge, reception, during RCV)

AUX_GTC_USE_FW_RESET_VALUE.Comment: Use firmware configured value instead of hardware generated one

AUX_GTC_FIRST_EDGE_OF_REPLY_EN.Comment: This is to enable the capture of local gtc value to be sent to source

AUX_GTC_USE_REFERENCE_CNTR.Comment: Use 32-bit input GTC for all operations.  Set this when another AUX port is a GTC slave, and thus is the master/reference GTC for the chip

AUX_GTC_XMT_EN.Comment: Automatically merge GTC when 00057h/00157h is transmitted?

AUX_GTC_RECEPTION_EN.Comment: Store local GTC when external GTC is received?

AUX_GTC_FIRST_EDGE_EN.Comment: Store local GTC @ 1st edge after SYNC?

AUX_GTC_DEN.Comment: GTC Data Enable.  Set this bit when GTC is trained and stable

AUX_GTC_EDGE_CAPTURE_OFFSET.Comment: OFFset added to the reset value for edge capture issue

AUX_GTC_GTX_TX_VALUE.Description: DPCD access register 0. Accessed on aux_mailbox_intf_clk (27MHz - 270MHz, or DC) domain.

AUX_GTC_GTX_PHASE_CTRL.Description: DPCD access register 0. Accessed on aux_mailbox_intf_clk (27MHz - 270MHz, or DC) domain.

AUX_LTTPR_EVENT_TRIGGER.Description: LTTPR ready triggers, write to this register triggers a strobe.

AUX_LTTPR_WR_DONE.Comment: Write to capability or PHy repeater DPCD address space is completed

AUX_LTTPR_RD_DONE.Comment: Non capability LTTPR DPCD address read response is ready

AUX_LTTPR_FW_CONFIG_CAP_UPDATED.Comment: FW has read the reply from DFP and updated it as per its PHY repeater capability

AUX_LTTPR_RESPONSE_TIMEOUT_VAL.Comment: TIMEOUT value for the counter to send DEFER.

AUX_LTTPR_PASS_CMD.Comment: Pass the response: ACK, NACK, DEFER to the UFP.

AUX_LTTPR_UFP_RX_DBG_SEL.Comment: Debug bus select for LTTPR UFP module.

AUX_LTTPR_NONTRANSP_MODE_EN.Comment: When 0xF0003 is written with 0xAA, this register is set.

AUX_LTTPR_ACK_CAP_DPCD_WO_WR_DONE.Comment: Send ACK for capability dpcd address without receiving WR_DONE.

AUX_LTTPR_IGNORE_DAT_RDY_EN.Comment: For capability, DFP data is needed for comparison,we can ignore the DFP data if needed, though not recommended.

AUX_LTTPR_PASS_NON_ACK_RD_REPLY.Comment: For read if ACK is not received then pass the response unmodified

AUX_LTTPR_MISSED_DAT_RDY_ALLOWED.Comment: Firmware triggers RDY after the response is received from DFP

AUX_LTTPR_WR_REPLY_PASS_THRU.Comment: Pass through DFP reply for AUX write request

AUX_LTTPR_SEND_DEFER_WHEN_NOT_RDY.Comment: Send DEFER when Firmware has not responded with RDY

AUX_LTTPR_USE_MAILBOX.Comment: LTTPR request and responses are sent using mailbox

AUX_LTTPR_REPEATER_EN.Comment: LTTPR functionality is enabled for transparent/non-transparent mode

AUX_LTTPR_USE_FW_CONFIG_CAPABILITY.Comment: Firmware configures all the responses for capability/ID address space

SLEEPOUT.Comment: Display State Control%%0A0: Enter Sleep mode%%0A1: Exit Sleep mode

DISP_READY.Comment: Timming Controller reset%%0A1: Release standby reset

DISP_INT_CLR.Comment: Clear display Interupt %%0A[7]: VSYNC1_INT%%0A[6]: VSYNC0_INT%%0A[5]: LED_FIFO1_INT%%0A[4]: LED_FIFO0_INT%%0A[3]: GENERIC1_INT%%0A[2]: GENERIC0_INT%%0A[1]: APO_INT%%0A[0]: FAIL_DET_INT

EDP_LOCK_FLG.Comment: eDP Link Training Lock detection.%%0AFirmware sets this regiser to 1 when eDP link training establish.%%0A0: Unlock%%0A1: Lock

ST0_COEFM_WR_DATA.Comment: Coef Memory Access write data setting(Stream0)

ST0_SHAPEM_WR_DATA.Comment: Shape Memory Access write data setting(Stream0)

ST1_COEFM_WR_DATA.Comment: Coef Memory Access write data setting(Stream1)

ST1_SHAPEM_WR_DATA.Comment: Shape Memory Access write data setting(Stream1)

ST0_LD_BL_DTO_SEL.Comment: LED FIFO Data Out Select%%0A0: IP%%0A1: FIFO

ST1_LD_BL_DTO_SEL.Comment: LED FIFO Data Out Select%%0A0: IP%%0A1: FIFO

OPCODE.Comment: Write a Hydra opcode here to start a vector instruction%%0AThis register always reads as 0

VL.Comment: Vector length%%0AThis and the various address registers are `HYDRA_WIDTH_W bits wide,%%0Aconfigured for each chip based on the size of the chip's RAM address space%%0AFor DIG2409, they are 17 bits wide to address 128KB of RAM

ERROR_WHICH.Comment: Location of reported error%%0A0: General error%%0A1: In src1%%0A2: In src2%%0A3: In src3 or dest2%%0A4: In dest%%0A5: In other opcode field%%0A6: In datapath%%0A7: In SPU

ERROR_REASON.Comment: Type of reported error%%0A0: No error%%0A1: Instruction buffer overrun%%0A2: Invalid opcode%%0A3: Feature not available%%0A4: Invalid CFG%%0A5: Invalid operand%%0A6: Invalid parameter%%0A7: Invalid base address%%0A8: Invalid dimension%%0A9: Bus error%%0A15: Internal fault

ACK_TRREADY.Comment: Write a 1 to clear TRREADY condition

ACK_TRIDLE.Comment: Write a 1 to clear TRIDLE condition

ACK_ERROR.Comment: Write a 1 to clear ERROR condition

ACK_DONE.Comment: Write a 1 to clear DONE condition

NREADY.Comment: Read-only complement of the READY bit

RESET.Comment: Write a 1 to reset Hydra to idle state

TRREADY.Comment: Read-only flag, set upon a transition from BUSY state to READY or IDLE

TRIDLE.Comment: Read-only flag, set upon a transition to BUSY or READY state to IdLE

ERROR.Comment: Read-only flag, set when any error is detected

DONE.Comment: Read-only flag, set when an instruction finishes

READY.Comment: Reads as 1 when the instruction buffer is READY or IDLE%%0AThis means Hydra is ready to accept a new instruction in OPCODE

IDLE.Comment: Reads as 1 when the instruction buffer is IDLE%%0AThis means Hydra has finished all pending vector instructions or SPU programs

EN_TRREADY.Comment: If 1, TRREADY condition asserts a CPU interrupt

EN_TRIDLE.Comment: If 1, TRIDLE condition asserts a CPU interrupt

EN_ERROR.Comment: If 1, ERROR condition asserts a CPU interrupt

EN_DONE.Comment: If 1, DONE condition asserts a CPU interrupt

EN_READY.Comment: If 1, READY condition asserts a CPU interrupt

EN_IDLE.Comment: If 1, IDLE condition asserts a CPU interrupt

PRIV_ONLY.Comment: If 1, only privileged firmware can read/write Hydra registers

DIS_JOIN.Comment: If 1, instruction joining feature is inhibited

DIS_HSHAKE.Comment: If 1, read/write handshake stalls are inhibited for OPCODE, G0, and G1

EN_WADDR.Comment: If 1, enable word address compatibility mode  (Chimera systems only)

ROUND.Comment: Rounding mode for arithmetic%%0A0: Round to nearest, ties to even  (standard IEEE rounding)%%0A1: Round toward zero%%0A2: Round upward (toward +infinity)%%0A3: Round downward (toward -infinity)%%0A4: Round to nearest, ties toward +infinity%%0A5: Round to nearest, ties away from zero%%0A6: Round away from zero

EVENT.Comment: Type of event to count%%0A0: None (counter is disabled)%%0A1: Count each instruction posted to instruction buffer%%0A2: Count each cycle that reports an error%%0A3: Count each cycle when pipeline stalls%%0A4: Count all cycles when Hydra is active%%0A5: Count all cycles when Hydra's ALU is active%%0A6: Count all cycles when SPU is active%%0A7: Count each instruction posted while ERROR is already true%%0A8: Count vector iterations processed

HYDRA_STATUS.Description: Status flags from recent vector operations%%0AAfter each status-producing vector instruction completes, these bits change to 1 to indicate when at least one vector iteration had the indicated kind of result%%0AThese bits will change back to 0 only when firmware writes to STATUS

NZERO.Comment: Mathematical result was not exactly zero

INEXACT.Comment: Result was inexact  (significant bits were lost to rounding or overflow)

UNDERFLOW.Comment: Result underflowed  (too near zero to be represented)

OVERFLOW.Comment: Result overflowed  (too large in magnitude to be represented)

COMPAT_OPCODE.Comment: Write a Hydra 3-style opcode here to start an instruction%%0AThis register always reads as 0

VMCNT.Comment: Vector mask population count%%0AAfter each mask-using or mask-producing instruction completes, this register updates with a count of the active bits in the mask.
